154void RenderBox::willBeDestroyed()
155{
156 if (frame().eventHandler().autoscrollRenderer() == this)
157 frame().eventHandler().stopAutoscrollTimer(true);
158
159 clearOverridingContentSize();
160 clearOverridingContainingBlockContentSize();
161
162 RenderBlock::removePercentHeightDescendantIfNeeded(*this);
163
164 ShapeOutsideInfo::removeInfo(*this);
165
166 view().unscheduleLazyRepaint(*this);
167 removeControlStatesForRenderer(*this);
168
169 if (hasInitializedStyle() && style().hasSnapPosition())
170 view().unregisterBoxWithScrollSnapPositions(*this);
171
172 RenderBoxModelObject::willBeDestroyed();
173}

175RenderFragmentContainer* RenderBox::clampToStartAndEndFragments(RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
176{
177 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
178
179 ASSERT(isRenderView() || (fragment && fragmentedFlow));
180 if (isRenderView())
181 return fragment;
182
183 // We need to clamp to the block, since we want any lines or blocks that overflow out of the
184 // logical top or logical bottom of the block to size as though the border box in the first and
185 // last fragments extended infinitely. Otherwise the lines are going to size according to the fragments
186 // they overflow into, which makes no sense when this block doesn't exist in |fragment| at all.
187 RenderFragmentContainer* startFragment = nullptr;
188 RenderFragmentContainer* endFragment = nullptr;
189 if (!fragmentedFlow->getFragmentRangeForBox(this, startFragment, endFragment))
190 return fragment;
191
192 if (fragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent() < startFragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent())
193 return startFragment;
194 if (fragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent() > endFragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent())
195 return endFragment;
196
197 return fragment;
198}
199
200bool RenderBox::hasFragmentRangeInFragmentedFlow() const
201{
202 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
203 if (!fragmentedFlow || !fragmentedFlow->hasValidFragmentInfo())
204 return false;
205
206 return fragmentedFlow->hasCachedFragmentRangeForBox(*this);
207}

209LayoutRect RenderBox::clientBoxRectInFragment(RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
210{
211 if (!fragment)
212 return clientBoxRect();
213
214 LayoutRect clientBox = borderBoxRectInFragment(fragment);
215 clientBox.setLocation(clientBox.location() + LayoutSize(borderLeft(), borderTop()));
216 clientBox.setSize(clientBox.size() - LayoutSize(borderLeft() + borderRight() + verticalScrollbarWidth(), borderTop() + borderBottom() + horizontalScrollbarHeight()));
217
218 return clientBox;
219}
220
221LayoutRect RenderBox::borderBoxRectInFragment(RenderFragmentContainer*, RenderBoxFragmentInfoFlags) const
222{
223 return borderBoxRect();
224}

226static RenderBlockFlow* outermostBlockContainingFloatingObject(RenderBox& box)
227{
228 ASSERT(box.isFloating());
229 RenderBlockFlow* parentBlock = nullptr;
230 for (auto& ancestor : ancestorsOfType<RenderBlockFlow>(box)) {
231 if (!parentBlock || ancestor.containsFloat(box))
232 parentBlock = &ancestor;
233 }
234 return parentBlock;
235}
236
237void RenderBox::removeFloatingOrPositionedChildFromBlockLists()
238{
239 ASSERT(isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned());
240
241 if (renderTreeBeingDestroyed())
242 return;
243
244 if (isFloating()) {
245 if (RenderBlockFlow* parentBlock = outermostBlockContainingFloatingObject(*this)) {
246 parentBlock->markSiblingsWithFloatsForLayout(this);
247 parentBlock->markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout(this, false);
248 }
249 }
250
251 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned())
252 RenderBlock::removePositionedObject(*this);
253}

255void RenderBox::styleWillChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
256{
257 s_hadOverflowClip = hasOverflowClip();
258
259 const RenderStyle* oldStyle = hasInitializedStyle() ? &style() : nullptr;
260 if (oldStyle) {
261 // The background of the root element or the body element could propagate up to
262 // the canvas. Issue full repaint, when our style changes substantially.
263 if (diff >= StyleDifference::Repaint && (isDocumentElementRenderer() || isBody())) {
264 view().repaintRootContents();
265 if (oldStyle->hasEntirelyFixedBackground() != newStyle.hasEntirelyFixedBackground())
266 view().compositor().rootLayerConfigurationChanged();
267 }
268
269 // When a layout hint happens and an object's position style changes, we have to do a layout
270 // to dirty the render tree using the old position value now.
271 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout && parent() && oldStyle->position() != newStyle.position()) {
272 markContainingBlocksForLayout();
273 if (oldStyle->position() != PositionType::Static && newStyle.hasOutOfFlowPosition())
274 parent()->setChildNeedsLayout();
275 if (isFloating() && !isOutOfFlowPositioned() && newStyle.hasOutOfFlowPosition())
276 removeFloatingOrPositionedChildFromBlockLists();
277 }
278 } else if (isBody())
279 view().repaintRootContents();
280
281 bool boxContributesSnapPositions = newStyle.hasSnapPosition();
282 if (boxContributesSnapPositions || (oldStyle && oldStyle->hasSnapPosition())) {
283 if (boxContributesSnapPositions)
284 view().registerBoxWithScrollSnapPositions(*this);
285 else
286 view().unregisterBoxWithScrollSnapPositions(*this);
287 }
288
289 RenderBoxModelObject::styleWillChange(diff, newStyle);
290}
291
292void RenderBox::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
293{
294 // Horizontal writing mode definition is updated in RenderBoxModelObject::updateFromStyle,
295 // (as part of the RenderBoxModelObject::styleDidChange call below). So, we can safely cache the horizontal
296 // writing mode value before style change here.
297 bool oldHorizontalWritingMode = isHorizontalWritingMode();
298
299 RenderBoxModelObject::styleDidChange(diff, oldStyle);
300
301 const RenderStyle& newStyle = style();
302 if (needsLayout() && oldStyle) {
303 RenderBlock::removePercentHeightDescendantIfNeeded(*this);
304
305 // Normally we can do optimized positioning layout for absolute/fixed positioned objects. There is one special case, however, which is
306 // when the positioned object's margin-before is changed. In this case the parent has to get a layout in order to run margin collapsing
307 // to determine the new static position.
308 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned() && newStyle.hasStaticBlockPosition(isHorizontalWritingMode()) && oldStyle->marginBefore() != newStyle.marginBefore()
309 && parent() && !parent()->normalChildNeedsLayout())
310 parent()->setChildNeedsLayout();
311 }
312
313 if (RenderBlock::hasPercentHeightContainerMap() && firstChild()
314 && oldHorizontalWritingMode != isHorizontalWritingMode())
315 RenderBlock::clearPercentHeightDescendantsFrom(*this);
316
317 // If our zoom factor changes and we have a defined scrollLeft/Top, we need to adjust that value into the
318 // new zoomed coordinate space.
319 if (hasOverflowClip() && layer() && oldStyle && oldStyle->effectiveZoom() != newStyle.effectiveZoom()) {
320 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer()->scrollableArea()) {
321 ScrollPosition scrollPosition = scrollableArea->scrollPosition();
322 float zoomScaleFactor = newStyle.effectiveZoom() / oldStyle->effectiveZoom();
323 scrollPosition.scale(zoomScaleFactor);
324 scrollableArea->setPostLayoutScrollPosition(scrollPosition);
325 }
326 }
327
328 // Our opaqueness might have changed without triggering layout.
329 if (diff >= StyleDifference::Repaint && diff <= StyleDifference::RepaintLayer) {
330 auto parentToInvalidate = parent();
331 for (unsigned i = 0; i < backgroundObscurationTestMaxDepth && parentToInvalidate; ++i) {
332 parentToInvalidate->invalidateBackgroundObscurationStatus();
333 parentToInvalidate = parentToInvalidate->parent();
334 }
335 }
336
337 bool isBodyRenderer = isBody();
338 bool isDocElementRenderer = isDocumentElementRenderer();
339
340 if (isDocElementRenderer || isBodyRenderer) {
341 // Propagate the new writing mode and direction up to the RenderView.
342 auto* documentElementRenderer = document().documentElement()->renderer();
343 auto& viewStyle = view().mutableStyle();
344 bool rootStyleChanged = false;
345 bool viewDirectionOrWritingModeChanged = false;
346 auto* rootRenderer = isBodyRenderer ? documentElementRenderer : nullptr;
347 if (viewStyle.direction() != newStyle.direction() && (isDocElementRenderer || !documentElementRenderer->style().hasExplicitlySetDirection())) {
348 viewStyle.setDirection(newStyle.direction());
349 viewDirectionOrWritingModeChanged = true;
350 if (isBodyRenderer) {
351 rootRenderer->mutableStyle().setDirection(newStyle.direction());
352 rootStyleChanged = true;
353 }
354 setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
355
356 view().frameView().topContentDirectionDidChange();
357 }
358
359 if (viewStyle.writingMode() != newStyle.writingMode() && (isDocElementRenderer || !documentElementRenderer->style().hasExplicitlySetWritingMode())) {
360 viewStyle.setWritingMode(newStyle.writingMode());
361 viewDirectionOrWritingModeChanged = true;
362 view().setHorizontalWritingMode(newStyle.isHorizontalWritingMode());
363 view().markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
364 if (isBodyRenderer) {
365 rootStyleChanged = true;
366 rootRenderer->mutableStyle().setWritingMode(newStyle.writingMode());
367 rootRenderer->setHorizontalWritingMode(newStyle.isHorizontalWritingMode());
368 }
369 setNeedsLayoutAndPrefWidthsRecalc();
370 }
371
372#if ENABLE(DARK_MODE_CSS)
373 view().frameView().recalculateBaseBackgroundColor();
374#endif
375
376 view().frameView().recalculateScrollbarOverlayStyle();
377
378 const Pagination& pagination = view().frameView().pagination();
379 if (viewDirectionOrWritingModeChanged && pagination.mode != Pagination::Unpaginated) {
380 viewStyle.setColumnStylesFromPaginationMode(pagination.mode);
381 if (view().multiColumnFlow())
382 view().updateColumnProgressionFromStyle(viewStyle);
383 }
384
385 if (viewDirectionOrWritingModeChanged && view().multiColumnFlow())
386 view().updateStylesForColumnChildren();
387
388 if (rootStyleChanged && is<RenderBlockFlow>(rootRenderer) && downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*rootRenderer).multiColumnFlow())
389 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*rootRenderer).updateStylesForColumnChildren();
390
391 if (isBodyRenderer && pagination.mode != Pagination::Unpaginated && page().paginationLineGridEnabled()) {
392 // Propagate the body font back up to the RenderView and use it as
393 // the basis of the grid.
394 if (newStyle.fontDescription() != view().style().fontDescription()) {
395 view().mutableStyle().setFontDescription(FontCascadeDescription { newStyle.fontDescription() });
396 view().mutableStyle().fontCascade().update(&document().fontSelector());
397 }
398 }
399
400 if (diff != StyleDifference::Equal)
401 view().compositor().rootOrBodyStyleChanged(*this, oldStyle);
402 }
403
404 if ((oldStyle && oldStyle->shapeOutside()) || style().shapeOutside())
405 updateShapeOutsideInfoAfterStyleChange(style(), oldStyle);
406 updateGridPositionAfterStyleChange(style(), oldStyle);
407
408 // Changing the position from/to absolute can potentially create/remove flex/grid items, as absolutely positioned
409 // children of a flex/grid box are out-of-flow, and thus, not flex/grid items. This means that we need to clear
410 // any override content size set by our container, because it would likely be incorrect after the style change.
411 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned() && parent() && parent()->style().isDisplayFlexibleOrGridBox())
412 clearOverridingContentSize();
413
414#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
415 if (diff >= StyleDifference::Repaint) {
416 if (auto* lineLayout = LayoutIntegration::LineLayout::containing(*this))
417 lineLayout->updateStyle(*this);
418 }
419#endif
420}
421
422void RenderBox::updateGridPositionAfterStyleChange(const RenderStyle& style, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
423{
424 if (!oldStyle || !is<RenderGrid>(parent()))
425 return;
426
427 if (oldStyle->gridItemColumnStart() == style.gridItemColumnStart()
428 && oldStyle->gridItemColumnEnd() == style.gridItemColumnEnd()
429 && oldStyle->gridItemRowStart() == style.gridItemRowStart()
430 && oldStyle->gridItemRowEnd() == style.gridItemRowEnd()
431 && oldStyle->order() == style.order()
432 && oldStyle->hasOutOfFlowPosition() == style.hasOutOfFlowPosition())
433 return;
434
435 // Positioned items don't participate on the layout of the grid,
436 // so we don't need to mark the grid as dirty if they change positions.
437 if (oldStyle->hasOutOfFlowPosition() && style.hasOutOfFlowPosition())
438 return;
439
440 // It should be possible to not dirty the grid in some cases (like moving an
441 // explicitly placed grid item).
442 // For now, it's more simple to just always recompute the grid.
443 downcast<RenderGrid>(*parent()).dirtyGrid();
444}
445
446void RenderBox::updateShapeOutsideInfoAfterStyleChange(const RenderStyle& style, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
447{
448 const ShapeValue* shapeOutside = style.shapeOutside();
449 const ShapeValue* oldShapeOutside = oldStyle ? oldStyle->shapeOutside() : nullptr;
450
451 Length shapeMargin = style.shapeMargin();
452 Length oldShapeMargin = oldStyle ? oldStyle->shapeMargin() : RenderStyle::initialShapeMargin();
453
454 float shapeImageThreshold = style.shapeImageThreshold();
455 float oldShapeImageThreshold = oldStyle ? oldStyle->shapeImageThreshold() : RenderStyle::initialShapeImageThreshold();
456
457 // FIXME: A future optimization would do a deep comparison for equality. (bug 100811)
458 if (shapeOutside == oldShapeOutside && shapeMargin == oldShapeMargin && shapeImageThreshold == oldShapeImageThreshold)
459 return;
460
461 if (!shapeOutside)
462 ShapeOutsideInfo::removeInfo(*this);
463 else
464 ShapeOutsideInfo::ensureInfo(*this).markShapeAsDirty();
465
466 if (shapeOutside || shapeOutside != oldShapeOutside)
467 markShapeOutsideDependentsForLayout();
468}
469
470void RenderBox::updateFromStyle()
471{
472 RenderBoxModelObject::updateFromStyle();
473
474 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
475 bool isDocElementRenderer = isDocumentElementRenderer();
476 bool isViewObject = isRenderView();
477
478 // The root and the RenderView always paint their backgrounds/borders.
479 if (isDocElementRenderer || isViewObject)
480 setHasVisibleBoxDecorations(true);
481
482 setFloating(!isOutOfFlowPositioned() && styleToUse.isFloating());
483
484 // We also handle <body> and <html>, whose overflow applies to the viewport.
485 if (styleToUse.overflowX() != Overflow::Visible && !isDocElementRenderer && isRenderBlock()) {
486 bool boxHasOverflowClip = true;
487 if (isBody()) {
488 // Overflow on the body can propagate to the viewport under the following conditions.
489 // (1) The root element is <html>.
490 // (2) We are the primary <body> (can be checked by looking at document.body).
491 // (3) The root element has visible overflow.
492 if (is<HTMLHtmlElement>(*document().documentElement())
493 && document().body() == element()
494 && document().documentElement()->renderer()->style().overflowX() == Overflow::Visible) {
495 boxHasOverflowClip = false;
496 }
497 }
498 // Check for overflow clip.
499 // It's sufficient to just check one direction, since it's illegal to have visible on only one overflow value.
500 if (boxHasOverflowClip) {
501 if (!s_hadOverflowClip && hasRenderOverflow()) {
502 // Erase the overflow.
503 // Overflow changes have to result in immediate repaints of the entire layout overflow area because
504 // repaints issued by removal of descendants get clipped using the updated style when they shouldn't.
505 repaintRectangle(visualOverflowRect());
506 repaintRectangle(layoutOverflowRect());
507 }
508 setHasOverflowClip();
509 }
510 }
511 setHasTransformRelatedProperty(styleToUse.hasTransformRelatedProperty());
512 setHasReflection(styleToUse.boxReflect());
513}
514
515void RenderBox::layout()
516{
517 StackStats::LayoutCheckPoint layoutCheckPoint;
518 ASSERT(needsLayout());
519
520 RenderObject* child = firstChild();
521 if (!child) {
522 clearNeedsLayout();
523 return;
524 }
525
526 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode());
527 while (child) {
528 if (child->needsLayout())
529 downcast<RenderElement>(*child).layout();
530 ASSERT(!child->needsLayout());
531 child = child->nextSibling();
532 }
533 invalidateBackgroundObscurationStatus();
534 clearNeedsLayout();
535}

548
549int RenderBox::scrollWidth() const
550{
551 if (hasOverflowClip() && layer())
552 return layer()->scrollWidth();
553 // For objects with visible overflow, this matches IE.
554 // FIXME: Need to work right with writing modes.
555 if (style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
556 // FIXME: This should use snappedIntSize() instead with absolute coordinates.
557 return roundToInt(std::max(clientWidth(), layoutOverflowRect().maxX() - borderLeft()));
558 }
559 return roundToInt(clientWidth() - std::min<LayoutUnit>(0, layoutOverflowRect().x() - borderLeft()));
560}
561
562int RenderBox::scrollHeight() const
563{
564 if (hasOverflowClip() && layer())
565 return layer()->scrollHeight();
566 // For objects with visible overflow, this matches IE.
567 // FIXME: Need to work right with writing modes.
568 // FIXME: This should use snappedIntSize() instead with absolute coordinates.
569 return roundToInt(std::max(clientHeight(), layoutOverflowRect().maxY() - borderTop()));
570}

572int RenderBox::scrollLeft() const
573{
574 auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;
575 return (hasOverflowClip() && scrollableArea) ? scrollableArea->scrollPosition().x() : 0;
576}

578int RenderBox::scrollTop() const
579{
580 auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;

582}

633void RenderBox::absoluteQuads(Vector<FloatQuad>& quads, bool* wasFixed) const
634{
635 FloatRect localRect(0, 0, width(), height());
636
637 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
638 if (fragmentedFlow && fragmentedFlow->absoluteQuadsForBox(quads, wasFixed, this, localRect.y(), localRect.maxY()))
639 return;
640
641 quads.append(localToAbsoluteQuad(localRect, UseTransforms, wasFixed));
642}

651LayoutUnit RenderBox::constrainLogicalWidthInFragmentByMinMax(LayoutUnit logicalWidth, LayoutUnit availableWidth, RenderBlock& cb, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment, AllowIntrinsic allowIntrinsic) const
652{
653 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
654
655 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio()) {
656 auto [logicalMinWidth, logicalMaxWidth] = computeMinMaxLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
657 logicalWidth = std::clamp(logicalWidth, logicalMinWidth, logicalMaxWidth);
658 }
659
660 if (!styleToUse.logicalMaxWidth().isUndefined() && (allowIntrinsic == AllowIntrinsic::Yes || !styleToUse.logicalMaxWidth().isIntrinsic()))
661 logicalWidth = std::min(logicalWidth, computeLogicalWidthInFragmentUsing(MaxSize, styleToUse.logicalMaxWidth(), availableWidth, cb, fragment));
662 if (allowIntrinsic == AllowIntrinsic::No && styleToUse.logicalMinWidth().isIntrinsic())
663 return logicalWidth;
664 auto minLength = styleToUse.logicalMinWidth();
665 if (styleToUse.hasAspectRatio() && minLength.isAuto() && (styleToUse.logicalWidth().isAuto() || styleToUse.logicalWidth().isMinContent() || styleToUse.logicalWidth().isMaxContent()) && styleToUse.overflowInlineDirection() == Overflow::Visible) {
666 // Make sure we actually used the aspect ratio.
667 if (shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio())
668 minLength = Length(LengthType::MinIntrinsic);
669 }
670 return std::max(logicalWidth, computeLogicalWidthInFragmentUsing(MinSize, minLength, availableWidth, cb, fragment));
671}
672
673LayoutUnit RenderBox::constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(LayoutUnit logicalHeight, std::optional<LayoutUnit> intrinsicContentHeight) const
674{
675 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
676 if (!styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight().isUndefined()) {
677 if (std::optional<LayoutUnit> maxH = computeLogicalHeightUsing(MaxSize, styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight(), intrinsicContentHeight))
678 logicalHeight = std::min(logicalHeight, maxH.value());
679 }
680 auto logicalMinHeight = styleToUse.logicalMinHeight();
681 if (logicalMinHeight.isAuto() && shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio() && intrinsicContentHeight && styleToUse.overflowBlockDirection() == Overflow::Visible)
682 logicalMinHeight = Length(*intrinsicContentHeight, LengthType::Fixed);
683 if (logicalMinHeight.isMinContent() || logicalMinHeight.isMaxContent())
684 logicalMinHeight = Length();
685 if (std::optional<LayoutUnit> computedLogicalHeight = computeLogicalHeightUsing(MinSize, logicalMinHeight, intrinsicContentHeight))
686 return std::max(logicalHeight, computedLogicalHeight.value());
687 return logicalHeight;
688}
689
690LayoutUnit RenderBox::constrainContentBoxLogicalHeightByMinMax(LayoutUnit logicalHeight, std::optional<LayoutUnit> intrinsicContentHeight) const
691{
692 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
693 if (!styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight().isUndefined()) {
694 if (std::optional<LayoutUnit> maxH = computeContentLogicalHeight(MaxSize, styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight(), intrinsicContentHeight))
695 logicalHeight = std::min(logicalHeight, maxH.value());
696 }
697 if (std::optional<LayoutUnit> computedContentLogicalHeight = computeContentLogicalHeight(MinSize, styleToUse.logicalMinHeight(), intrinsicContentHeight))
698 return std::max(logicalHeight, computedContentLogicalHeight.value());
699 return logicalHeight;
700}

702RoundedRect::Radii RenderBox::borderRadii() const
703{
704 auto& style = this->style();
705 LayoutRect bounds = frameRect();
706
707 unsigned borderLeft = style.borderLeftWidth();
708 unsigned borderTop = style.borderTopWidth();
709 bounds.moveBy(LayoutPoint(borderLeft, borderTop));
710 bounds.contract(borderLeft + style.borderRightWidth(), borderTop + style.borderBottomWidth());
711 return style.getRoundedBorderFor(bounds).radii();
712}

719LayoutRect RenderBox::paddingBoxRect() const
720{

740LayoutRect RenderBox::referenceBox(CSSBoxType boxType) const
741{
742 LayoutRect referenceBox;
743 switch (boxType) {
744 case CSSBoxType::ContentBox:
745 case CSSBoxType::FillBox:
746 return contentBoxRect();
747 case CSSBoxType::PaddingBox:
748 return paddingBoxRect();
749 case CSSBoxType::MarginBox:
750 return marginBoxRect();
751 // stroke-box, view-box compute to border-box for HTML elements.
752 case CSSBoxType::StrokeBox:
753 case CSSBoxType::ViewBox:
754 case CSSBoxType::BorderBox:
755 case CSSBoxType::BoxMissing:
756 return borderBoxRect();

758 return { };

776LayoutRect RenderBox::outlineBoundsForRepaint(const RenderLayerModelObject* repaintContainer, const RenderGeometryMap* geometryMap) const
777{
778 LayoutRect box = borderBoundingBox();
779 adjustRectForOutlineAndShadow(box);
780
781 if (repaintContainer != this) {
782 FloatQuad containerRelativeQuad;
783 if (geometryMap)
784 containerRelativeQuad = geometryMap->mapToContainer(box, repaintContainer);
785 else
786 containerRelativeQuad = localToContainerQuad(FloatRect(box), repaintContainer);
787
788 box = LayoutRect(containerRelativeQuad.boundingBox());
789 }
790
791 // FIXME: layoutDelta needs to be applied in parts before/after transforms and
792 // repaint containers. https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=23308
793 box.move(view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutDelta());
794
795 return LayoutRect(snapRectToDevicePixels(box, document().deviceScaleFactor()));
796}

804int RenderBox::reflectionOffset() const
805{
806 if (!style().boxReflect())
807 return 0;
808 if (style().boxReflect()->direction() == ReflectionDirection::Left || style().boxReflect()->direction() == ReflectionDirection::Right)
809 return valueForLength(style().boxReflect()->offset(), borderBoxRect().width());
810 return valueForLength(style().boxReflect()->offset(), borderBoxRect().height());
811}
812
813LayoutRect RenderBox::reflectedRect(const LayoutRect& r) const
814{
815 if (!style().boxReflect())
816 return LayoutRect();
817
818 LayoutRect box = borderBoxRect();
819 LayoutRect result = r;
820 switch (style().boxReflect()->direction()) {
821 case ReflectionDirection::Below:
822 result.setY(box.maxY() + reflectionOffset() + (box.maxY() - r.maxY()));
823 break;
824 case ReflectionDirection::Above:
825 result.setY(box.y() - reflectionOffset() - box.height() + (box.maxY() - r.maxY()));
826 break;
827 case ReflectionDirection::Left:
828 result.setX(box.x() - reflectionOffset() - box.width() + (box.maxX() - r.maxX()));
829 break;
830 case ReflectionDirection::Right:
831 result.setX(box.maxX() + reflectionOffset() + (box.maxX() - r.maxX()));
832 break;
833 }
834 return result;
835}

888bool RenderBox::scrollLayer(ScrollDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, float multiplier, Element** stopElement)
889{
890 auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;
891 if (scrollableArea && scrollableArea->scroll(direction, granularity, multiplier)) {
892 if (stopElement)
893 *stopElement = element();
894
895 return true;
896 }
897
898 return false;
899}
900
901bool RenderBox::scroll(ScrollDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, float multiplier, Element** stopElement, RenderBox* startBox, const IntPoint& wheelEventAbsolutePoint)
902{
903 if (scrollLayer(direction, granularity, multiplier, stopElement))
904 return true;
905
906 if (stopElement && *stopElement && *stopElement == element())
907 return true;
908
909 RenderBlock* nextScrollBlock = containingBlock();
910
911 if (nextScrollBlock && !nextScrollBlock->isRenderView())
912 return nextScrollBlock->scroll(direction, granularity, multiplier, stopElement, startBox, wheelEventAbsolutePoint);
913
914 return false;
915}
916
917bool RenderBox::logicalScroll(ScrollLogicalDirection direction, ScrollGranularity granularity, float multiplier, Element** stopElement)
918{
919 bool scrolled = false;
920
921 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr) {
922#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
923 // On Mac only we reset the inline direction position when doing a document scroll (e.g., hitting Home/End).
924 if (granularity == ScrollByDocument)
925 scrolled = scrollableArea->scroll(logicalToPhysical(ScrollInlineDirectionBackward, isHorizontalWritingMode(), style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode()), ScrollByDocument, multiplier);
926#endif
927 if (scrollableArea->scroll(logicalToPhysical(direction, isHorizontalWritingMode(), style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode()), granularity, multiplier))
928 scrolled = true;
929
930 if (scrolled) {
931 if (stopElement)
932 *stopElement = element();
933 return true;
934 }
935 }
936
937 if (stopElement && *stopElement && *stopElement == element())
938 return true;
939
940 RenderBlock* b = containingBlock();
941 if (b && !b->isRenderView())
942 return b->logicalScroll(direction, granularity, multiplier, stopElement);
943 return false;
944}

1000// There are two kinds of renderer that can autoscroll.
1001bool RenderBox::canAutoscroll() const
1002{
1003 if (isRenderView())
1004 return view().frameView().isScrollable();
1005

1008 return true;
1009

1012
1013// If specified point is in border belt, returned offset denotes direction of
1014// scrolling.
1015IntSize RenderBox::calculateAutoscrollDirection(const IntPoint& windowPoint) const
1016{
1017 IntRect box(absoluteBoundingBoxRect());
1018 box.moveBy(view().frameView().scrollPosition());
1019 IntRect windowBox = view().frameView().contentsToWindow(box);
1020
1021 IntPoint windowAutoscrollPoint = windowPoint;
1022
1023 if (windowAutoscrollPoint.x() < windowBox.x() + autoscrollBeltSize)
1024 windowAutoscrollPoint.move(-autoscrollBeltSize, 0);
1025 else if (windowAutoscrollPoint.x() > windowBox.maxX() - autoscrollBeltSize)
1026 windowAutoscrollPoint.move(autoscrollBeltSize, 0);
1027
1028 if (windowAutoscrollPoint.y() < windowBox.y() + autoscrollBeltSize)
1029 windowAutoscrollPoint.move(0, -autoscrollBeltSize);
1030 else if (windowAutoscrollPoint.y() > windowBox.maxY() - autoscrollBeltSize)
1031 windowAutoscrollPoint.move(0, autoscrollBeltSize);
1032
1033 return windowAutoscrollPoint - windowPoint;
1034}
1035
1036RenderBox* RenderBox::findAutoscrollable(RenderObject* renderer)
1037{
1038 while (renderer && !(is<RenderBox>(*renderer) && downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).canAutoscroll())) {
1039 if (is<RenderView>(*renderer) && renderer->document().ownerElement())
1040 renderer = renderer->document().ownerElement()->renderer();
1041 else
1042 renderer = renderer->parent();
1043 }
1044
1045 return is<RenderBox>(renderer) ? downcast<RenderBox>(renderer) : nullptr;
1046}

1059bool RenderBox::hasAutoScrollbar(ScrollbarOrientation orientation) const
1060{
1061 if (!hasOverflowClip())
1062 return false;
1063
1064 auto isAutoOrScrollWithOverlayScrollbar = [&](Overflow overflow) {
1065 return overflow == Overflow::Auto || (overflow == Overflow::Scroll && canUseOverlayScrollbars());
1066 };
1067
1068 switch (orientation) {
1069 case ScrollbarOrientation::HorizontalScrollbar:
1070 return isAutoOrScrollWithOverlayScrollbar(style().overflowX());
1071 case ScrollbarOrientation::VerticalScrollbar:
1072 return isAutoOrScrollWithOverlayScrollbar(style().overflowY());
1073 }
1074 return false;
1075}

1078{
1079 if (!hasOverflowClip())
1080 return false;
1081
1082 auto isAlwaysVisibleScrollbar = [&](Overflow overflow) {
1083 return overflow == Overflow::Scroll && !canUseOverlayScrollbars();
1084 };
1085
1086 switch (orientation) {
1087 case ScrollbarOrientation::HorizontalScrollbar:
1088 return isAlwaysVisibleScrollbar(style().overflowX());
1089 case ScrollbarOrientation::VerticalScrollbar:
1090 return isAlwaysVisibleScrollbar(style().overflowY());
1091 }
1092 return false;

1119
1120bool RenderBox::applyCachedClipAndScrollPosition(LayoutRect& rect, const RenderLayerModelObject* container, VisibleRectContext context) const
1121{
1122 flipForWritingMode(rect);
1123
1124 if (context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedContainerScrolls) || this != container || !usesCompositedScrolling())
1125 rect.moveBy(-scrollPosition()); // For overflow:auto/scroll/hidden.
1126
1127 // Do not clip scroll layer contents to reduce the number of repaints while scrolling.
1128 if ((!context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedClips) && usesCompositedScrolling())
1129 || (!context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyContainerClip) && this == container)) {
1130 flipForWritingMode(rect);
1131 return true;
1132 }
1133
1134 // height() is inaccurate if we're in the middle of a layout of this RenderBox, so use the
1135 // layer's size instead. Even if the layer's size is wrong, the layer itself will repaint
1136 // anyway if its size does change.
1137 LayoutRect clipRect(LayoutPoint(), cachedSizeForOverflowClip());
1138 bool intersects;
1139 if (context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::UseEdgeInclusiveIntersection))
1140 intersects = rect.edgeInclusiveIntersect(clipRect);
1141 else {
1142 rect.intersect(clipRect);
1143 intersects = !rect.isEmpty();
1144 }
1145 flipForWritingMode(rect);
1146 return intersects;
1147}

1314LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(const Length& logicalWidth) const
1315{
1316 auto width = LayoutUnit { logicalWidth.value() };
1317 LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding = borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
1318 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::ContentBox || logicalWidth.isIntrinsicOrAuto())
1319 return width + bordersPlusPadding;
1320 return std::max(width, bordersPlusPadding);
1321}
1322
1323LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(LayoutUnit computedLogicalWidth, LengthType originalType) const
1324{
1325 if (originalType == LengthType::Calculated)
1326 return adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing({ computedLogicalWidth, LengthType::Fixed, false });
1327 return adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing({ computedLogicalWidth, originalType, false });
1328}
1329
1330LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustBorderBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(LayoutUnit height) const
1331{
1332 LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
1333 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::ContentBox)
1334 return height + bordersPlusPadding;
1335 return std::max(height, bordersPlusPadding);
1336}
1337
1338LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(const Length& logicalWidth) const
1339{
1340 auto width = LayoutUnit { logicalWidth.value() };
1341 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::ContentBox || logicalWidth.isIntrinsicOrAuto())
1342 return std::max(0_lu, width);
1343 return std::max(0_lu, width - borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth());
1344}
1345
1346LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(LayoutUnit computedLogicalWidth, LengthType originalType) const
1347{
1348 if (originalType == LengthType::Calculated)
1349 return adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing({ computedLogicalWidth, LengthType::Fixed, false });
1350 return adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing({ computedLogicalWidth, originalType, false });
1351}

1353LayoutUnit RenderBox::adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(std::optional<LayoutUnit> height) const
1354{
1355 if (!height)
1356 return 0;
1357 LayoutUnit result = height.value();
1358 if (style().boxSizing() == BoxSizing::BorderBox)
1359 result -= borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();

1363// Hit Testing
1364bool RenderBox::hitTestVisualOverflow(const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset) const
1365{
1366 if (isRenderView())
1367 return true;
1368
1369 LayoutPoint adjustedLocation = accumulatedOffset + location();
1370 LayoutRect overflowBox = visualOverflowRect();
1371 flipForWritingMode(overflowBox);
1372 overflowBox.moveBy(adjustedLocation);
1373 return hitTestLocation.intersects(overflowBox);
1374}
1375
1376bool RenderBox::hitTestClipPath(const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset) const
1377{
1378 if (!style().clipPath())
1379 return true;
1380
1381 auto offsetFromHitTestRoot = toLayoutSize(accumulatedOffset + location());
1382 auto hitTestLocationInLocalCoordinates = hitTestLocation.point() - offsetFromHitTestRoot;
1383 switch (style().clipPath()->type()) {
1384 case ClipPathOperation::Shape: {
1385 auto& clipPath = downcast<ShapeClipPathOperation>(*style().clipPath());
1386 auto referenceBoxRect = referenceBox(clipPath.referenceBox());
1387 if (!clipPath.pathForReferenceRect(referenceBoxRect).contains(hitTestLocationInLocalCoordinates, clipPath.windRule()))
1388 return false;
1389 break;
1390 }
1391 case ClipPathOperation::Reference: {
1392 const auto& referenceClipPathOperation = downcast<ReferenceClipPathOperation>(*style().clipPath());
1393 auto* element = document().getElementById(referenceClipPathOperation.fragment());
1394 if (!element || !element->renderer())
1395 break;
1396 if (!is<SVGClipPathElement>(*element))
1397 break;
1398 auto& clipper = downcast<RenderSVGResourceClipper>(*element->renderer());
1399 if (!clipper.hitTestClipContent(FloatRect(borderBoxRect()), FloatPoint { hitTestLocationInLocalCoordinates }))
1400 return false;
1401 break;
1402 }
1403 case ClipPathOperation::Box:
1404 break;
1405 }
1406
1407 return true;
1408}
1409
1410bool RenderBox::hitTestBorderRadius(const HitTestLocation& hitTestLocation, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset) const
1411{
1412 if (isRenderView() || !style().hasBorderRadius())
1413 return true;
1414
1415 LayoutPoint adjustedLocation = accumulatedOffset + location();
1416 LayoutRect borderRect = borderBoxRect();
1417 borderRect.moveBy(adjustedLocation);
1418 RoundedRect border = style().getRoundedBorderFor(borderRect);
1419 return hitTestLocation.intersects(border);
1420}
1421
1422bool RenderBox::nodeAtPoint(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset, HitTestAction action)
1423{
1424 LayoutPoint adjustedLocation = accumulatedOffset + location();
1425
1426 // Check kids first.
1427 for (RenderObject* child = lastChild(); child; child = child->previousSibling()) {
1428 if (!child->hasLayer() && child->nodeAtPoint(request, result, locationInContainer, adjustedLocation, action)) {
1429 updateHitTestResult(result, locationInContainer.point() - toLayoutSize(adjustedLocation));
1430 return true;
1431 }
1432 }
1433
1434 // Check our bounds next. For this purpose always assume that we can only be hit in the
1435 // foreground phase (which is true for replaced elements like images).
1436 LayoutRect boundsRect = borderBoxRectInFragment(nullptr);
1437 boundsRect.moveBy(adjustedLocation);
1438 if (visibleToHitTesting(request) && action == HitTestForeground && locationInContainer.intersects(boundsRect)) {
1439 if (!hitTestVisualOverflow(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
1440 return false;
1441
1442 if (!hitTestClipPath(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
1443 return false;
1444
1445 if (!hitTestBorderRadius(locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset))
1446 return false;
1447
1448 updateHitTestResult(result, locationInContainer.point() - toLayoutSize(adjustedLocation));
1449 if (result.addNodeToListBasedTestResult(nodeForHitTest(), request, locationInContainer, boundsRect) == HitTestProgress::Stop)
1450 return true;
1451 }
1452
1453 return RenderBoxModelObject::nodeAtPoint(request, result, locationInContainer, accumulatedOffset, action);
1454}

1457
1458void RenderBox::paintRootBoxFillLayers(const PaintInfo& paintInfo)
1459{
1460 ASSERT(isDocumentElementRenderer());
1461 if (paintInfo.skipRootBackground())
1462 return;
1463
1464 auto* rootBackgroundRenderer = view().rendererForRootBackground();
1465 if (!rootBackgroundRenderer)
1466 return;
1467
1468 auto& style = rootBackgroundRenderer->style();
1469 auto color = style.visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1470 auto compositeOp = document().compositeOperatorForBackgroundColor(color, *this);
1471
1472 paintFillLayers(paintInfo, style.colorByApplyingColorFilter(color), style.backgroundLayers(), view().backgroundRect(), BackgroundBleedNone, compositeOp, rootBackgroundRenderer);
1473}
1474
1475BackgroundBleedAvoidance RenderBox::determineBackgroundBleedAvoidance(GraphicsContext& context) const
1476{
1477 if (context.paintingDisabled())
1478 return BackgroundBleedNone;
1479
1480 const RenderStyle& style = this->style();
1481
1482 if (!style.hasBackground() || !style.hasBorder() || !style.hasBorderRadius() || borderImageIsLoadedAndCanBeRendered())
1483 return BackgroundBleedNone;
1484
1485 AffineTransform ctm = context.getCTM();
1486 FloatSize contextScaling(static_cast<float>(ctm.xScale()), static_cast<float>(ctm.yScale()));
1487
1488 // Because RoundedRect uses IntRect internally the inset applied by the
1489 // BackgroundBleedShrinkBackground strategy cannot be less than one integer
1490 // layout coordinate, even with subpixel layout enabled. To take that into
1491 // account, we clamp the contextScaling to 1.0 for the following test so
1492 // that borderObscuresBackgroundEdge can only return true if the border
1493 // widths are greater than 2 in both layout coordinates and screen
1494 // coordinates.
1495 // This precaution will become obsolete if RoundedRect is ever promoted to
1496 // a sub-pixel representation.
1497 if (contextScaling.width() > 1)
1498 contextScaling.setWidth(1);
1499 if (contextScaling.height() > 1)
1500 contextScaling.setHeight(1);
1501
1502 if (borderObscuresBackgroundEdge(contextScaling))
1503 return BackgroundBleedShrinkBackground;
1504 if (!style.hasAppearance() && borderObscuresBackground() && backgroundHasOpaqueTopLayer())
1505 return BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder;
1506
1507 return BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer;
1508}
1509
1510void RenderBox::paintBoxDecorations(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1511{
1512 if (!paintInfo.shouldPaintWithinRoot(*this))
1513 return;
1514
1515 LayoutRect paintRect = borderBoxRectInFragment(nullptr);
1516 paintRect.moveBy(paintOffset);
1517 adjustBorderBoxRectForPainting(paintRect);
1518
1519 paintRect = theme().adjustedPaintRect(*this, paintRect);
1520 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance = determineBackgroundBleedAvoidance(paintInfo.context());
1521
1522 // FIXME: Should eventually give the theme control over whether the box shadow should paint, since controls could have
1523 // custom shadows of their own.
1524 if (!boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(paintRect.location(), bleedAvoidance))
1525 paintBoxShadow(paintInfo, paintRect, style(), ShadowStyle::Normal);
1526
1527 GraphicsContextStateSaver stateSaver(paintInfo.context(), false);
1528 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer) {
1529 // To avoid the background color bleeding out behind the border, we'll render background and border
1530 // into a transparency layer, and then clip that in one go (which requires setting up the clip before
1531 // beginning the layer).
1532 stateSaver.save();
1533 paintInfo.context().clipRoundedRect(style().getRoundedBorderFor(paintRect).pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(document().deviceScaleFactor()));
1534 paintInfo.context().beginTransparencyLayer(1);
1535 }
1536
1537 // If we have a native theme appearance, paint that before painting our background.
1538 // The theme will tell us whether or not we should also paint the CSS background.
1539 bool borderOrBackgroundPaintingIsNeeded = true;
1540 if (style().hasAppearance()) {
1541 ControlStates* controlStates = controlStatesForRenderer(*this);
1542 borderOrBackgroundPaintingIsNeeded = theme().paint(*this, *controlStates, paintInfo, paintRect);
1543 if (controlStates->needsRepaint())
1544 view().scheduleLazyRepaint(*this);
1545 }
1546
1547 if (borderOrBackgroundPaintingIsNeeded) {
1548 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder)
1549 paintBorder(paintInfo, paintRect, style(), bleedAvoidance);
1550
1551 paintBackground(paintInfo, paintRect, bleedAvoidance);
1552
1553 if (style().hasAppearance())
1554 theme().paintDecorations(*this, paintInfo, paintRect);
1555 }
1556 paintBoxShadow(paintInfo, paintRect, style(), ShadowStyle::Inset);
1557
1558 // The theme will tell us whether or not we should also paint the CSS border.
1559 if (bleedAvoidance != BackgroundBleedBackgroundOverBorder && (!style().hasAppearance() || (borderOrBackgroundPaintingIsNeeded && theme().paintBorderOnly(*this, paintInfo, paintRect))) && style().hasVisibleBorderDecoration())
1560 paintBorder(paintInfo, paintRect, style(), bleedAvoidance);
1561
1562 if (bleedAvoidance == BackgroundBleedUseTransparencyLayer)
1563 paintInfo.context().endTransparencyLayer();
1564}
1565
1566bool RenderBox::paintsOwnBackground() const
1567{
1568 if (isBody()) {
1569 // The <body> only paints its background if the root element has defined a background independent of the body,
1570 // or if the <body>'s parent is not the document element's renderer (e.g. inside SVG foreignObject).
1571 auto documentElementRenderer = document().documentElement()->renderer();
1572 return !documentElementRenderer
1573 || documentElementRenderer->hasBackground()
1574 || (documentElementRenderer != parent());
1575 }
1576
1577 return true;
1578}
1579
1580void RenderBox::paintBackground(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutRect& paintRect, BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance)
1581{
1582 if (isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
1583 paintRootBoxFillLayers(paintInfo);
1584 return;
1585 }
1586
1587 if (!paintsOwnBackground())
1588 return;
1589
1590 if (backgroundIsKnownToBeObscured(paintRect.location()) && !boxShadowShouldBeAppliedToBackground(paintRect.location(), bleedAvoidance))
1591 return;
1592
1593 auto backgroundColor = style().visitedDependentColor(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1594 auto compositeOp = document().compositeOperatorForBackgroundColor(backgroundColor, *this);
1595
1596 paintFillLayers(paintInfo, style().colorByApplyingColorFilter(backgroundColor), style().backgroundLayers(), paintRect, bleedAvoidance, compositeOp);
1597}
1598
1599bool RenderBox::getBackgroundPaintedExtent(const LayoutPoint& paintOffset, LayoutRect& paintedExtent) const
1600{
1601 ASSERT(hasBackground());
1602 LayoutRect backgroundRect = snappedIntRect(borderBoxRect());
1603
1604 Color backgroundColor = style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1605 if (backgroundColor.isVisible()) {
1606 paintedExtent = backgroundRect;
1607 return true;
1608 }
1609
1610 auto& layers = style().backgroundLayers();
1611 if (!layers.image() || layers.next()) {
1612 paintedExtent = backgroundRect;
1613 return true;
1614 }
1615
1616 auto geometry = calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(nullptr, layers, paintOffset, backgroundRect);
1617 paintedExtent = geometry.destRect();
1618 return !geometry.hasNonLocalGeometry();
1619}
1620
1621bool RenderBox::backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(const LayoutRect& localRect) const
1622{
1623 if (!paintsOwnBackground())
1624 return false;
1625
1626 Color backgroundColor = style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1627 if (!backgroundColor.isOpaque())
1628 return false;
1629
1630 // If the element has appearance, it might be painted by theme.
1631 // We cannot be sure if theme paints the background opaque.
1632 // In this case it is safe to not assume opaqueness.
1633 // FIXME: May be ask theme if it paints opaque.
1634 if (style().hasAppearance())
1635 return false;
1636 // FIXME: Check the opaqueness of background images.
1637
1638 if (hasClip() || hasClipPath())
1639 return false;
1640
1641 // FIXME: Use rounded rect if border radius is present.
1642 if (style().hasBorderRadius())
1643 return false;
1644
1645 // FIXME: The background color clip is defined by the last layer.
1646 if (style().backgroundLayers().next())
1647 return false;
1648 LayoutRect backgroundRect;
1649 switch (style().backgroundClip()) {
1650 case FillBox::Border:
1651 backgroundRect = borderBoxRect();
1652 break;
1653 case FillBox::Padding:
1654 backgroundRect = paddingBoxRect();
1655 break;
1656 case FillBox::Content:
1657 backgroundRect = contentBoxRect();
1658 break;
1659 default:
1660 break;
1661 }
1662 return backgroundRect.contains(localRect);
1663}
1664
1665static bool isCandidateForOpaquenessTest(const RenderBox& childBox)
1666{
1667 const RenderStyle& childStyle = childBox.style();
1668 if (childStyle.position() != PositionType::Static && childBox.containingBlock() != childBox.parent())
1669 return false;
1670 if (childStyle.visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
1671 return false;
1672 if (childStyle.shapeOutside())
1673 return false;
1674 if (!childBox.width() || !childBox.height())
1675 return false;
1676 if (RenderLayer* childLayer = childBox.layer()) {
1677 if (childLayer->isComposited())
1678 return false;
1679 // FIXME: Deal with z-index.
1680 if (!childStyle.hasAutoUsedZIndex())
1681 return false;
1682 if (childLayer->hasTransform() || childLayer->isTransparent() || childLayer->hasFilter())
1683 return false;
1684 if (!childBox.scrollPosition().isZero())
1685 return false;
1686 }
1687 return true;
1688}
1689
1690bool RenderBox::foregroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(const LayoutRect& localRect, unsigned maxDepthToTest) const
1691{
1692 if (!maxDepthToTest)
1693 return false;
1694
1695 for (auto& childBox : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
1696 if (!isCandidateForOpaquenessTest(childBox))
1697 continue;
1698 LayoutPoint childLocation = childBox.location();
1699 if (childBox.isRelativelyPositioned())
1700 childLocation.move(childBox.relativePositionOffset());
1701 LayoutRect childLocalRect = localRect;
1702 childLocalRect.moveBy(-childLocation);
1703 if (childLocalRect.y() < 0 || childLocalRect.x() < 0) {
1704 // If there is unobscured area above/left of a static positioned box then the rect is probably not covered.
1705 if (childBox.style().position() == PositionType::Static)
1706 return false;
1707 continue;
1708 }
1709 if (childLocalRect.maxY() > childBox.height() || childLocalRect.maxX() > childBox.width())
1710 continue;
1711 if (childBox.backgroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(childLocalRect))
1712 return true;
1713 if (childBox.foregroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(childLocalRect, maxDepthToTest - 1))
1714 return true;
1715 }
1716 return false;
1717}
1718
1719bool RenderBox::computeBackgroundIsKnownToBeObscured(const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1720{
1721 // Test to see if the children trivially obscure the background.
1722 // FIXME: This test can be much more comprehensive.
1723 if (!hasBackground())
1724 return false;
1725 // Table and root background painting is special.
1726 if (isTable() || isDocumentElementRenderer())
1727 return false;
1728
1729 LayoutRect backgroundRect;
1730 if (!getBackgroundPaintedExtent(paintOffset, backgroundRect))
1731 return false;
1732
1733 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr) {
1734 if (scrollableArea->scrollingMayRevealBackground())
1735 return false;
1736 }
1737 return foregroundIsKnownToBeOpaqueInRect(backgroundRect, backgroundObscurationTestMaxDepth);
1738}
1739
1740bool RenderBox::backgroundHasOpaqueTopLayer() const
1741{
1742 auto& fillLayer = style().backgroundLayers();
1743 if (fillLayer.clip() != FillBox::Border)
1744 return false;
1745
1746 // Clipped with local scrolling
1747 if (hasOverflowClip() && fillLayer.attachment() == FillAttachment::LocalBackground)
1748 return false;
1749
1750 if (fillLayer.hasOpaqueImage(*this) && fillLayer.hasRepeatXY() && fillLayer.image()->canRender(this, style().effectiveZoom()))
1751 return true;
1752
1753 // If there is only one layer and no image, check whether the background color is opaque.
1754 if (!fillLayer.next() && !fillLayer.hasImage()) {
1755 Color bgColor = style().visitedDependentColorWithColorFilter(CSSPropertyBackgroundColor);
1756 if (bgColor.isOpaque())
1757 return true;
1758 }
1759
1760 return false;
1761}

1781
1782void RenderBox::paintMaskImages(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutRect& paintRect)
1783{
1784 // Figure out if we need to push a transparency layer to render our mask.
1785 bool pushTransparencyLayer = false;
1786 bool compositedMask = hasLayer() && layer()->hasCompositedMask();
1787 bool flattenCompositingLayers = paintInfo.paintBehavior.contains(PaintBehavior::FlattenCompositingLayers);
1788 CompositeOperator compositeOp = CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
1789
1790 bool allMaskImagesLoaded = true;
1791
1792 if (!compositedMask || flattenCompositingLayers) {
1793 pushTransparencyLayer = true;
1794
1795 // Don't render a masked element until all the mask images have loaded, to prevent a flash of unmasked content.
1796 if (auto* maskBoxImage = style().maskBoxImage().image())
1797 allMaskImagesLoaded &= maskBoxImage->isLoaded();
1798
1799 allMaskImagesLoaded &= style().maskLayers().imagesAreLoaded();
1800
1801 paintInfo.context().setCompositeOperation(CompositeOperator::DestinationIn);
1802 paintInfo.context().beginTransparencyLayer(1);
1803 compositeOp = CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
1804 }
1805
1806 if (allMaskImagesLoaded) {
1807 paintFillLayers(paintInfo, Color(), style().maskLayers(), paintRect, BackgroundBleedNone, compositeOp);
1808 paintNinePieceImage(paintInfo.context(), paintRect, style(), style().maskBoxImage(), compositeOp);
1809 }
1810
1811 if (pushTransparencyLayer)
1812 paintInfo.context().endTransparencyLayer();
1813}
1814
1815LayoutRect RenderBox::maskClipRect(const LayoutPoint& paintOffset)
1816{
1817 const NinePieceImage& maskBoxImage = style().maskBoxImage();
1818 if (maskBoxImage.image()) {
1819 LayoutRect borderImageRect = borderBoxRect();
1820
1821 // Apply outsets to the border box.
1822 borderImageRect.expand(style().maskBoxImageOutsets());
1823 return borderImageRect;
1824 }
1825
1826 LayoutRect result;
1827 LayoutRect borderBox = borderBoxRect();
1828 for (auto* maskLayer = &style().maskLayers(); maskLayer; maskLayer = maskLayer->next()) {
1829 if (maskLayer->image()) {
1830 // Masks should never have fixed attachment, so it's OK for paintContainer to be null.
1831 result.unite(calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(nullptr, *maskLayer, paintOffset, borderBox).destRect());
1832 }
1833 }
1834 return result;
1835}
1836
1837void RenderBox::paintFillLayers(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const Color& color, const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutRect& rect,
1838 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, CompositeOperator op, RenderElement* backgroundObject)
1839{
1840 Vector<const FillLayer*, 8> layers;
1841 bool shouldDrawBackgroundInSeparateBuffer = false;
1842
1843 for (auto* layer = &fillLayer; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
1844 layers.append(layer);
1845
1846 if (layer->blendMode() != BlendMode::Normal)
1847 shouldDrawBackgroundInSeparateBuffer = true;
1848
1849 // Stop traversal when an opaque layer is encountered.
1850 // FIXME: It would be possible for the following occlusion culling test to be more aggressive
1851 // on layers with no repeat by testing whether the image covers the layout rect.
1852 // Testing that here would imply duplicating a lot of calculations that are currently done in
1853 // RenderBoxModelObject::paintFillLayerExtended. A more efficient solution might be to move
1854 // the layer recursion into paintFillLayerExtended, or to compute the layer geometry here
1855 // and pass it down.
1856
1857 // The clipOccludesNextLayers condition must be evaluated first to avoid short-circuiting.
1858 if (layer->clipOccludesNextLayers(layer == &fillLayer) && layer->hasOpaqueImage(*this) && layer->image()->canRender(this, style().effectiveZoom()) && layer->hasRepeatXY() && layer->blendMode() == BlendMode::Normal)
1859 break;
1860 }
1861
1862 auto& context = paintInfo.context();
1863 auto baseBgColorUsage = BaseBackgroundColorUse;
1864
1865 if (shouldDrawBackgroundInSeparateBuffer) {
1866 paintFillLayer(paintInfo, color, *layers.last(), rect, bleedAvoidance, op, backgroundObject, BaseBackgroundColorOnly);
1867 baseBgColorUsage = BaseBackgroundColorSkip;
1868 context.beginTransparencyLayer(1);
1869 }
1870
1871 auto topLayer = layers.rend();
1872 for (auto it = layers.rbegin(); it != topLayer; ++it)
1873 paintFillLayer(paintInfo, color, **it, rect, bleedAvoidance, op, backgroundObject, baseBgColorUsage);
1874
1875 if (shouldDrawBackgroundInSeparateBuffer)
1876 context.endTransparencyLayer();
1877}
1878
1879void RenderBox::paintFillLayer(const PaintInfo& paintInfo, const Color& c, const FillLayer& fillLayer, const LayoutRect& rect,
1880 BackgroundBleedAvoidance bleedAvoidance, CompositeOperator op, RenderElement* backgroundObject, BaseBackgroundColorUsage baseBgColorUsage)
1881{
1882 paintFillLayerExtended(paintInfo, c, fillLayer, rect, bleedAvoidance, nullptr, LayoutSize(), op, backgroundObject, baseBgColorUsage);
1883}
1884
1885static StyleImage* findLayerUsedImage(WrappedImagePtr image, const FillLayer& layers)
1886{
1887 for (auto* layer = &layers; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
1888 if (layer->image() && image == layer->image()->data())
1889 return layer->image();
1890 }
1891 return nullptr;
1892}
1893
1894void RenderBox::imageChanged(WrappedImagePtr image, const IntRect*)
1895{
1896 if (!parent())
1897 return;
1898
1899 if ((style().borderImage().image() && style().borderImage().image()->data() == image) ||
1900 (style().maskBoxImage().image() && style().maskBoxImage().image()->data() == image)) {
1901 repaint();
1902 return;
1903 }
1904
1905 ShapeValue* shapeOutsideValue = style().shapeOutside();
1906 if (!view().frameView().layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout() && isFloating() && shapeOutsideValue && shapeOutsideValue->image() && shapeOutsideValue->image()->data() == image) {
1907 ShapeOutsideInfo::ensureInfo(*this).markShapeAsDirty();
1908 markShapeOutsideDependentsForLayout();
1909 }
1910
1911 bool didFullRepaint = repaintLayerRectsForImage(image, style().backgroundLayers(), true);
1912 if (!didFullRepaint)
1913 repaintLayerRectsForImage(image, style().maskLayers(), false);
1914
1915 if (!isComposited())
1916 return;
1917
1918 if (layer()->hasCompositedMask() && findLayerUsedImage(image, style().maskLayers()))
1919 layer()->contentChanged(MaskImageChanged);
1920
1921 if (auto* styleImage = findLayerUsedImage(image, style().backgroundLayers())) {
1922 layer()->contentChanged(BackgroundImageChanged);
1923 incrementVisuallyNonEmptyPixelCountIfNeeded(flooredIntSize(styleImage->imageSize(this, style().effectiveZoom())));
1924 }

1935
1936bool RenderBox::repaintLayerRectsForImage(WrappedImagePtr image, const FillLayer& layers, bool drawingBackground)
1937{
1938 LayoutRect rendererRect;
1939 RenderBox* layerRenderer = nullptr;
1940
1941 for (auto* layer = &layers; layer; layer = layer->next()) {
1942 if (layer->image() && image == layer->image()->data() && (layer->image()->isLoaded() || layer->image()->canRender(this, style().effectiveZoom()))) {
1943 // Now that we know this image is being used, compute the renderer and the rect if we haven't already.
1944 bool drawingRootBackground = drawingBackground && (isDocumentElementRenderer() || (isBody() && !document().documentElement()->renderer()->hasBackground()));
1945 if (!layerRenderer) {
1946 if (drawingRootBackground) {
1947 layerRenderer = &view();
1948
1949 LayoutUnit rw = downcast<RenderView>(*layerRenderer).frameView().contentsWidth();
1950 LayoutUnit rh = downcast<RenderView>(*layerRenderer).frameView().contentsHeight();
1951
1952 rendererRect = LayoutRect(-layerRenderer->marginLeft(),
1953 -layerRenderer->marginTop(),
1954 std::max(layerRenderer->width() + layerRenderer->horizontalMarginExtent() + layerRenderer->borderLeft() + layerRenderer->borderRight(), rw),
1955 std::max(layerRenderer->height() + layerRenderer->verticalMarginExtent() + layerRenderer->borderTop() + layerRenderer->borderBottom(), rh));
1956 } else {
1957 layerRenderer = this;
1958 rendererRect = borderBoxRect();
1959 }
1960 }
1961 // FIXME: Figure out how to pass absolute position to calculateBackgroundImageGeometry (for pixel snapping)
1962 BackgroundImageGeometry geometry = layerRenderer->calculateBackgroundImageGeometry(nullptr, *layer, LayoutPoint(), rendererRect);
1963 if (geometry.hasNonLocalGeometry()) {
1964 // Rather than incur the costs of computing the paintContainer for renderers with fixed backgrounds
1965 // in order to get the right destRect, just repaint the entire renderer.
1966 layerRenderer->repaint();
1967 return true;
1968 }
1969
1970 LayoutRect rectToRepaint = geometry.destRect();
1971 bool shouldClipToLayer = true;
1972
1973 // If this is the root background layer, we may need to extend the repaintRect if the FrameView has an
1974 // extendedBackground. We should only extend the rect if it is already extending the full width or height
1975 // of the rendererRect.
1976 if (drawingRootBackground && view().frameView().hasExtendedBackgroundRectForPainting()) {
1977 shouldClipToLayer = false;
1978 IntRect extendedBackgroundRect = view().frameView().extendedBackgroundRectForPainting();
1979 if (rectToRepaint.width() == rendererRect.width()) {
1980 rectToRepaint.move(extendedBackgroundRect.x(), 0);
1981 rectToRepaint.setWidth(extendedBackgroundRect.width());
1982 }
1983 if (rectToRepaint.height() == rendererRect.height()) {
1984 rectToRepaint.move(0, extendedBackgroundRect.y());
1985 rectToRepaint.setHeight(extendedBackgroundRect.height());
1986 }
1987 }
1988
1989 layerRenderer->repaintRectangle(rectToRepaint, shouldClipToLayer);
1990 if (geometry.destRect() == rendererRect)
1991 return true;
1992 }
1993 }
1994 return false;
1995}
1996
1997bool RenderBox::pushContentsClip(PaintInfo& paintInfo, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset)
1998{
1999 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::BlockBackground || paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::SelfOutline || paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Mask)
2000 return false;
2001
2002 bool isControlClip = hasControlClip();
2003 bool isOverflowClip = hasOverflowClip() && !layer()->isSelfPaintingLayer();
2004
2005 if (!isControlClip && !isOverflowClip)
2006 return false;
2007
2008 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::Outline)
2009 paintInfo.phase = PaintPhase::ChildOutlines;
2010 else if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground) {
2011 paintInfo.phase = PaintPhase::BlockBackground;
2012 paintObject(paintInfo, accumulatedOffset);
2013 paintInfo.phase = PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackgrounds;
2014 }
2015 float deviceScaleFactor = document().deviceScaleFactor();
2016 FloatRect clipRect = snapRectToDevicePixels((isControlClip ? controlClipRect(accumulatedOffset) : overflowClipRect(accumulatedOffset, nullptr, IgnoreOverlayScrollbarSize, paintInfo.phase)), deviceScaleFactor);
2017 paintInfo.context().save();
2018 if (style().hasBorderRadius())
2019 paintInfo.context().clipRoundedRect(style().getRoundedInnerBorderFor(LayoutRect(accumulatedOffset, size())).pixelSnappedRoundedRectForPainting(deviceScaleFactor));
2020 paintInfo.context().clip(clipRect);
2021
2022 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::EventRegion)
2023 paintInfo.eventRegionContext->pushClip(enclosingIntRect(clipRect));
2024
2025 return true;
2026}
2027
2028void RenderBox::popContentsClip(PaintInfo& paintInfo, PaintPhase originalPhase, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset)
2029{
2030 ASSERT(hasControlClip() || (hasOverflowClip() && !layer()->isSelfPaintingLayer()));
2031
2032 if (paintInfo.phase == PaintPhase::EventRegion)
2033 paintInfo.eventRegionContext->popClip();
2034
2035 paintInfo.context().restore();
2036 if (originalPhase == PaintPhase::Outline) {
2037 paintInfo.phase = PaintPhase::SelfOutline;
2038 paintObject(paintInfo, accumulatedOffset);
2039 paintInfo.phase = originalPhase;
2040 } else if (originalPhase == PaintPhase::ChildBlockBackground)
2041 paintInfo.phase = originalPhase;
2042}

2044LayoutRect RenderBox::overflowClipRect(const LayoutPoint& location, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment, OverlayScrollbarSizeRelevancy relevancy, PaintPhase) const
2045{
2046 // FIXME: When overflow-clip (CSS3) is implemented, we'll obtain the property
2047 // here.
2048 LayoutRect clipRect = borderBoxRectInFragment(fragment);
2049 clipRect.setLocation(location + clipRect.location() + LayoutSize(borderLeft(), borderTop()));
2050 clipRect.setSize(clipRect.size() - LayoutSize(borderLeft() + borderRight(), borderTop() + borderBottom()));
2051
2052 // Subtract out scrollbars if we have them.
2053 if (auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr) {
2054 if (shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft())
2055 clipRect.move(scrollableArea->verticalScrollbarWidth(relevancy), 0);
2056 clipRect.contract(scrollableArea->verticalScrollbarWidth(relevancy), scrollableArea->horizontalScrollbarHeight(relevancy));
2057 }
2058
2059 return clipRect;
2060}
2061
2062LayoutRect RenderBox::clipRect(const LayoutPoint& location, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
2063{
2064 LayoutRect borderBoxRect = borderBoxRectInFragment(fragment);
2065 LayoutRect clipRect = LayoutRect(borderBoxRect.location() + location, borderBoxRect.size());
2066
2067 if (!style().clipLeft().isAuto()) {
2068 LayoutUnit c = valueForLength(style().clipLeft(), borderBoxRect.width());
2069 clipRect.move(c, 0_lu);
2070 clipRect.contract(c, 0_lu);
2071 }
2072
2073 // We don't use the fragment-specific border box's width and height since clip offsets are (stupidly) specified
2074 // from the left and top edges. Therefore it's better to avoid constraining to smaller widths and heights.
2075
2076 if (!style().clipRight().isAuto())
2077 clipRect.contract(width() - valueForLength(style().clipRight(), width()), 0_lu);
2078
2079 if (!style().clipTop().isAuto()) {
2080 LayoutUnit c = valueForLength(style().clipTop(), borderBoxRect.height());
2081 clipRect.move(0_lu, c);
2082 clipRect.contract(0_lu, c);
2083 }
2084
2085 if (!style().clipBottom().isAuto())
2086 clipRect.contract(0_lu, height() - valueForLength(style().clipBottom(), height()));
2087
2088 return clipRect;
2089}
2090
2091LayoutUnit RenderBox::shrinkLogicalWidthToAvoidFloats(LayoutUnit childMarginStart, LayoutUnit childMarginEnd, const RenderBlock& cb, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
2092{
2093 RenderFragmentContainer* containingBlockFragment = nullptr;
2094 LayoutUnit logicalTopPosition = logicalTop();
2095 if (fragment) {
2096 LayoutUnit offsetFromLogicalTopOfFragment = fragment ? fragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent() - offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() : 0_lu;
2097 logicalTopPosition = std::max(logicalTopPosition, logicalTopPosition + offsetFromLogicalTopOfFragment);
2098 containingBlockFragment = cb.clampToStartAndEndFragments(fragment);
2099 }
2100
2101 LayoutUnit logicalHeight = cb.logicalHeightForChild(*this);
2102 LayoutUnit result = cb.availableLogicalWidthForLineInFragment(logicalTopPosition, DoNotIndentText, containingBlockFragment, logicalHeight) - childMarginStart - childMarginEnd;
2103
2104 // We need to see if margins on either the start side or the end side can contain the floats in question. If they can,
2105 // then just using the line width is inaccurate. In the case where a float completely fits, we don't need to use the line
2106 // offset at all, but can instead push all the way to the content edge of the containing block. In the case where the float
2107 // doesn't fit, we can use the line offset, but we need to grow it by the margin to reflect the fact that the margin was
2108 // "consumed" by the float. Negative margins aren't consumed by the float, and so we ignore them.
2109 if (childMarginStart > 0) {
2110 LayoutUnit startContentSide = cb.startOffsetForContent(containingBlockFragment);
2111 LayoutUnit startContentSideWithMargin = startContentSide + childMarginStart;
2112 LayoutUnit startOffset = cb.startOffsetForLineInFragment(logicalTopPosition, DoNotIndentText, containingBlockFragment, logicalHeight);
2113 if (startOffset > startContentSideWithMargin)
2114 result += childMarginStart;
2115 else
2116 result += startOffset - startContentSide;
2117 }
2118
2119 if (childMarginEnd > 0) {
2120 LayoutUnit endContentSide = cb.endOffsetForContent(containingBlockFragment);
2121 LayoutUnit endContentSideWithMargin = endContentSide + childMarginEnd;
2122 LayoutUnit endOffset = cb.endOffsetForLineInFragment(logicalTopPosition, DoNotIndentText, containingBlockFragment, logicalHeight);
2123 if (endOffset > endContentSideWithMargin)
2124 result += childMarginEnd;
2125 else
2126 result += endOffset - endContentSide;
2127 }
2128
2129 return result;
2130}

2214
2215void RenderBox::mapLocalToContainer(const RenderLayerModelObject* ancestorContainer, TransformState& transformState, MapCoordinatesFlags mode, bool* wasFixed) const
2216{
2217 if (ancestorContainer == this)
2218 return;
2219
2220 if (!ancestorContainer && view().frameView().layoutContext().isPaintOffsetCacheEnabled()) {
2221 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
2222 LayoutSize offset = layoutState->paintOffset() + locationOffset();
2223 if (style().hasInFlowPosition() && layer())
2224 offset += layer()->offsetForInFlowPosition();
2225 transformState.move(offset);
2226 return;
2227 }
2228
2229 bool containerSkipped;
2230 RenderElement* container = this->container(ancestorContainer, containerSkipped);
2231 if (!container)
2232 return;
2233
2234 bool isFixedPos = isFixedPositioned();
2235 // If this box has a transform, it acts as a fixed position container for fixed descendants,
2236 // and may itself also be fixed position. So propagate 'fixed' up only if this box is fixed position.
2237 if (hasTransform() && !isFixedPos)
2238 mode &= ~IsFixed;
2239 else if (isFixedPos)
2240 mode |= IsFixed;
2241
2242 if (wasFixed)
2243 *wasFixed = mode & IsFixed;
2244
2245 LayoutSize containerOffset = offsetFromContainer(*container, LayoutPoint(transformState.mappedPoint()));
2246
2247 bool preserve3D = mode & UseTransforms && (container->style().preserves3D() || style().preserves3D());
2248 if (mode & UseTransforms && shouldUseTransformFromContainer(container)) {
2249 TransformationMatrix t;
2250 getTransformFromContainer(container, containerOffset, t);
2251 transformState.applyTransform(t, preserve3D ? TransformState::AccumulateTransform : TransformState::FlattenTransform);
2252 } else
2253 transformState.move(containerOffset.width(), containerOffset.height(), preserve3D ? TransformState::AccumulateTransform : TransformState::FlattenTransform);
2254
2255 if (containerSkipped) {
2256 // There can't be a transform between ancestorContainer and o, because transforms create containers, so it should be safe
2257 // to just subtract the delta between the ancestorContainer and o.
2258 LayoutSize containerOffset = ancestorContainer->offsetFromAncestorContainer(*container);
2259 transformState.move(-containerOffset.width(), -containerOffset.height(), preserve3D ? TransformState::AccumulateTransform : TransformState::FlattenTransform);
2260 return;
2261 }
2262
2263 mode &= ~ApplyContainerFlip;
2264
2265 container->mapLocalToContainer(ancestorContainer, transformState, mode, wasFixed);
2266}
2267
2268const RenderObject* RenderBox::pushMappingToContainer(const RenderLayerModelObject* ancestorToStopAt, RenderGeometryMap& geometryMap) const
2269{
2270 ASSERT(ancestorToStopAt != this);
2271
2272 bool ancestorSkipped;
2273 RenderElement* container = this->container(ancestorToStopAt, ancestorSkipped);
2274 if (!container)
2275 return nullptr;
2276
2277 bool isFixedPos = isFixedPositioned();
2278 LayoutSize adjustmentForSkippedAncestor;
2279 if (ancestorSkipped) {
2280 // There can't be a transform between repaintContainer and container, because transforms create containers, so it should be safe
2281 // to just subtract the delta between the ancestor and container.
2282 adjustmentForSkippedAncestor = -ancestorToStopAt->offsetFromAncestorContainer(*container);
2283 }
2284
2285 bool offsetDependsOnPoint = false;
2286 LayoutSize containerOffset = offsetFromContainer(*container, LayoutPoint(), &offsetDependsOnPoint);
2287
2288 bool preserve3D = container->style().preserves3D() || style().preserves3D();
2289 if (shouldUseTransformFromContainer(container) && (geometryMap.mapCoordinatesFlags() & UseTransforms)) {
2290 TransformationMatrix t;
2291 getTransformFromContainer(container, containerOffset, t);
2292 t.translateRight(adjustmentForSkippedAncestor.width(), adjustmentForSkippedAncestor.height());
2293
2294 geometryMap.push(this, t, preserve3D, offsetDependsOnPoint, isFixedPos, hasTransform());
2295 } else {
2296 containerOffset += adjustmentForSkippedAncestor;
2297 geometryMap.push(this, containerOffset, preserve3D, offsetDependsOnPoint, isFixedPos, hasTransform());
2298 }
2299
2300 return ancestorSkipped ? ancestorToStopAt : container;
2301}
2302
2303void RenderBox::mapAbsoluteToLocalPoint(MapCoordinatesFlags mode, TransformState& transformState) const
2304{
2305 bool isFixedPos = isFixedPositioned();
2306 if (hasTransform() && !isFixedPos) {
2307 // If this box has a transform, it acts as a fixed position container for fixed descendants,
2308 // and may itself also be fixed position. So propagate 'fixed' up only if this box is fixed position.
2309 mode &= ~IsFixed;
2310 } else if (isFixedPos)
2311 mode |= IsFixed;
2312
2313 RenderBoxModelObject::mapAbsoluteToLocalPoint(mode, transformState);
2314}

2316LayoutSize RenderBox::offsetFromContainer(RenderElement& container, const LayoutPoint&, bool* offsetDependsOnPoint) const
2317{
2318 // A fragment "has" boxes inside it without being their container.
2319 ASSERT(&container == this->container() || is<RenderFragmentContainer>(container));
2320
2321 LayoutSize offset;
2322 if (isInFlowPositioned())
2323 offset += offsetForInFlowPosition();
2324
2325 if (!isInline() || isReplaced())
2326 offset += topLeftLocationOffset();
2327
2328 if (is<RenderBox>(container))
2329 offset -= toLayoutSize(downcast<RenderBox>(container).scrollPosition());
2330
2331 if (isAbsolutelyPositioned() && container.isInFlowPositioned() && is<RenderInline>(container))
2332 offset += downcast<RenderInline>(container).offsetForInFlowPositionedInline(this);
2333
2334 if (offsetDependsOnPoint)
2335 *offsetDependsOnPoint |= is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(container);
2336
2337 return offset;
2338}

2357void RenderBox::positionLineBox(LegacyInlineElementBox& box)
2358{
2359 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
2360 // Cache the x position only if we were an DisplayType::Inline type originally.
2361 bool wasInline = style().isOriginalDisplayInlineType();
2362 if (wasInline) {
2363 // The value is cached in the xPos of the box. We only need this value if
2364 // our object was inline originally, since otherwise it would have ended up underneath
2365 // the inlines.
2366 LegacyRootInlineBox& rootBox = box.root();
2367 rootBox.blockFlow().setStaticInlinePositionForChild(*this, rootBox.lineBoxTop(), LayoutUnit::fromFloatRound(box.logicalLeft()));
2368 if (style().hasStaticInlinePosition(box.isHorizontal()))
2369 setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis); // Just mark the positioned object as needing layout, so it will update its position properly.
2370 } else {
2371 // Our object was a block originally, so we make our normal flow position be
2372 // just below the line box (as though all the inlines that came before us got
2373 // wrapped in an anonymous block, which is what would have happened had we been
2374 // in flow). This value was cached in the y() of the box.
2375 layer()->setStaticBlockPosition(LayoutUnit(box.logicalTop()));
2376 if (style().hasStaticBlockPosition(box.isHorizontal()))
2377 setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis); // Just mark the positioned object as needing layout, so it will update its position properly.
2378 }
2379 return;
2380 }
2381
2382 if (isReplaced()) {
2383 setLocation(LayoutPoint(box.topLeft()));
2384 setInlineBoxWrapper(&box);
2385 }
2386}

2410LayoutRect RenderBox::computeVisibleRectUsingPaintOffset(const LayoutRect& rect) const

2428
2429std::optional<LayoutRect> RenderBox::computeVisibleRectInContainer(const LayoutRect& rect, const RenderLayerModelObject* container, VisibleRectContext context) const
2430{
2431 // The rect we compute at each step is shifted by our x/y offset in the parent container's coordinate space.
2432 // Only when we cross a writing mode boundary will we have to possibly flipForWritingMode (to convert into a more appropriate
2433 // offset corner for the enclosing container). This allows for a fully RL or BT document to repaint
2434 // properly even during layout, since the rect remains flipped all the way until the end.
2435 //
2436 // RenderView::computeVisibleRectInContainer then converts the rect to physical coordinates. We also convert to
2437 // physical when we hit a repaint container boundary. Therefore the final rect returned is always in the
2438 // physical coordinate space of the container.
2439 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
2440 // Paint offset cache is only valid for root-relative, non-fixed position repainting
2441 if (view().frameView().layoutContext().isPaintOffsetCacheEnabled() && !container && styleToUse.position() != PositionType::Fixed && !context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::UseEdgeInclusiveIntersection))
2442 return computeVisibleRectUsingPaintOffset(rect);
2443
2444 LayoutRect adjustedRect = rect;
2445 if (hasReflection())
2446 adjustedRect.unite(reflectedRect(adjustedRect));
2447
2448 if (container == this) {
2449 if (container->style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
2450 flipForWritingMode(adjustedRect);
2451 if (context.descendantNeedsEnclosingIntRect)
2452 adjustedRect = enclosingIntRect(adjustedRect);
2453 return adjustedRect;
2454 }
2455
2456 bool containerIsSkipped;
2457 auto* localContainer = this->container(container, containerIsSkipped);
2458 if (!localContainer)
2459 return adjustedRect;
2460
2461 if (isWritingModeRoot()) {
2462 if (!isOutOfFlowPositioned() || !context.dirtyRectIsFlipped) {
2463 flipForWritingMode(adjustedRect);
2464 context.dirtyRectIsFlipped = true;
2465 }
2466 }
2467
2468 LayoutSize locationOffset = this->locationOffset();
2469 // FIXME: This is needed as long as RenderWidget snaps to integral size/position.
2470 if (isRenderReplaced() && isWidget()) {
2471 LayoutSize flooredLocationOffset = toIntSize(flooredIntPoint(locationOffset));
2472 adjustedRect.expand(locationOffset - flooredLocationOffset);
2473 locationOffset = flooredLocationOffset;
2474 context.descendantNeedsEnclosingIntRect = true;
2475 }
2476
2477 if (is<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(this)) {
2478 // We won't normally run this code. Only when the container is null (i.e., we're trying
2479 // to get the rect in view coordinates) will we come in here, since normally container
2480 // will be set and we'll stop at the flow thread. This case is mainly hit by the check for whether
2481 // or not images should animate.
2482 // FIXME: Just as with offsetFromContainer, we aren't really handling objects that span
2483 // multiple columns properly.
2484 LayoutPoint physicalPoint(flipForWritingMode(adjustedRect.location()));
2485 if (auto* fragment = downcast<RenderMultiColumnFlow>(*this).physicalTranslationFromFlowToFragment((physicalPoint))) {
2486 adjustedRect.setLocation(fragment->flipForWritingMode(physicalPoint));
2487 return fragment->computeVisibleRectInContainer(adjustedRect, container, context);
2488 }
2489 }
2490
2491 LayoutPoint topLeft = adjustedRect.location();
2492 topLeft.move(locationOffset);
2493
2494 // We are now in our parent container's coordinate space. Apply our transform to obtain a bounding box
2495 // in the parent's coordinate space that encloses us.
2496 auto position = styleToUse.position();
2497 if (hasLayer() && layer()->transform()) {
2498 context.hasPositionFixedDescendant = position == PositionType::Fixed;
2499 adjustedRect = LayoutRect(encloseRectToDevicePixels(layer()->transform()->mapRect(adjustedRect), document().deviceScaleFactor()));
2500 topLeft = adjustedRect.location();
2501 topLeft.move(locationOffset);
2502 } else if (position == PositionType::Fixed)
2503 context.hasPositionFixedDescendant = true;
2504
2505 if (position == PositionType::Absolute && localContainer->isInFlowPositioned() && is<RenderInline>(*localContainer))
2506 topLeft += downcast<RenderInline>(*localContainer).offsetForInFlowPositionedInline(this);
2507 else if (styleToUse.hasInFlowPosition() && layer()) {
2508 // Apply the relative position offset when invalidating a rectangle. The layer
2509 // is translated, but the render box isn't, so we need to do this to get the
2510 // right dirty rect. Since this is called from RenderObject::setStyle, the relative position
2511 // flag on the RenderObject has been cleared, so use the one on the style().
2512 topLeft += layer()->offsetForInFlowPosition();
2513 }
2514
2515 // FIXME: We ignore the lightweight clipping rect that controls use, since if |o| is in mid-layout,
2516 // its controlClipRect will be wrong. For overflow clip we use the values cached by the layer.
2517 adjustedRect.setLocation(topLeft);
2518 if (localContainer->hasOverflowClip()) {
2519 RenderBox& containerBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*localContainer);
2520 bool isEmpty = !containerBox.applyCachedClipAndScrollPosition(adjustedRect, container, context);
2521 if (isEmpty) {
2522 if (context.options.contains(VisibleRectContextOption::UseEdgeInclusiveIntersection))
2523 return std::nullopt;
2524 return adjustedRect;
2525 }
2526 }
2527
2528 if (containerIsSkipped) {
2529 // If the container is below localContainer, then we need to map the rect into container's coordinates.
2530 LayoutSize containerOffset = container->offsetFromAncestorContainer(*localContainer);
2531 adjustedRect.move(-containerOffset);
2532 return adjustedRect;
2533 }
2534 return localContainer->computeVisibleRectInContainer(adjustedRect, container, context);
2535}

2537void RenderBox::repaintDuringLayoutIfMoved(const LayoutRect& oldRect)
2538{
2539 if (oldRect.location() != m_frameRect.location()) {
2540 LayoutRect newRect = m_frameRect;
2541 // The child moved. Invalidate the object's old and new positions. We have to do this
2542 // since the object may not have gotten a layout.
2543 m_frameRect = oldRect;
2544 repaint();
2545 repaintOverhangingFloats(true);
2546 m_frameRect = newRect;
2547 repaint();
2548 repaintOverhangingFloats(true);
2549 }
2550}
