2574
2575void RenderBox::computeLogicalWidthInFragment(LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
2576{
2577 computedValues.m_extent = logicalWidth();
2578 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeft();
2579 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = marginStart();
2580 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = marginEnd();
2581
2582 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
2583 // FIXME: This calculation is not patched for block-flow yet.
2584 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46500
2585 computePositionedLogicalWidth(computedValues, fragment);
2586 return;
2587 }
2588
2589 // If layout is limited to a subtree, the subtree root's logical width does not change.
2590 if (element() && !view().frameView().layoutContext().isLayoutPending() && view().frameView().layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot() == this)
2591 return;
2592
2593 // The parent box is flexing us, so it has increased or decreased our
2594 // width. Use the width from the style context.
2595 // FIXME: Account for block-flow in flexible boxes.
2596 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46418
2597 if (hasOverridingLogicalWidth() && (isRubyRun() || style().borderFit() == BorderFit::Lines || (parent()->isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated()))) {
2598 computedValues.m_extent = overridingLogicalWidth();
2599 return;
2600 }
2601
2602 // FIXME: Account for block-flow in flexible boxes.
2603 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46418
2604 bool inVerticalBox = parent()->isDeprecatedFlexibleBox() && (parent()->style().boxOrient() == BoxOrient::Vertical);
2605 bool stretching = (parent()->style().boxAlign() == BoxAlignment::Stretch);
2606 // FIXME: Stretching is the only reason why we don't want the box to be treated as a replaced element, so we could perhaps
2607 // refactor all this logic, not only for flex and grid since alignment is intended to be applied to any block.
2608 bool treatAsReplaced = shouldComputeSizeAsReplaced() && (!inVerticalBox || !stretching);
2609 treatAsReplaced = treatAsReplaced && (!isGridItem() || !hasStretchedLogicalWidth());
2610
2611 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
2612 Length logicalWidthLength = treatAsReplaced ? Length(computeReplacedLogicalWidth(), LengthType::Fixed) : styleToUse.logicalWidth();
2613
2614 RenderBlock& cb = *containingBlock();
2615 LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, containingBlockLogicalWidthForContentInFragment(fragment));
2616 bool hasPerpendicularContainingBlock = cb.isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode();
2617
2618 if (isInline() && !isInlineBlockOrInlineTable()) {
2619 // just calculate margins
2620 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = minimumValueForLength(styleToUse.marginStart(), containerLogicalWidth);
2621 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = minimumValueForLength(styleToUse.marginEnd(), containerLogicalWidth);
2622 if (treatAsReplaced)
2623 computedValues.m_extent = std::max(LayoutUnit(floatValueForLength(logicalWidthLength, 0) + borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth()), minPreferredLogicalWidth());
2624 return;
2625 }
2626
2627 LayoutUnit containerWidthInInlineDirection = containerLogicalWidth;
2628 if (hasPerpendicularContainingBlock)
2629 containerWidthInInlineDirection = perpendicularContainingBlockLogicalHeight();
2630
2631 // Width calculations
2632 if (treatAsReplaced) {
2633 computedValues.m_extent = logicalWidthLength.value() + borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
2634 } else if (shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio() && style().logicalWidth().isAuto()) {
2635 computedValues.m_extent = computeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio(fragment);
2636 } else {
2637 LayoutUnit preferredWidth = computeLogicalWidthInFragmentUsing(MainOrPreferredSize, styleToUse.logicalWidth(), containerWidthInInlineDirection, cb, fragment);
2638 computedValues.m_extent = constrainLogicalWidthInFragmentByMinMax(preferredWidth, containerWidthInInlineDirection, cb, fragment);
2639 }
2640
2641 // Margin calculations.
2642 if (hasPerpendicularContainingBlock || isFloating() || isInline()) {
2643 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = minimumValueForLength(styleToUse.marginStart(), containerLogicalWidth);
2644 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = minimumValueForLength(styleToUse.marginEnd(), containerLogicalWidth);
2645 } else {
2646 LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidthForAutoMargins = containerLogicalWidth;
2647 if (avoidsFloats() && cb.containsFloats())
2648 containerLogicalWidthForAutoMargins = containingBlockAvailableLineWidthInFragment(fragment);
2649 bool hasInvertedDirection = cb.style().isLeftToRightDirection() != style().isLeftToRightDirection();
2650 computeInlineDirectionMargins(cb, containerLogicalWidthForAutoMargins, computedValues.m_extent,
2651 hasInvertedDirection ? computedValues.m_margins.m_end : computedValues.m_margins.m_start,
2652 hasInvertedDirection ? computedValues.m_margins.m_start : computedValues.m_margins.m_end);
2653 }
2654
2655 if (!hasPerpendicularContainingBlock && containerLogicalWidth && containerLogicalWidth != (computedValues.m_extent + computedValues.m_margins.m_start + computedValues.m_margins.m_end)
2656 && !isFloating() && !isInline() && !cb.isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated()
2657#if ENABLE(MATHML)
2658 // RenderMathMLBlocks take the size of their content so we must not adjust the margin to fill the container size.
2659 && !cb.isRenderMathMLBlock()
2660#endif
2661 && !cb.isRenderGrid()
2662 ) {
2663 LayoutUnit newMarginTotal = containerLogicalWidth - computedValues.m_extent;
2664 bool hasInvertedDirection = cb.style().isLeftToRightDirection() != style().isLeftToRightDirection();
2665 if (hasInvertedDirection)
2666 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = newMarginTotal - computedValues.m_margins.m_end;
2667 else
2668 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = newMarginTotal - computedValues.m_margins.m_start;
2669 }
2670}

2674 LayoutUnit marginStart;
2675 LayoutUnit marginEnd;
2676 return fillAvailableMeasure(availableLogicalWidth, marginStart, marginEnd);
2677}

2679LayoutUnit RenderBox::fillAvailableMeasure(LayoutUnit availableLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& marginStart, LayoutUnit& marginEnd) const
2680{
2681 marginStart = minimumValueForLength(style().marginStart(), availableLogicalWidth);
2682 marginEnd = minimumValueForLength(style().marginEnd(), availableLogicalWidth);
2683 return availableLogicalWidth - marginStart - marginEnd;

2685
2686LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeIntrinsicLogicalWidthUsing(Length logicalWidthLength, LayoutUnit availableLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit borderAndPadding) const
2687{
2688 if (logicalWidthLength.isFillAvailable())
2689 return std::max(borderAndPadding, fillAvailableMeasure(availableLogicalWidth));
2690
2691 LayoutUnit minLogicalWidth;
2692 LayoutUnit maxLogicalWidth;
2693 if (!logicalWidthLength.isMinIntrinsic() && shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio())
2694 minLogicalWidth = maxLogicalWidth = computeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
2695 else
2696 computeIntrinsicKeywordLogicalWidths(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
2697
2698 if (logicalWidthLength.isMinContent() || logicalWidthLength.isMinIntrinsic())
2699 return minLogicalWidth + borderAndPadding;
2700
2701 if (logicalWidthLength.isMaxContent())
2702 return maxLogicalWidth + borderAndPadding;
2703
2704 if (logicalWidthLength.isFitContent()) {
2705 minLogicalWidth += borderAndPadding;
2706 maxLogicalWidth += borderAndPadding;
2707 return std::max(minLogicalWidth, std::min(maxLogicalWidth, fillAvailableMeasure(availableLogicalWidth)));
2708 }
2709
2710 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2711 return 0;
2712}
2713
2714LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeLogicalWidthInFragmentUsing(SizeType widthType, Length logicalWidth, LayoutUnit availableLogicalWidth,
2715 const RenderBlock& cb, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
2716{
2717 ASSERT(widthType == MinSize || widthType == MainOrPreferredSize || !logicalWidth.isAuto());
2718 if (widthType == MinSize && logicalWidth.isAuto())
2719 return adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(0, logicalWidth.type());
2720
2721 if (!logicalWidth.isIntrinsicOrAuto()) {
2722 // FIXME: If the containing block flow is perpendicular to our direction we need to use the available logical height instead.
2723 return adjustBorderBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth), logicalWidth.type());
2724 }
2725
2726 if (logicalWidth.isIntrinsic() || logicalWidth.isMinIntrinsic())
2727 return computeIntrinsicLogicalWidthUsing(logicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth());
2728
2729 LayoutUnit marginStart;
2730 LayoutUnit marginEnd;
2731 LayoutUnit logicalWidthResult = fillAvailableMeasure(availableLogicalWidth, marginStart, marginEnd);
2732
2733 if (shrinkToAvoidFloats() && cb.containsFloats())
2734 logicalWidthResult = std::min(logicalWidthResult, shrinkLogicalWidthToAvoidFloats(marginStart, marginEnd, cb, fragment));
2735
2736 if (widthType == MainOrPreferredSize && sizesLogicalWidthToFitContent(widthType))
2737 return std::max(minPreferredLogicalWidth(), std::min(maxPreferredLogicalWidth(), logicalWidthResult));
2738 return logicalWidthResult;
2739}
2740
2741bool RenderBox::columnFlexItemHasStretchAlignment() const
2742{
2743 // auto margins mean we don't stretch. Note that this function will only be
2744 // used for widths, so we don't have to check marginBefore/marginAfter.
2745 const auto& parentStyle = parent()->style();
2746 ASSERT(parentStyle.isColumnFlexDirection());
2747 if (style().marginStart().isAuto() || style().marginEnd().isAuto())
2748 return false;
2749 return style().resolvedAlignSelf(&parentStyle, containingBlock()->selfAlignmentNormalBehavior()).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch;
2750}
2751
2752bool RenderBox::isStretchingColumnFlexItem() const
2753{
2754 if (parent()->isDeprecatedFlexibleBox() && parent()->style().boxOrient() == BoxOrient::Vertical && parent()->style().boxAlign() == BoxAlignment::Stretch)
2755 return true;
2756
2757 // We don't stretch multiline flexboxes because they need to apply line spacing (align-content) first.
2758 if (parent()->isFlexibleBox() && parent()->style().flexWrap() == FlexWrap::NoWrap && parent()->style().isColumnFlexDirection() && columnFlexItemHasStretchAlignment())
2759 return true;
2760 return false;
2761}
2762
2763// FIXME: Can/Should we move this inside specific layout classes (flex. grid)? Can we refactor columnFlexItemHasStretchAlignment logic?
2764bool RenderBox::hasStretchedLogicalWidth() const
2765{
2766 auto& style = this->style();
2767 if (!style.logicalWidth().isAuto() || style.marginStart().isAuto() || style.marginEnd().isAuto())
2768 return false;
2769 RenderBlock* containingBlock = this->containingBlock();
2770 if (!containingBlock) {
2771 // We are evaluating align-self/justify-self, which default to 'normal' for the root element.
2772 // The 'normal' value behaves like 'start' except for Flexbox Items, which obviously should have a container.
2773 return false;
2774 }
2775 if (containingBlock->isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode())
2776 return style.resolvedAlignSelf(&containingBlock->style(), containingBlock->selfAlignmentNormalBehavior(this)).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch;
2777 return style.resolvedJustifySelf(&containingBlock->style(), containingBlock->selfAlignmentNormalBehavior(this)).position() == ItemPosition::Stretch;
2778}
2779
2780bool RenderBox::sizesLogicalWidthToFitContent(SizeType widthType) const
2781{
2782 // Marquees in WinIE are like a mixture of blocks and inline-blocks. They size as though they're blocks,
2783 // but they allow text to sit on the same line as the marquee.
2784 if (isFloating() || (isInlineBlockOrInlineTable() && !isHTMLMarquee()))
2785 return true;
2786
2787 if (isGridItem())
2788 return !hasStretchedLogicalWidth();
2789
2790 // This code may look a bit strange. Basically width:intrinsic should clamp the size when testing both
2791 // min-width and width. max-width is only clamped if it is also intrinsic.
2792 Length logicalWidth = (widthType == MaxSize) ? style().logicalMaxWidth() : style().logicalWidth();
2793 if (logicalWidth.type() == LengthType::Intrinsic)
2794 return true;
2795
2796 // Children of a horizontal marquee do not fill the container by default.
2797 // FIXME: Need to deal with MarqueeDirection::Auto value properly. It could be vertical.
2798 // FIXME: Think about block-flow here. Need to find out how marquee direction relates to
2799 // block-flow (as well as how marquee overflow should relate to block flow).
2800 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46472
2801 if (parent()->isHTMLMarquee()) {
2802 MarqueeDirection dir = parent()->style().marqueeDirection();
2803 if (dir == MarqueeDirection::Auto || dir == MarqueeDirection::Forward || dir == MarqueeDirection::Backward || dir == MarqueeDirection::Left || dir == MarqueeDirection::Right)
2804 return true;
2805 }
2806
2807#if ENABLE(MATHML)
2808 // RenderMathMLBlocks take the size of their content, not of their container.
2809 if (parent()->isRenderMathMLBlock())
2810 return true;
2811#endif
2812
2813 // Flexible box items should shrink wrap, so we lay them out at their intrinsic widths.
2814 // In the case of columns that have a stretch alignment, we layout at the stretched size
2815 // to avoid an extra layout when applying alignment.
2816 if (parent()->isFlexibleBox()) {
2817 // For multiline columns, we need to apply align-content first, so we can't stretch now.
2818 if (!parent()->style().isColumnFlexDirection() || parent()->style().flexWrap() != FlexWrap::NoWrap)
2819 return true;
2820 if (!columnFlexItemHasStretchAlignment())
2821 return true;
2822 }
2823
2824 // Flexible horizontal boxes lay out children at their intrinsic widths. Also vertical boxes
2825 // that don't stretch their kids lay out their children at their intrinsic widths.
2826 // FIXME: Think about block-flow here.
2827 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46473
2828 if (parent()->isDeprecatedFlexibleBox() && (parent()->style().boxOrient() == BoxOrient::Horizontal || parent()->style().boxAlign() != BoxAlignment::Stretch))
2829 return true;
2830
2831 // Button, input, select, textarea, and legend treat width value of 'auto' as 'intrinsic' unless it's in a
2832 // stretching column flexbox.
2833 // FIXME: Think about block-flow here.
2834 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46473
2835 if (logicalWidth.isAuto() && !isStretchingColumnFlexItem() && element() && (is<HTMLInputElement>(*element()) || is<HTMLSelectElement>(*element()) || is<HTMLButtonElement>(*element()) || is<HTMLTextAreaElement>(*element()) || is<HTMLLegendElement>(*element())))
2836 return true;
2837
2838 if (isHorizontalWritingMode() != containingBlock()->isHorizontalWritingMode())
2839 return true;
2840
2841 return false;
2842}
2843
2844void RenderBox::computeInlineDirectionMargins(const RenderBlock& containingBlock, LayoutUnit containerWidth, LayoutUnit childWidth, LayoutUnit& marginStart, LayoutUnit& marginEnd) const
2845{
2846
2847 const RenderStyle& containingBlockStyle = containingBlock.style();
2848 Length marginStartLength = style().marginStartUsing(&containingBlockStyle);
2849 Length marginEndLength = style().marginEndUsing(&containingBlockStyle);
2850
2851 if (isFloating() || isInline()) {
2852 // Inline blocks/tables and floats don't have their margins increased.
2853 marginStart = minimumValueForLength(marginStartLength, containerWidth);
2854 marginEnd = minimumValueForLength(marginEndLength, containerWidth);
2855 return;
2856 }
2857
2858 if (containingBlock.isFlexibleBox()) {
2859 // We need to let flexbox handle the margin adjustment - otherwise, flexbox
2860 // will think we're wider than we actually are and calculate line sizes
2861 // wrong. See also http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-flexbox/#auto-margins
2862 if (marginStartLength.isAuto())
2863 marginStartLength = Length(0, LengthType::Fixed);
2864 if (marginEndLength.isAuto())
2865 marginEndLength = Length(0, LengthType::Fixed);
2866 }
2867
2868 // Case One: The object is being centered in the containing block's available logical width.
2869 if ((marginStartLength.isAuto() && marginEndLength.isAuto() && childWidth < containerWidth)
2870 || (!marginStartLength.isAuto() && !marginEndLength.isAuto() && containingBlock.style().textAlign() == TextAlignMode::WebKitCenter)) {
2871 // Other browsers center the margin box for align=center elements so we match them here.
2872 LayoutUnit marginStartWidth = minimumValueForLength(marginStartLength, containerWidth);
2873 LayoutUnit marginEndWidth = minimumValueForLength(marginEndLength, containerWidth);
2874 LayoutUnit centeredMarginBoxStart = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, (containerWidth - childWidth - marginStartWidth - marginEndWidth) / 2);
2875 marginStart = centeredMarginBoxStart + marginStartWidth;
2876 marginEnd = containerWidth - childWidth - marginStart + marginEndWidth;
2877 return;
2878 }
2879
2880 // Case Two: The object is being pushed to the start of the containing block's available logical width.
2881 if (marginEndLength.isAuto() && childWidth < containerWidth) {
2882 marginStart = valueForLength(marginStartLength, containerWidth);
2883 marginEnd = containerWidth - childWidth - marginStart;
2884 return;
2885 }
2886
2887 // Case Three: The object is being pushed to the end of the containing block's available logical width.
2888 bool pushToEndFromTextAlign = !marginEndLength.isAuto() && ((!containingBlockStyle.isLeftToRightDirection() && containingBlockStyle.textAlign() == TextAlignMode::WebKitLeft)
2889 || (containingBlockStyle.isLeftToRightDirection() && containingBlockStyle.textAlign() == TextAlignMode::WebKitRight));
2890 if ((marginStartLength.isAuto() || pushToEndFromTextAlign) && childWidth < containerWidth) {
2891 marginEnd = valueForLength(marginEndLength, containerWidth);
2892 marginStart = containerWidth - childWidth - marginEnd;
2893 return;
2894 }
2895
2896 // Case Four: Either no auto margins, or our width is >= the container width (css2.1, 10.3.3). In that case
2897 // auto margins will just turn into 0.
2898 marginStart = minimumValueForLength(marginStartLength, containerWidth);
2899 marginEnd = minimumValueForLength(marginEndLength, containerWidth);
2900}
2901
2902RenderBoxFragmentInfo* RenderBox::renderBoxFragmentInfo(RenderFragmentContainer* fragment, RenderBoxFragmentInfoFlags cacheFlag) const
2903{
2904 // Make sure nobody is trying to call this with a null fragment.
2905 if (!fragment)
2906 return nullptr;
2907
2908 // If we have computed our width in this fragment already, it will be cached, and we can
2909 // just return it.
2910 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = fragment->renderBoxFragmentInfo(this);
2911 if (boxInfo && cacheFlag == CacheRenderBoxFragmentInfo)
2912 return boxInfo;
2913
2914 return nullptr;
2915}
2916
2917static bool shouldFlipBeforeAfterMargins(const RenderStyle& containingBlockStyle, const RenderStyle* childStyle)
2918{
2919 ASSERT(containingBlockStyle.isHorizontalWritingMode() != childStyle->isHorizontalWritingMode());
2920 WritingMode childWritingMode = childStyle->writingMode();
2921 bool shouldFlip = false;
2922 switch (containingBlockStyle.writingMode()) {
2923 case WritingMode::TopToBottom:
2924 shouldFlip = (childWritingMode == WritingMode::RightToLeft);
2925 break;
2926 case WritingMode::BottomToTop:
2927 shouldFlip = (childWritingMode == WritingMode::RightToLeft);
2928 break;
2929 case WritingMode::RightToLeft:
2930 shouldFlip = (childWritingMode == WritingMode::BottomToTop);
2931 break;
2932 case WritingMode::LeftToRight:
2933 shouldFlip = (childWritingMode == WritingMode::BottomToTop);
2934 break;
2935 }
2936
2937 if (!containingBlockStyle.isLeftToRightDirection())
2938 shouldFlip = !shouldFlip;
2939
2940 return shouldFlip;
2941}

2945 // FIXME: it should be enough with checking hasOverridingLogicalHeight() as this logic could be shared

2949 return;
2950 downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(parent())->setCachedChildIntrinsicContentLogicalHeight(*this, height);

2952
2953void RenderBox::updateLogicalHeight()
2954{
2955 if (shouldApplySizeContainment(*this) && !isRenderGrid()) {
2956 // We need the exact width of border and padding here, yet we can't use borderAndPadding* interfaces.
2957 // Because these interfaces evetually call borderAfter/Before, and RenderBlock::borderBefore
2958 // adds extra border to fieldset by adding intrinsicBorderForFieldset which is not needed here.
2959 auto borderAndPadding = RenderBox::borderBefore() + RenderBox::paddingBefore() + RenderBox::borderAfter() + RenderBox::paddingAfter();
2960 setLogicalHeight(borderAndPadding + scrollbarLogicalHeight());
2961 }
2962
2963 cacheIntrinsicContentLogicalHeightForFlexItem(contentLogicalHeight());
2964 auto computedValues = computeLogicalHeight(logicalHeight(), logicalTop());
2965 setLogicalHeight(computedValues.m_extent);
2966 setLogicalTop(computedValues.m_position);
2967 setMarginBefore(computedValues.m_margins.m_before);
2968 setMarginAfter(computedValues.m_margins.m_after);
2969}
2970
2971RenderBox::LogicalExtentComputedValues RenderBox::computeLogicalHeight(LayoutUnit logicalHeight, LayoutUnit logicalTop) const
2972{
2973 LogicalExtentComputedValues computedValues;
2974 computedValues.m_extent = logicalHeight;
2975 computedValues.m_position = logicalTop;
2976
2977 // Cell height is managed by the table and inline non-replaced elements do not support a height property.
2978 if (isTableCell() || (isInline() && !isReplaced()))
2979 return computedValues;
2980
2981 Length h;
2982 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned())
2983 computePositionedLogicalHeight(computedValues);
2984 else {
2985 RenderBlock& cb = *containingBlock();
2986 bool hasPerpendicularContainingBlock = cb.isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode();
2987
2988 if (!hasPerpendicularContainingBlock) {
2989 bool shouldFlipBeforeAfter = cb.style().writingMode() != style().writingMode();
2990 computeBlockDirectionMargins(cb,
2991 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_after : computedValues.m_margins.m_before,
2992 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_before : computedValues.m_margins.m_after);
2993 }
2994
2995 // For tables, calculate margins only.
2996 if (isTable()) {
2997 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio())
2998 computedValues.m_extent = blockSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth());
2999 if (hasPerpendicularContainingBlock) {
3000 bool shouldFlipBeforeAfter = shouldFlipBeforeAfterMargins(cb.style(), &style());
3001 computeInlineDirectionMargins(cb, containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent(), computedValues.m_extent,
3002 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_after : computedValues.m_margins.m_before,
3003 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_before : computedValues.m_margins.m_after);
3004 }
3005 return computedValues;
3006 }
3007
3008 // FIXME: Account for block-flow in flexible boxes.
3009 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46418
3010 bool inHorizontalBox = parent()->isDeprecatedFlexibleBox() && parent()->style().boxOrient() == BoxOrient::Horizontal;
3011 bool stretching = parent()->style().boxAlign() == BoxAlignment::Stretch;
3012 bool treatAsReplaced = shouldComputeSizeAsReplaced() && (!inHorizontalBox || !stretching);
3013 bool checkMinMaxHeight = false;
3014
3015 // The parent box is flexing us, so it has increased or decreased our height. We have to
3016 // grab our cached flexible height.
3017 // FIXME: Account for block-flow in flexible boxes.
3018 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46418
3019 if (hasOverridingLogicalHeight() && (parent()->isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated() || parent()->isRenderGrid())) {
3020 h = Length(overridingLogicalHeight(), LengthType::Fixed);
3021 } else if (treatAsReplaced)
3022 h = Length(computeReplacedLogicalHeight() + borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight(), LengthType::Fixed);
3023 else {
3024 h = style().logicalHeight();
3025 checkMinMaxHeight = true;
3026 }
3027
3028 // Block children of horizontal flexible boxes fill the height of the box.
3029 // FIXME: Account for block-flow in flexible boxes.
3030 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46418
3031 if (h.isAuto() && is<RenderDeprecatedFlexibleBox>(*parent()) && parent()->style().boxOrient() == BoxOrient::Horizontal
3032 && downcast<RenderDeprecatedFlexibleBox>(*parent()).isStretchingChildren()) {
3033 h = Length(parentBox()->contentLogicalHeight() - marginBefore() - marginAfter(), LengthType::Fixed);
3034 checkMinMaxHeight = false;
3035 }
3036
3037 LayoutUnit heightResult;
3038 if (checkMinMaxHeight) {
3039 // Callers passing LayoutUnit::max() for logicalHeight means an indefinite height, so
3040 // translate this to a nullopt intrinsic height for further logical height computations.
3041 std::optional<LayoutUnit> intrinsicHeight;
3042 if (computedValues.m_extent != LayoutUnit::max())
3043 intrinsicHeight = computedValues.m_extent;
3044 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio()) {
3045 if (intrinsicHeight && style().boxSizingForAspectRatio() == BoxSizing::ContentBox)
3046 *intrinsicHeight -= borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3047 heightResult = blockSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth());
3048 } else {
3049 if (intrinsicHeight)
3050 *intrinsicHeight -= borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3051 heightResult = computeLogicalHeightUsing(MainOrPreferredSize, style().logicalHeight(), intrinsicHeight).value_or(computedValues.m_extent);
3052 }
3053 heightResult = constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(heightResult, intrinsicHeight);
3054 } else {
3055 ASSERT(h.isFixed());
3056 heightResult = h.value();
3057 }
3058
3059 computedValues.m_extent = heightResult;
3060
3061 if (hasPerpendicularContainingBlock) {
3062 bool shouldFlipBeforeAfter = shouldFlipBeforeAfterMargins(cb.style(), &style());
3063 computeInlineDirectionMargins(cb, containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent(), heightResult,
3064 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_after : computedValues.m_margins.m_before,
3065 shouldFlipBeforeAfter ? computedValues.m_margins.m_before : computedValues.m_margins.m_after);
3066 }
3067 }
3068
3069 // WinIE quirk: The <html> block always fills the entire canvas in quirks mode. The <body> always fills the
3070 // <html> block in quirks mode. Only apply this quirk if the block is normal flow and no height
3071 // is specified. When we're printing, we also need this quirk if the body or root has a percentage
3072 // height since we don't set a height in RenderView when we're printing. So without this quirk, the
3073 // height has nothing to be a percentage of, and it ends up being 0. That is bad.
3074 bool paginatedContentNeedsBaseHeight = document().printing() && h.isPercentOrCalculated()
3075 && (isDocumentElementRenderer() || (isBody() && document().documentElement()->renderer()->style().logicalHeight().isPercentOrCalculated())) && !isInline();
3076 if (stretchesToViewport() || paginatedContentNeedsBaseHeight) {
3077 LayoutUnit margins = collapsedMarginBefore() + collapsedMarginAfter();
3078 LayoutUnit visibleHeight = view().pageOrViewLogicalHeight();
3079 if (isDocumentElementRenderer())
3080 computedValues.m_extent = std::max(computedValues.m_extent, visibleHeight - margins);
3081 else {
3082 LayoutUnit marginsBordersPadding = margins + parentBox()->marginBefore() + parentBox()->marginAfter() + parentBox()->borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3083 computedValues.m_extent = std::max(computedValues.m_extent, visibleHeight - marginsBordersPadding);
3084 }
3085 }
3086 return computedValues;
3087}

3141
3142bool RenderBox::skipContainingBlockForPercentHeightCalculation(const RenderBox& containingBlock, bool isPerpendicularWritingMode) const
3143{
3144 // Flow threads for multicol or paged overflow should be skipped. They are invisible to the DOM,
3145 // and percent heights of children should be resolved against the multicol or paged container.
3146 if (containingBlock.isRenderFragmentedFlow() && !isPerpendicularWritingMode)
3147 return true;
3148
3149 // Render view is not considered auto height.
3150 if (is<RenderView>(containingBlock))
3151 return false;
3152
3153 // If the writing mode of the containing block is orthogonal to ours, it means
3154 // that we shouldn't skip anything, since we're going to resolve the
3155 // percentage height against a containing block *width*.
3156 if (isPerpendicularWritingMode)
3157 return false;
3158
3159 // Anonymous blocks should not impede percentage resolution on a child.
3160 // Examples of such anonymous blocks are blocks wrapped around inlines that
3161 // have block siblings (from the CSS spec) and multicol flow threads (an
3162 // implementation detail). Another implementation detail, ruby runs, create
3163 // anonymous inline-blocks, so skip those too. All other types of anonymous
3164 // objects, such as table-cells and flexboxes, will be treated as if they were
3165 // non-anonymous.
3166 if (containingBlock.isAnonymous())
3167 return containingBlock.style().display() == DisplayType::Block || containingBlock.style().display() == DisplayType::InlineBlock;
3168
3169 // For quirks mode, we skip most auto-height containing blocks when computing
3170 // percentages.
3171 return document().inQuirksMode() && !containingBlock.isTableCell() && !containingBlock.isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !containingBlock.isRenderGrid() && !containingBlock.isFlexibleBoxIncludingDeprecated() && containingBlock.style().logicalHeight().isAuto();
3172}
3173
3174bool RenderBox::shouldTreatChildAsReplacedInTableCells() const
3175{
3176 if (isReplaced())
3177 return true;
3178 return element() && (element()->isFormControlElement() || is<HTMLImageElement>(element()));
3179}
3180
3181static bool tableCellShouldHaveZeroInitialSize(const RenderBlock& block, const RenderBox& child, bool scrollsOverflowY)
3182{
3183 // Normally we would let the cell size intrinsically, but scrolling overflow has to be
3184 // treated differently, since WinIE lets scrolled overflow fragments shrink as needed.
3185 // While we can't get all cases right, we can at least detect when the cell has a specified
3186 // height or when the table has a specified height. In these cases we want to initially have
3187 // no size and allow the flexing of the table or the cell to its specified height to cause us
3188 // to grow to fill the space. This could end up being wrong in some cases, but it is
3189 // preferable to the alternative (sizing intrinsically and making the row end up too big).
3190 const RenderTableCell& cell = downcast<RenderTableCell>(block);
3191 return scrollsOverflowY && !child.shouldTreatChildAsReplacedInTableCells() && (!cell.style().logicalHeight().isAuto() || !cell.table()->style().logicalHeight().isAuto());
3192}
3193
3194std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBox::computePercentageLogicalHeight(const Length& height, UpdatePercentageHeightDescendants updateDescendants) const
3195{
3196 std::optional<LayoutUnit> availableHeight;
3197
3198 bool skippedAutoHeightContainingBlock = false;
3199 RenderBlock* cb = containingBlock();
3200 const RenderBox* containingBlockChild = this;
3201 LayoutUnit rootMarginBorderPaddingHeight;
3202 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
3203 while (cb && !is<RenderView>(*cb) && skipContainingBlockForPercentHeightCalculation(*cb, isHorizontal != cb->isHorizontalWritingMode())) {
3204 if (cb->isBody() || cb->isDocumentElementRenderer())
3205 rootMarginBorderPaddingHeight += cb->marginBefore() + cb->marginAfter() + cb->borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3206 skippedAutoHeightContainingBlock = true;
3207 containingBlockChild = cb;
3208 cb = cb->containingBlock();
3209 }
3210 if (updateDescendants == UpdatePercentageHeightDescendants::Yes)
3211 cb->addPercentHeightDescendant(const_cast<RenderBox&>(*this));
3212
3213 bool isOrthogonal = isHorizontal != cb->isHorizontalWritingMode();
3214 if (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth() && isOrthogonal)
3215 availableHeight = overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth();
3216 else if (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() && !isOrthogonal)
3217 availableHeight = overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight();
3218 else if (isOrthogonal)
3219 availableHeight = containingBlockChild->containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent();
3220 else if (is<RenderTableCell>(*cb)) {
3221 if (!skippedAutoHeightContainingBlock) {
3222 // Table cells violate what the CSS spec says to do with heights. Basically we
3223 // don't care if the cell specified a height or not. We just always make ourselves
3224 // be a percentage of the cell's current content height.
3225 if (!cb->hasOverridingLogicalHeight())
3226 return tableCellShouldHaveZeroInitialSize(*cb, *this, scrollsOverflowY()) ? std::optional<LayoutUnit>(0) : std::nullopt;
3227
3228 availableHeight = cb->overridingLogicalHeight() - cb->computedCSSPaddingBefore() - cb->computedCSSPaddingAfter() - cb->borderBefore() - cb->borderAfter();
3229 }
3230 } else
3231 availableHeight = cb->availableLogicalHeightForPercentageComputation();
3232
3233 if (!availableHeight)
3234 return availableHeight;
3235
3236 LayoutUnit result = valueForLength(height, availableHeight.value() - rootMarginBorderPaddingHeight + (isTable() && isOutOfFlowPositioned() ? cb->paddingBefore() + cb->paddingAfter() : 0_lu));
3237
3238 // |overridingLogicalHeight| is the maximum height made available by the
3239 // cell to its percent height children when we decide they can determine the
3240 // height of the cell. If the percent height child is box-sizing:content-box
3241 // then we must subtract the border and padding from the cell's
3242 // |availableHeight| (given by |overridingLogicalHeight|) to arrive
3243 // at the child's computed height.
3244 bool subtractBorderAndPadding = isTable() || (is<RenderTableCell>(*cb) && !skippedAutoHeightContainingBlock && cb->hasOverridingLogicalHeight());
3245 if (subtractBorderAndPadding) {
3246 result -= borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3247 return std::max(0_lu, result);
3248 }
3249 return result;
3250}

3257LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeReplacedLogicalWidthRespectingMinMaxWidth(LayoutUnit logicalWidth, ShouldComputePreferred shouldComputePreferred) const
3258{
3259 auto& logicalMinWidth = style().logicalMinWidth();
3260 auto& logicalMaxWidth = style().logicalMaxWidth();
3261 bool useLogicalWidthForMinWidth = (shouldComputePreferred == ComputePreferred && logicalMinWidth.isPercentOrCalculated()) || logicalMinWidth.isUndefined();
3262 bool useLogicalWidthForMaxWidth = (shouldComputePreferred == ComputePreferred && logicalMaxWidth.isPercentOrCalculated()) || logicalMaxWidth.isUndefined();
3263 auto minLogicalWidth = useLogicalWidthForMinWidth ? logicalWidth : computeReplacedLogicalWidthUsing(MinSize, logicalMinWidth);
3264 auto maxLogicalWidth = useLogicalWidthForMaxWidth ? logicalWidth : computeReplacedLogicalWidthUsing(MaxSize, logicalMaxWidth);
3265 return std::max(minLogicalWidth, std::min(logicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth));

3268LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeReplacedLogicalWidthUsing(SizeType widthType, Length logicalWidth) const
3269{
3270 ASSERT(widthType == MinSize || widthType == MainOrPreferredSize || !logicalWidth.isAuto());
3271 if (widthType == MinSize && logicalWidth.isAuto())
3272 return adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(0, logicalWidth.type());
3273
3274 switch (logicalWidth.type()) {
3275 case LengthType::Fixed:
3276 return adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(logicalWidth);
3277 case LengthType::MinContent:
3278 case LengthType::MaxContent: {
3279 // MinContent/MaxContent don't need the availableLogicalWidth argument.
3280 LayoutUnit availableLogicalWidth;
3281 return computeIntrinsicLogicalWidthUsing(logicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth()) - borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
3282 }
3283 case LengthType::FitContent:
3284 case LengthType::FillAvailable:
3285 case LengthType::Percent:
3286 case LengthType::Calculated: {
3287 // FIXME: containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent() is wrong if the replaced element's block-flow is perpendicular to the
3288 // containing block's block-flow.
3289 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46496
3290 const LayoutUnit cw = isOutOfFlowPositioned() ? containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container())) : containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent();
3291 Length containerLogicalWidth = containingBlock()->style().logicalWidth();
3292 // FIXME: Handle cases when containing block width is calculated or viewport percent.
3293 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=91071
3294 if (logicalWidth.isIntrinsic())
3295 return computeIntrinsicLogicalWidthUsing(logicalWidth, cw, borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth()) - borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
3296 if (cw > 0 || (!cw && (containerLogicalWidth.isFixed() || containerLogicalWidth.isPercentOrCalculated())))
3297 return adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(minimumValueForLength(logicalWidth, cw), logicalWidth.type());
3298 return 0_lu;
3299 }
3300 case LengthType::Intrinsic:
3301 case LengthType::MinIntrinsic:
3302 case LengthType::Auto:
3303 case LengthType::Relative:
3304 case LengthType::Undefined:
3305 return intrinsicLogicalWidth();
3306 }
3307
3308 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3309 return 0;
3310}

3334void RenderBox::computePreferredLogicalWidths(const Length& minWidth, const Length& maxWidth, LayoutUnit borderAndPadding)
3335{
3336 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio()) {
3337 auto [logicalMinWidth, logicalMaxWidth] = computeMinMaxLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
3338 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = std::clamp(m_minPreferredLogicalWidth, logicalMinWidth, logicalMaxWidth);
3339 m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = std::clamp(m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth, logicalMinWidth, logicalMaxWidth);
3340 }
3341
3342 if (maxWidth.isFixed()) {
3343 auto adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(maxWidth);
3344 m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = std::min(m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth, adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth);
3345 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = std::min(m_minPreferredLogicalWidth, adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth);
3346 }
3347
3348 if (minWidth.isFixed() && minWidth.value() > 0) {
3349 auto adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(minWidth);
3350 m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth = std::max(m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth, adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth);
3351 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth = std::max(m_minPreferredLogicalWidth, adjustContentBoxLogicalWidth);
3352 }
3353
3354 m_minPreferredLogicalWidth += borderAndPadding;
3355 m_maxPreferredLogicalWidth += borderAndPadding;
3356}

3358bool RenderBox::replacedMinMaxLogicalHeightComputesAsNone(SizeType sizeType) const
3359{
3360 ASSERT(sizeType == MinSize || sizeType == MaxSize);
3361
3362 auto logicalHeight = sizeType == MinSize ? style().logicalMinHeight() : style().logicalMaxHeight();
3363 auto initialLogicalHeight = sizeType == MinSize ? RenderStyle::initialMinSize() : RenderStyle::initialMaxSize();
3364
3365 if (logicalHeight == initialLogicalHeight)
3366 return true;
3367
3368 if (logicalHeight.isPercentOrCalculated() && hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight())
3369 return overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight() == std::nullopt;
3370
3371 // Make sure % min-height and % max-height resolve to none if the containing block has auto height.
3372 // Note that the "height" case for replaced elements was handled by hasReplacedLogicalHeight, which is why
3373 // min and max-height are the only ones handled here.
3374 // FIXME: For now we put in a quirk for iBooks until we can move them to viewport units.
3375 if (auto* cb = containingBlockForAutoHeightDetection(logicalHeight))
3376 return allowMinMaxPercentagesInAutoHeightBlocksQuirk() ? false : cb->hasAutoHeightOrContainingBlockWithAutoHeight();
3377
3378 return false;
3379}

3381LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeReplacedLogicalHeightRespectingMinMaxHeight(LayoutUnit logicalHeight) const
3382{
3383 LayoutUnit minLogicalHeight;
3384 if (!replacedMinMaxLogicalHeightComputesAsNone(MinSize))
3385 minLogicalHeight = computeReplacedLogicalHeightUsing(MinSize, style().logicalMinHeight());
3386 LayoutUnit maxLogicalHeight = logicalHeight;
3387 if (!replacedMinMaxLogicalHeightComputesAsNone(MaxSize))
3388 maxLogicalHeight = computeReplacedLogicalHeightUsing(MaxSize, style().logicalMaxHeight());
3389 return std::max(minLogicalHeight, std::min(logicalHeight, maxLogicalHeight));

3391
3392LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeReplacedLogicalHeightUsing(SizeType heightType, Length logicalHeight) const
3393{
3394 ASSERT(heightType == MinSize || heightType == MainOrPreferredSize || !logicalHeight.isAuto());
3395 if (heightType == MinSize && logicalHeight.isAuto())
3396 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(std::optional<LayoutUnit>(0));
3397
3398 switch (logicalHeight.type()) {
3399 case LengthType::Fixed:
3400 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(LayoutUnit(logicalHeight.value()));
3401 case LengthType::Percent:
3402 case LengthType::Calculated: {
3403 auto* container = isOutOfFlowPositioned() ? this->container() : containingBlock();
3404 while (container && container->isAnonymous()) {
3405 // Stop at rendering context root.
3406 if (is<RenderView>(*container))
3407 break;
3408 container = container->containingBlock();
3409 }
3410 bool hasPerpendicularContainingBlock = container->isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode();
3411 std::optional<LayoutUnit> stretchedHeight;
3412 if (is<RenderBlock>(container)) {
3413 auto* block = downcast<RenderBlock>(container);
3414 block->addPercentHeightDescendant(*const_cast<RenderBox*>(this));
3415 if (block->isFlexItem() && downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(block->parent())->useChildOverridingLogicalHeightForPercentageResolution(*block))
3416 stretchedHeight = block->overridingContentLogicalHeight();
3417 else if (block->isGridItem() && block->hasOverridingLogicalHeight() && !hasPerpendicularContainingBlock)
3418 stretchedHeight = block->overridingContentLogicalHeight();
3419 }
3420
3421 // FIXME: This calculation is not patched for block-flow yet.
3422 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46500
3423 if (container->isOutOfFlowPositioned()
3424 && container->style().height().isAuto()
3425 && !(container->style().top().isAuto() || container->style().bottom().isAuto())) {
3426 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(container->isRenderBlock());
3427 auto& block = downcast<RenderBlock>(*container);
3428 auto computedValues = block.computeLogicalHeight(block.logicalHeight(), 0);
3429 LayoutUnit newContentHeight = computedValues.m_extent - block.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() - block.scrollbarLogicalHeight();
3430 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalHeight, newContentHeight));
3431 }
3432
3433 // FIXME: availableLogicalHeight() is wrong if the replaced element's block-flow is perpendicular to the
3434 // containing block's block-flow.
3435 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46496
3436 LayoutUnit availableHeight;
3437 if (isOutOfFlowPositioned())
3438 availableHeight = containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container));
3439 else if (stretchedHeight)
3440 availableHeight = stretchedHeight.value();
3441 else {
3442 availableHeight = hasPerpendicularContainingBlock ? containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent() : containingBlockLogicalHeightForContent(IncludeMarginBorderPadding);
3443 // It is necessary to use the border-box to match WinIE's broken
3444 // box model. This is essential for sizing inside
3445 // table cells using percentage heights.
3446 // FIXME: This needs to be made block-flow-aware. If the cell and image are perpendicular block-flows, this isn't right.
3447 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46997
3448 while (container && !is<RenderView>(*container)
3449 && (container->style().logicalHeight().isAuto() || container->style().logicalHeight().isPercentOrCalculated())) {
3450 if (container->isTableCell()) {
3451 // Don't let table cells squeeze percent-height replaced elements
3452 // <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15359>
3453 availableHeight = std::max(availableHeight, intrinsicLogicalHeight());
3454 return valueForLength(logicalHeight, availableHeight - borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight());
3455 }
3456 downcast<RenderBlock>(*container).addPercentHeightDescendant(const_cast<RenderBox&>(*this));
3457 container = container->containingBlock();
3458 }
3459 }
3460 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalHeight, availableHeight));
3461 }
3462 case LengthType::MinContent:
3463 case LengthType::MaxContent:
3464 case LengthType::FitContent:
3465 case LengthType::FillAvailable:
3466 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(computeIntrinsicLogicalContentHeightUsing(logicalHeight, intrinsicLogicalHeight(), borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight()));
3467 default:
3468 return intrinsicLogicalHeight();
3469 }
3470}

3472LayoutUnit RenderBox::availableLogicalHeight(AvailableLogicalHeightType heightType) const
3473{
3474 return constrainContentBoxLogicalHeightByMinMax(availableLogicalHeightUsing(style().logicalHeight(), heightType), std::nullopt);
3475}
3476
3477LayoutUnit RenderBox::availableLogicalHeightUsing(const Length& h, AvailableLogicalHeightType heightType) const
3478{
3479 // We need to stop here, since we don't want to increase the height of the table
3480 // artificially. We're going to rely on this cell getting expanded to some new
3481 // height, and then when we lay out again we'll use the calculation below.
3482 if (isTableCell() && (h.isAuto() || h.isPercentOrCalculated())) {
3483 if (hasOverridingLogicalHeight())
3484 return overridingLogicalHeight() - computedCSSPaddingBefore() - computedCSSPaddingAfter() - borderBefore() - borderAfter();
3485 return logicalHeight() - borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3486 }
3487
3488 if (isFlexItem() && downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(*parent()).useChildOverridingLogicalHeightForPercentageResolution(*this))
3489 return overridingContentLogicalHeight();
3490
3491 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio())
3492 return blockSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth());
3493
3494 if (h.isPercentOrCalculated() && isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !isRenderFragmentedFlow()) {
3495 // FIXME: This is wrong if the containingBlock has a perpendicular writing mode.
3496 LayoutUnit availableHeight = containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(*containingBlock());
3497 return adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(valueForLength(h, availableHeight));
3498 }
3499
3500 if (std::optional<LayoutUnit> heightIncludingScrollbar = computeContentAndScrollbarLogicalHeightUsing(MainOrPreferredSize, h, std::nullopt))
3501 return std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(heightIncludingScrollbar) - scrollbarLogicalHeight());
3502
3503 // FIXME: Check logicalTop/logicalBottom here to correctly handle vertical writing-mode.
3504 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=46500
3505 if (is<RenderBlock>(*this) && isOutOfFlowPositioned() && style().height().isAuto() && !(style().top().isAuto() || style().bottom().isAuto())) {
3506 RenderBlock& block = const_cast<RenderBlock&>(downcast<RenderBlock>(*this));
3507 auto computedValues = block.computeLogicalHeight(block.logicalHeight(), 0);
3508 return computedValues.m_extent - block.borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() - block.scrollbarLogicalHeight();
3509 }
3510
3511 // FIXME: This is wrong if the containingBlock has a perpendicular writing mode.
3512 LayoutUnit availableHeight = containingBlockLogicalHeightForContent(heightType);
3513 if (heightType == ExcludeMarginBorderPadding) {
3514 // FIXME: Margin collapsing hasn't happened yet, so this incorrectly removes collapsed margins.
3515 availableHeight -= marginBefore() + marginAfter() + borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
3516 }
3517 return availableHeight;
3518}
3519
3520void RenderBox::computeBlockDirectionMargins(const RenderBlock& containingBlock, LayoutUnit& marginBefore, LayoutUnit& marginAfter) const
3521{
3522 if (isTableCell()) {
3523 // FIXME: Not right if we allow cells to have different directionality than the table. If we do allow this, though,
3524 // we may just do it with an extra anonymous block inside the cell.
3525 marginBefore = 0;
3526 marginAfter = 0;
3527 return;
3528 }
3529
3530 // Margins are calculated with respect to the logical width of
3531 // the containing block (8.3)
3532 LayoutUnit cw = containingBlockLogicalWidthForContent();
3533 const RenderStyle& containingBlockStyle = containingBlock.style();
3534 marginBefore = minimumValueForLength(style().marginBeforeUsing(&containingBlockStyle), cw);
3535 marginAfter = minimumValueForLength(style().marginAfterUsing(&containingBlockStyle), cw);
3536}

3538void RenderBox::computeAndSetBlockDirectionMargins(const RenderBlock& containingBlock)
3539{
3540 LayoutUnit marginBefore;
3541 LayoutUnit marginAfter;
3542 computeBlockDirectionMargins(containingBlock, marginBefore, marginAfter);
3543 containingBlock.setMarginBeforeForChild(*this, marginBefore);
3544 containingBlock.setMarginAfterForChild(*this, marginAfter);

3546
3547LayoutUnit RenderBox::containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(const RenderBoxModelObject& containingBlock, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment, bool checkForPerpendicularWritingMode) const
3548{
3549 if (checkForPerpendicularWritingMode && containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode())
3550 return containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(containingBlock, false);
3551
3552 if (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth()) {
3553 if (auto width = overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalWidth())
3554 return width.value();
3555 }
3556
3557 if (is<RenderBox>(containingBlock)) {
3558 bool isFixedPosition = isFixedPositioned();
3559
3560 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
3561 if (!fragmentedFlow) {
3562 if (isFixedPosition && is<RenderView>(containingBlock))
3563 return downcast<RenderView>(containingBlock).clientLogicalWidthForFixedPosition();
3564
3565 return downcast<RenderBox>(containingBlock).clientLogicalWidth();
3566 }
3567
3568 if (!is<RenderBlock>(containingBlock))
3569 return downcast<RenderBox>(containingBlock).clientLogicalWidth();
3570
3571 const RenderBlock& cb = downcast<RenderBlock>(containingBlock);
3572 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = nullptr;
3573 if (!fragment) {
3574 if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(containingBlock) && !checkForPerpendicularWritingMode)
3575 return downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(containingBlock).contentLogicalWidthOfFirstFragment();
3576 if (isWritingModeRoot()) {
3577 LayoutUnit cbPageOffset = cb.offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage();
3578 RenderFragmentContainer* cbFragment = cb.fragmentAtBlockOffset(cbPageOffset);
3579 if (cbFragment)
3580 boxInfo = cb.renderBoxFragmentInfo(cbFragment);
3581 }
3582 } else if (fragmentedFlow->isHorizontalWritingMode() == containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
3583 RenderFragmentContainer* containingBlockFragment = cb.clampToStartAndEndFragments(fragment);
3584 boxInfo = cb.renderBoxFragmentInfo(containingBlockFragment);
3585 }
3586 return (boxInfo) ? std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, cb.clientLogicalWidth() - (cb.logicalWidth() - boxInfo->logicalWidth())) : cb.clientLogicalWidth();
3587 }
3588
3589 ASSERT(containingBlock.isInFlowPositioned());
3590
3591 const auto& flow = downcast<RenderInline>(containingBlock);
3592 LegacyInlineFlowBox* first = flow.firstLineBox();
3593 LegacyInlineFlowBox* last = flow.lastLineBox();
3594
3595 // If the containing block is empty, return a width of 0.
3596 if (!first || !last)
3597 return 0;
3598
3599 LayoutUnit fromLeft;
3600 LayoutUnit fromRight;
3601 if (containingBlock.style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
3602 fromLeft = first->logicalLeft() + first->borderLogicalLeft();
3603 fromRight = last->logicalLeft() + last->logicalWidth() - last->borderLogicalRight();
3604 } else {
3605 fromRight = first->logicalLeft() + first->logicalWidth() - first->borderLogicalRight();
3606 fromLeft = last->logicalLeft() + last->borderLogicalLeft();
3607 }
3608
3609 return std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, fromRight - fromLeft);
3610}
3611
3612LayoutUnit RenderBox::containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(const RenderBoxModelObject& containingBlock, bool checkForPerpendicularWritingMode) const
3613{
3614 if (checkForPerpendicularWritingMode && containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() != isHorizontalWritingMode())
3615 return containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containingBlock, nullptr, false);
3616
3617 if (hasOverridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight()) {
3618 if (auto height = overridingContainingBlockContentLogicalHeight())
3619 return height.value();
3620 }
3621
3622 if (containingBlock.isBox()) {
3623 bool isFixedPosition = isFixedPositioned();
3624
3625 if (isFixedPosition && is<RenderView>(containingBlock))
3626 return downcast<RenderView>(containingBlock).clientLogicalHeightForFixedPosition();
3627
3628 const RenderBlock& cb = is<RenderBlock>(containingBlock) ? downcast<RenderBlock>(containingBlock) : *containingBlock.containingBlock();
3629 LayoutUnit result = cb.clientLogicalHeight();
3630 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
3631 if (fragmentedFlow && is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(containingBlock) && fragmentedFlow->isHorizontalWritingMode() == containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode())
3632 return downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(containingBlock).contentLogicalHeightOfFirstFragment();
3633 return result;
3634 }
3635
3636 ASSERT(containingBlock.isInFlowPositioned());
3637
3638 const auto& flow = downcast<RenderInline>(containingBlock);
3639 LegacyInlineFlowBox* first = flow.firstLineBox();
3640 LegacyInlineFlowBox* last = flow.lastLineBox();
3641
3642 // If the containing block is empty, return a height of 0.
3643 if (!first || !last)
3644 return 0;
3645
3646 LayoutUnit heightResult;
3647 LayoutRect boundingBox = flow.linesBoundingBox();
3648 if (containingBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode())
3649 heightResult = boundingBox.height();
3650 else
3651 heightResult = boundingBox.width();
3652 heightResult -= (containingBlock.borderBefore() + containingBlock.borderAfter());
3653 return heightResult;
3654}
