3656static inline bool isVerticalLRChildInHorizontalTBParent(const RenderBox& child, RenderObject& parent)
3657{
3658 return !child.isHorizontalWritingMode() && child.style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode() && parent.isHorizontalWritingMode() && !parent.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode();
3659}
3660
3661static void computeInlineStaticDistance(Length& logicalLeft, Length& logicalRight, const RenderBox* child, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock, LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment)
3662{
3663 if (!logicalLeft.isAuto() || !logicalRight.isAuto())
3664 return;
3665
3666 RenderObject* parent = child->parent();
3667 TextDirection parentDirection = parent->style().direction();
3668
3669 // This method is using enclosingBox() which is wrong for absolutely
3670 // positioned grid items, as they rely on the grid area. So for grid items if
3671 // both "left" and "right" properties are "auto", we can consider that one of
3672 // them (depending on the direction) is simply "0".
3673 if (parent->isRenderGrid() && parent == child->containingBlock()) {
3674 if (parentDirection == TextDirection::LTR)
3675 logicalLeft.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
3676 else
3677 logicalRight.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
3678 return;
3679 }
3680
3681 // FIXME: The static distance computation has not been fully patched for mixed writing modes yet.
3682 if (parentDirection == TextDirection::LTR) {
3683 LayoutUnit staticPosition = isVerticalLRChildInHorizontalTBParent(*child, *parent) ? child->layer()->staticBlockPosition() - containerBlock.borderBefore() : child->layer()->staticInlinePosition() - containerBlock.borderLogicalLeft();
3684 for (auto* current = parent; current && current != &containerBlock; current = current->container()) {
3685 if (!is<RenderBox>(*current))
3686 continue;
3687 const auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*current);
3688 staticPosition += isVerticalLRChildInHorizontalTBParent(*child, *parent) ? renderBox.logicalTop() : renderBox.logicalLeft();
3689 if (renderBox.isInFlowPositioned())
3690 staticPosition += renderBox.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().width() : renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().height();
3691 if (fragment && is<RenderBlock>(*current)) {
3692 const RenderBlock& currentBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(*current);
3693 fragment = currentBlock.clampToStartAndEndFragments(fragment);
3694 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = currentBlock.renderBoxFragmentInfo(fragment);
3695 if (boxInfo)
3696 staticPosition += boxInfo->logicalLeft();
3697 }
3698 }
3699 logicalLeft.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, staticPosition);
3700 } else {
3701 LayoutUnit staticPosition = child->layer()->staticInlinePosition() + containerLogicalWidth + containerBlock.borderLogicalLeft();
3702 auto& enclosingBox = parent->enclosingBox();
3703 if (&enclosingBox != &containerBlock && containerBlock.isDescendantOf(&enclosingBox)) {
3704 logicalRight.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, staticPosition);
3705 return;
3706 }
3707
3708 staticPosition -= enclosingBox.logicalWidth();
3709 for (const RenderElement* current = &enclosingBox; current; current = current->container()) {
3710 if (!is<RenderBox>(*current))
3711 continue;
3712
3713 if (current != &containerBlock) {
3714 auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*current);
3715 staticPosition -= renderBox.logicalLeft();
3716 if (renderBox.isInFlowPositioned())
3717 staticPosition -= renderBox.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().width() : renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().height();
3718 }
3719 if (fragment && is<RenderBlock>(*current)) {
3720 auto& currentBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(*current);
3721 fragment = currentBlock.clampToStartAndEndFragments(fragment);
3722 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = currentBlock.renderBoxFragmentInfo(fragment);
3723 if (boxInfo) {
3724 if (current != &containerBlock)
3725 staticPosition -= currentBlock.logicalWidth() - (boxInfo->logicalLeft() + boxInfo->logicalWidth());
3726 if (current == &enclosingBox)
3727 staticPosition += enclosingBox.logicalWidth() - boxInfo->logicalWidth();
3728 }
3729 }
3730 if (current == &containerBlock)
3731 break;
3732 }
3733 logicalRight.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, staticPosition);
3734 }
3735}
3736
3737void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalWidth(LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues, RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
3738{
3739 if (isReplaced()) {
3740 // FIXME: Positioned replaced elements inside a flow thread are not working properly
3741 // with variable width fragments (see https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=69896 ).
3742 computePositionedLogicalWidthReplaced(computedValues);
3743 return;
3744 }
3745
3746 // QUESTIONS
3747 // FIXME 1: Should we still deal with these the cases of 'left' or 'right' having
3748 // the type 'static' in determining whether to calculate the static distance?
3749 // NOTE: 'static' is not a legal value for 'left' or 'right' as of CSS 2.1.
3750
3751 // FIXME 2: Can perhaps optimize out cases when max-width/min-width are greater
3752 // than or less than the computed width(). Be careful of box-sizing and
3753 // percentage issues.
3754
3755 // The following is based off of the W3C Working Draft from April 11, 2006 of
3756 // CSS 2.1: Section 10.3.7 "Absolutely positioned, non-replaced elements"
3757 // <http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#abs-non-replaced-width>
3758 // (block-style-comments in this function and in computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing()
3759 // correspond to text from the spec)
3760
3761
3762 // We don't use containingBlock(), since we may be positioned by an enclosing
3763 // relative positioned inline.
3764 const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container());
3765
3766 const LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock, fragment);
3767
3768 // Use the container block's direction except when calculating the static distance
3769 // This conforms with the reference results for abspos-replaced-width-margin-000.htm
3770 // of the CSS 2.1 test suite
3771 TextDirection containerDirection = containerBlock.style().direction();
3772
3773 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
3774 const LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding = borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
3775 const Length marginLogicalLeft = isHorizontal ? style().marginLeft() : style().marginTop();
3776 const Length marginLogicalRight = isHorizontal ? style().marginRight() : style().marginBottom();
3777
3778 Length logicalLeftLength = style().logicalLeft();
3779 Length logicalRightLength = style().logicalRight();
3780
3781 /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
3782 * For the purposes of this section and the next, the term "static position"
3783 * (of an element) refers, roughly, to the position an element would have had
3784 * in the normal flow. More precisely:
3785 *
3786 * * The static position for 'left' is the distance from the left edge of the
3787 * containing block to the left margin edge of a hypothetical box that would
3788 * have been the first box of the element if its 'position' property had
3789 * been 'static' and 'float' had been 'none'. The value is negative if the
3790 * hypothetical box is to the left of the containing block.
3791 * * The static position for 'right' is the distance from the right edge of the
3792 * containing block to the right margin edge of the same hypothetical box as
3793 * above. The value is positive if the hypothetical box is to the left of the
3794 * containing block's edge.
3795 *
3796 * But rather than actually calculating the dimensions of that hypothetical box,
3797 * user agents are free to make a guess at its probable position.
3798 *
3799 * For the purposes of calculating the static position, the containing block of
3800 * fixed positioned elements is the initial containing block instead of the
3801 * viewport, and all scrollable boxes should be assumed to be scrolled to their
3802 * origin.
3803 \*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3804
3805 // see FIXME 1
3806 // Calculate the static distance if needed.
3807 computeInlineStaticDistance(logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, this, containerBlock, containerLogicalWidth, fragment);
3808
3809 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'width' case.
3810 computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(MainOrPreferredSize, style().logicalWidth(), containerBlock, containerDirection,
3811 containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding,
3812 logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, marginLogicalLeft, marginLogicalRight,
3813 computedValues);
3814
3815 LayoutUnit transferredMinSize = LayoutUnit::min();
3816 LayoutUnit transferredMaxSize = LayoutUnit::max();
3817 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio())
3818 std::tie(transferredMinSize, transferredMaxSize) = computeMinMaxLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
3819
3820 LogicalExtentComputedValues maxValues;
3821 maxValues.m_extent = LayoutUnit::max();
3822 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'max-width' case.
3823 if (!style().logicalMaxWidth().isUndefined()) {
3824 computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(MaxSize, style().logicalMaxWidth(), containerBlock, containerDirection,
3825 containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding,
3826 logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, marginLogicalLeft, marginLogicalRight,
3827 maxValues);
3828 }
3829 if (transferredMaxSize < maxValues.m_extent) {
3830 computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(MaxSize, Length(transferredMaxSize, LengthType::Fixed), containerBlock, containerDirection,
3831 containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding,
3832 logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, marginLogicalLeft, marginLogicalRight,
3833 maxValues);
3834 }
3835 if (computedValues.m_extent > maxValues.m_extent) {
3836 computedValues.m_extent = maxValues.m_extent;
3837 computedValues.m_position = maxValues.m_position;
3838 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = maxValues.m_margins.m_start;
3839 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = maxValues.m_margins.m_end;
3840 }
3841
3842 LogicalExtentComputedValues minValues;
3843 minValues.m_extent = LayoutUnit::min();
3844 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'min-width' case.
3845 if (!style().logicalMinWidth().isZero() || style().logicalMinWidth().isIntrinsic()) {
3846 computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(MinSize, style().logicalMinWidth(), containerBlock, containerDirection,
3847 containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding,
3848 logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, marginLogicalLeft, marginLogicalRight,
3849 minValues);
3850 }
3851 if (transferredMinSize > minValues.m_extent) {
3852 computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(MinSize, Length(transferredMinSize, LengthType::Fixed), containerBlock, containerDirection,
3853 containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding,
3854 logicalLeftLength, logicalRightLength, marginLogicalLeft, marginLogicalRight,
3855 minValues);
3856 }
3857 if (computedValues.m_extent < minValues.m_extent) {
3858 computedValues.m_extent = minValues.m_extent;
3859 computedValues.m_position = minValues.m_position;
3860 computedValues.m_margins.m_start = minValues.m_margins.m_start;
3861 computedValues.m_margins.m_end = minValues.m_margins.m_end;
3862 }
3863
3864 computedValues.m_extent += bordersPlusPadding;
3865 if (is<RenderBox>(containerBlock)) {
3866 auto& containingBox = downcast<RenderBox>(containerBlock);
3867 if (containingBox.shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft() && isHorizontalWritingMode())
3868 computedValues.m_position += containingBox.verticalScrollbarWidth();
3869 }
3870
3871 // Adjust logicalLeft if we need to for the flipped version of our writing mode in fragments.
3872 // FIXME: Add support for other types of objects as containerBlock, not only RenderBlock.
3873 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
3874 if (fragmentedFlow && !fragment && isWritingModeRoot() && isHorizontalWritingMode() == containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() && is<RenderBlock>(containerBlock)) {
3875 ASSERT(containerBlock.canHaveBoxInfoInFragment());
3876 LayoutUnit logicalLeftPos = computedValues.m_position;
3877 const RenderBlock& renderBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(containerBlock);
3878 LayoutUnit cbPageOffset = renderBlock.offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage();
3879 RenderFragmentContainer* cbFragment = renderBlock.fragmentAtBlockOffset(cbPageOffset);
3880 if (cbFragment) {
3881 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = renderBlock.renderBoxFragmentInfo(cbFragment);
3882 if (boxInfo) {
3883 logicalLeftPos += boxInfo->logicalLeft();
3884 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeftPos;
3885 }
3886 }
3887 }
3888}
3889
3890static void computeLogicalLeftPositionedOffset(LayoutUnit& logicalLeftPos, const RenderBox* child, LayoutUnit logicalWidthValue, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock, LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth)
3891{
3892 // Deal with differing writing modes here. Our offset needs to be in the containing block's coordinate space. If the containing block is flipped
3893 // along this axis, then we need to flip the coordinate. This can only happen if the containing block is both a flipped mode and perpendicular to us.
3894 if (containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() != child->isHorizontalWritingMode() && containerBlock.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode()) {
3895 logicalLeftPos = containerLogicalWidth - logicalWidthValue - logicalLeftPos;
3896 logicalLeftPos += (child->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? containerBlock.borderRight() : containerBlock.borderBottom());
3897 } else
3898 logicalLeftPos += (child->isHorizontalWritingMode() ? containerBlock.borderLeft() : containerBlock.borderTop());
3899}
3900
3901void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalWidthUsing(SizeType widthType, Length logicalWidth, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock, TextDirection containerDirection,
3902 LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding,
3903 Length logicalLeft, Length logicalRight, Length marginLogicalLeft, Length marginLogicalRight,
3904 LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues) const
3905{
3906 ASSERT(widthType == MinSize || widthType == MainOrPreferredSize || !logicalWidth.isAuto());
3907 auto originalLogicalWidthType = logicalWidth.type();
3908 if (widthType == MinSize && logicalWidth.isAuto()) {
3909 if (shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio()) {
3910 LayoutUnit minLogicalWidth;
3911 LayoutUnit maxLogicalWidth;
3912 computeIntrinsicLogicalWidths(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
3913 logicalWidth = Length(minLogicalWidth, LengthType::Fixed);
3914 } else
3915 logicalWidth = Length(0, LengthType::Fixed);
3916 } else if (widthType == MainOrPreferredSize && logicalWidth.isAuto() && shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio())
3917 logicalWidth = Length(computeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio(), LengthType::Fixed);
3918 else if (logicalWidth.isIntrinsic())
3919 logicalWidth = Length(computeIntrinsicLogicalWidthUsing(logicalWidth, containerLogicalWidth, bordersPlusPadding) - bordersPlusPadding, LengthType::Fixed);
3920
3921 // 'left' and 'right' cannot both be 'auto' because one would of been
3922 // converted to the static position already
3923 ASSERT(!(logicalLeft.isAuto() && logicalRight.isAuto()));
3924
3925 LayoutUnit logicalLeftValue;
3926
3927 const LayoutUnit containerRelativeLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock, nullptr, false);
3928
3929 bool logicalWidthIsAuto = logicalWidth.isIntrinsicOrAuto() && !shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio();
3930 bool logicalLeftIsAuto = logicalLeft.isAuto();
3931 bool logicalRightIsAuto = logicalRight.isAuto();
3932 LayoutUnit& marginLogicalLeftValue = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? computedValues.m_margins.m_start : computedValues.m_margins.m_end;
3933 LayoutUnit& marginLogicalRightValue = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? computedValues.m_margins.m_end : computedValues.m_margins.m_start;
3934
3935 if (!logicalLeftIsAuto && !logicalWidthIsAuto && !logicalRightIsAuto) {
3936 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
3937 * If none of the three is 'auto': If both 'margin-left' and 'margin-
3938 * right' are 'auto', solve the equation under the extra constraint that
3939 * the two margins get equal values, unless this would make them negative,
3940 * in which case when direction of the containing block is 'ltr' ('rtl'),
3941 * set 'margin-left' ('margin-right') to zero and solve for 'margin-right'
3942 * ('margin-left'). If one of 'margin-left' or 'margin-right' is 'auto',
3943 * solve the equation for that value. If the values are over-constrained,
3944 * ignore the value for 'left' (in case the 'direction' property of the
3945 * containing block is 'rtl') or 'right' (in case 'direction' is 'ltr')
3946 * and solve for that value.
3947 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
3948 // NOTE: It is not necessary to solve for 'right' in the over constrained
3949 // case because the value is not used for any further calculations.
3950
3951 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
3952 computedValues.m_extent = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalWidth, containerLogicalWidth), originalLogicalWidthType);
3953
3954 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalWidth - (logicalLeftValue + computedValues.m_extent + valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth) + bordersPlusPadding);
3955
3956 // Margins are now the only unknown
3957 if (marginLogicalLeft.isAuto() && marginLogicalRight.isAuto()) {
3958 // Both margins auto, solve for equality
3959 if (availableSpace >= 0) {
3960 marginLogicalLeftValue = availableSpace / 2; // split the difference
3961 marginLogicalRightValue = availableSpace - marginLogicalLeftValue; // account for odd valued differences
3962 } else {
3963 // Use the containing block's direction rather than the parent block's
3964 // per CSS 2.1 reference test abspos-non-replaced-width-margin-000.
3965 if (containerDirection == TextDirection::LTR) {
3966 marginLogicalLeftValue = 0;
3967 marginLogicalRightValue = availableSpace; // will be negative
3968 } else {
3969 marginLogicalLeftValue = availableSpace; // will be negative
3970 marginLogicalRightValue = 0;
3971 }
3972 }
3973 } else if (marginLogicalLeft.isAuto()) {
3974 // Solve for left margin
3975 marginLogicalRightValue = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
3976 marginLogicalLeftValue = availableSpace - marginLogicalRightValue;
3977 } else if (marginLogicalRight.isAuto()) {
3978 // Solve for right margin
3979 marginLogicalLeftValue = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
3980 marginLogicalRightValue = availableSpace - marginLogicalLeftValue;
3981 } else {
3982 // Over-constrained, solve for left if direction is RTL
3983 marginLogicalLeftValue = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
3984 marginLogicalRightValue = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
3985
3986 // Use the containing block's direction rather than the parent block's
3987 // per CSS 2.1 reference test abspos-non-replaced-width-margin-000.
3988 if (containerDirection == TextDirection::RTL)
3989 logicalLeftValue = (availableSpace + logicalLeftValue) - marginLogicalLeftValue - marginLogicalRightValue;
3990 }
3991 } else {
3992 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------*\
3993 * Otherwise, set 'auto' values for 'margin-left' and 'margin-right'
3994 * to 0, and pick the one of the following six rules that applies.
3995 *
3996 * 1. 'left' and 'width' are 'auto' and 'right' is not 'auto', then the
3997 * width is shrink-to-fit. Then solve for 'left'
3998 *
3999 * OMIT RULE 2 AS IT SHOULD NEVER BE HIT
4000 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
4001 * 2. 'left' and 'right' are 'auto' and 'width' is not 'auto', then if
4002 * the 'direction' property of the containing block is 'ltr' set
4003 * 'left' to the static position, otherwise set 'right' to the
4004 * static position. Then solve for 'left' (if 'direction is 'rtl')
4005 * or 'right' (if 'direction' is 'ltr').
4006 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
4007 *
4008 * 3. 'width' and 'right' are 'auto' and 'left' is not 'auto', then the
4009 * width is shrink-to-fit . Then solve for 'right'
4010 * 4. 'left' is 'auto', 'width' and 'right' are not 'auto', then solve
4011 * for 'left'
4012 * 5. 'width' is 'auto', 'left' and 'right' are not 'auto', then solve
4013 * for 'width'
4014 * 6. 'right' is 'auto', 'left' and 'width' are not 'auto', then solve
4015 * for 'right'
4016 *
4017 * Calculation of the shrink-to-fit width is similar to calculating the
4018 * width of a table cell using the automatic table layout algorithm.
4019 * Roughly: calculate the preferred width by formatting the content
4020 * without breaking lines other than where explicit line breaks occur,
4021 * and also calculate the preferred minimum width, e.g., by trying all
4022 * possible line breaks. CSS 2.1 does not define the exact algorithm.
4023 * Thirdly, calculate the available width: this is found by solving
4024 * for 'width' after setting 'left' (in case 1) or 'right' (in case 3)
4025 * to 0.
4026 *
4027 * Then the shrink-to-fit width is:
4028 * min(max(preferred minimum width, available width), preferred width).
4029 \*--------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4030 // NOTE: For rules 3 and 6 it is not necessary to solve for 'right'
4031 // because the value is not used for any further calculations.
4032
4033 // Calculate margins, 'auto' margins are ignored.
4034 marginLogicalLeftValue = minimumValueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4035 marginLogicalRightValue = minimumValueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4036
4037 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalWidth - (marginLogicalLeftValue + marginLogicalRightValue + bordersPlusPadding);
4038
4039 // FIXME: Is there a faster way to find the correct case?
4040 // Use rule/case that applies.
4041 if (logicalLeftIsAuto && logicalWidthIsAuto && !logicalRightIsAuto) {
4042 // RULE 1: (use shrink-to-fit for width, and solve of left)
4043 LayoutUnit logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4044
4045 // FIXME: would it be better to have shrink-to-fit in one step?
4046 LayoutUnit preferredWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth() - bordersPlusPadding;
4047 LayoutUnit preferredMinWidth = minPreferredLogicalWidth() - bordersPlusPadding;
4048 LayoutUnit availableWidth = availableSpace - logicalRightValue;
4049 computedValues.m_extent = std::min(std::max(preferredMinWidth, availableWidth), preferredWidth);
4050 logicalLeftValue = availableSpace - (computedValues.m_extent + logicalRightValue);
4051 } else if (!logicalLeftIsAuto && logicalWidthIsAuto && logicalRightIsAuto) {
4052 // RULE 3: (use shrink-to-fit for width, and no need solve of right)
4053 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4054
4055 // FIXME: would it be better to have shrink-to-fit in one step?
4056 LayoutUnit preferredWidth = maxPreferredLogicalWidth() - bordersPlusPadding;
4057 LayoutUnit preferredMinWidth = minPreferredLogicalWidth() - bordersPlusPadding;
4058 LayoutUnit availableWidth = availableSpace - logicalLeftValue;
4059 computedValues.m_extent = std::min(std::max(preferredMinWidth, availableWidth), preferredWidth);
4060 } else if (logicalLeftIsAuto && !logicalWidthIsAuto && !logicalRightIsAuto) {
4061 // RULE 4: (solve for left)
4062 computedValues.m_extent = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalWidth, containerLogicalWidth), originalLogicalWidthType);
4063 logicalLeftValue = availableSpace - (computedValues.m_extent + valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth));
4064 } else if (!logicalLeftIsAuto && logicalWidthIsAuto && !logicalRightIsAuto) {
4065 // RULE 5: (solve for width)
4066 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4067 computedValues.m_extent = availableSpace - (logicalLeftValue + valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth));
4068 } else if (!logicalLeftIsAuto && !logicalWidthIsAuto && logicalRightIsAuto) {
4069 // RULE 6: (no need solve for right)
4070 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4071 computedValues.m_extent = adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalWidth, containerLogicalWidth), originalLogicalWidthType);
4072 }
4073 }
4074
4075 // Use computed values to calculate the horizontal position.
4076
4077 // FIXME: This hack is needed to calculate the logical left position for a 'rtl' relatively
4078 // positioned, inline because right now, it is using the logical left position
4079 // of the first line box when really it should use the last line box. When
4080 // this is fixed elsewhere, this block should be removed.
4081 if (is<RenderInline>(containerBlock) && !containerBlock.style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
4082 const auto& flow = downcast<RenderInline>(containerBlock);
4083 LegacyInlineFlowBox* firstLine = flow.firstLineBox();
4084 LegacyInlineFlowBox* lastLine = flow.lastLineBox();
4085 if (firstLine && lastLine && firstLine != lastLine) {
4086 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeftValue + marginLogicalLeftValue + lastLine->borderLogicalLeft() + (lastLine->logicalLeft() - firstLine->logicalLeft());
4087 return;
4088 }
4089 }
4090
4091 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeftValue + marginLogicalLeftValue;
4092 computeLogicalLeftPositionedOffset(computedValues.m_position, this, computedValues.m_extent + bordersPlusPadding, containerBlock, containerLogicalWidth);
4093}
4094
4095static void computeBlockStaticDistance(Length& logicalTop, Length& logicalBottom, const RenderBox* child, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock)
4096{
4097 if (!logicalTop.isAuto() || !logicalBottom.isAuto())
4098 return;
4099
4100 RenderObject* parent = child->parent();
4101 bool isParentDirectionLTR = parent->style().direction() == TextDirection::LTR;
4102
4103 // FIXME: The static distance computation has not been fully patched for mixed writing modes.
4104 LayoutUnit staticLogicalTop = isVerticalLRChildInHorizontalTBParent(*child, *parent) && isParentDirectionLTR ? child->layer()->staticInlinePosition() - containerBlock.borderLogicalLeft() : child->layer()->staticBlockPosition() - containerBlock.borderBefore();
4105 for (RenderElement* container = child->parent(); container && container != &containerBlock; container = container->container()) {
4106 if (!is<RenderBox>(*container))
4107 continue;
4108 const auto& renderBox = downcast<RenderBox>(*container);
4109 if (!is<RenderTableRow>(renderBox))
4110 staticLogicalTop += isVerticalLRChildInHorizontalTBParent(*child, *parent) && isParentDirectionLTR ? renderBox.logicalLeft() : renderBox.logicalTop();
4111 if (renderBox.isInFlowPositioned())
4112 staticLogicalTop += renderBox.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().height() : renderBox.offsetForInFlowPosition().width();
4113 }
4114 logicalTop.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, staticLogicalTop);
4115}
4116
4117void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalHeight(LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues) const
4118{
4119 if (isReplaced()) {
4120 computePositionedLogicalHeightReplaced(computedValues);
4121 return;
4122 }
4123
4124 // The following is based off of the W3C Working Draft from April 11, 2006 of
4125 // CSS 2.1: Section 10.6.4 "Absolutely positioned, non-replaced elements"
4126 // <http://www.w3.org/TR/2005/WD-CSS21-20050613/visudet.html#abs-non-replaced-height>
4127 // (block-style-comments in this function and in computePositionedLogicalHeightUsing()
4128 // correspond to text from the spec)
4129
4130
4131 // We don't use containingBlock(), since we may be positioned by an enclosing relpositioned inline.
4132 const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container());
4133
4134 const LayoutUnit containerLogicalHeight = containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(containerBlock);
4135
4136 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
4137 const LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding = borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
4138 const Length marginBefore = styleToUse.marginBefore();
4139 const Length marginAfter = styleToUse.marginAfter();
4140 Length logicalTopLength = styleToUse.logicalTop();
4141 Length logicalBottomLength = styleToUse.logicalBottom();
4142
4143 /*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4144 * For the purposes of this section and the next, the term "static position"
4145 * (of an element) refers, roughly, to the position an element would have had
4146 * in the normal flow. More precisely, the static position for 'top' is the
4147 * distance from the top edge of the containing block to the top margin edge
4148 * of a hypothetical box that would have been the first box of the element if
4149 * its 'position' property had been 'static' and 'float' had been 'none'. The
4150 * value is negative if the hypothetical box is above the containing block.
4151 *
4152 * But rather than actually calculating the dimensions of that hypothetical
4153 * box, user agents are free to make a guess at its probable position.
4154 *
4155 * For the purposes of calculating the static position, the containing block
4156 * of fixed positioned elements is the initial containing block instead of
4157 * the viewport.
4158 \*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4159
4160 // see FIXME 1
4161 // Calculate the static distance if needed.
4162 computeBlockStaticDistance(logicalTopLength, logicalBottomLength, this, containerBlock);
4163
4164 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'height' case.
4165 LayoutUnit logicalHeight = computedValues.m_extent;
4166 computePositionedLogicalHeightUsing(MainOrPreferredSize, styleToUse.logicalHeight(), containerBlock, containerLogicalHeight, bordersPlusPadding, logicalHeight,
4167 logicalTopLength, logicalBottomLength, marginBefore, marginAfter,
4168 computedValues);
4169
4170 // Avoid doing any work in the common case (where the values of min-height and max-height are their defaults).
4171 // see FIXME 2
4172
4173 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'max-height' case.
4174 if (!styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight().isUndefined()) {
4175 LogicalExtentComputedValues maxValues;
4176
4177 computePositionedLogicalHeightUsing(MaxSize, styleToUse.logicalMaxHeight(), containerBlock, containerLogicalHeight, bordersPlusPadding, logicalHeight,
4178 logicalTopLength, logicalBottomLength, marginBefore, marginAfter,
4179 maxValues);
4180
4181 if (computedValues.m_extent > maxValues.m_extent) {
4182 computedValues.m_extent = maxValues.m_extent;
4183 computedValues.m_position = maxValues.m_position;
4184 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = maxValues.m_margins.m_before;
4185 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = maxValues.m_margins.m_after;
4186 }
4187 }
4188
4189 // Calculate constraint equation values for 'min-height' case.
4190 Length logicalMinHeight = styleToUse.logicalMinHeight();
4191 if (logicalMinHeight.isAuto() || !logicalMinHeight.isZero() || logicalMinHeight.isIntrinsic()) {
4192 LogicalExtentComputedValues minValues;
4193
4194 computePositionedLogicalHeightUsing(MinSize, styleToUse.logicalMinHeight(), containerBlock, containerLogicalHeight, bordersPlusPadding, logicalHeight,
4195 logicalTopLength, logicalBottomLength, marginBefore, marginAfter,
4196 minValues);
4197
4198 if (computedValues.m_extent < minValues.m_extent) {
4199 computedValues.m_extent = minValues.m_extent;
4200 computedValues.m_position = minValues.m_position;
4201 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = minValues.m_margins.m_before;
4202 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = minValues.m_margins.m_after;
4203 }
4204 }
4205
4206 // Set final height value.
4207 computedValues.m_extent += bordersPlusPadding;
4208
4209 // Adjust logicalTop if we need to for perpendicular writing modes in fragments.
4210 // FIXME: Add support for other types of objects as containerBlock, not only RenderBlock.
4211 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
4212 if (fragmentedFlow && isHorizontalWritingMode() != containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode() && is<RenderBlock>(containerBlock)) {
4213 ASSERT(containerBlock.canHaveBoxInfoInFragment());
4214 LayoutUnit logicalTopPos = computedValues.m_position;
4215 const RenderBlock& renderBox = downcast<RenderBlock>(containerBlock);
4216 LayoutUnit cbPageOffset = renderBox.offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() - logicalLeft();
4217 RenderFragmentContainer* cbFragment = renderBox.fragmentAtBlockOffset(cbPageOffset);
4218 if (cbFragment) {
4219 RenderBoxFragmentInfo* boxInfo = renderBox.renderBoxFragmentInfo(cbFragment);
4220 if (boxInfo) {
4221 logicalTopPos += boxInfo->logicalLeft();
4222 computedValues.m_position = logicalTopPos;
4223 }
4224 }
4225 }
4226}
4227
4228static void computeLogicalTopPositionedOffset(LayoutUnit& logicalTopPos, const RenderBox* child, LayoutUnit logicalHeightValue, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock, LayoutUnit containerLogicalHeight)
4229{
4230 // Deal with differing writing modes here. Our offset needs to be in the containing block's coordinate space. If the containing block is flipped
4231 // along this axis, then we need to flip the coordinate. This can only happen if the containing block is both a flipped mode and perpendicular to us.
4232 if ((child->style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() && child->isHorizontalWritingMode() != containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode())
4233 || (child->style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() != containerBlock.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() && child->isHorizontalWritingMode() == containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode()))
4234 logicalTopPos = containerLogicalHeight - logicalHeightValue - logicalTopPos;
4235
4236 // Our offset is from the logical bottom edge in a flipped environment, e.g., right for vertical-rl and bottom for horizontal-bt.
4237 if (containerBlock.style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode() && child->isHorizontalWritingMode() == containerBlock.isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
4238 if (child->isHorizontalWritingMode())
4239 logicalTopPos += containerBlock.borderBottom();
4240 else
4241 logicalTopPos += containerBlock.borderRight();
4242 } else {
4243 if (child->isHorizontalWritingMode())
4244 logicalTopPos += containerBlock.borderTop();
4245 else
4246 logicalTopPos += containerBlock.borderLeft();
4247 }
4248}
4249
4250void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalHeightUsing(SizeType heightType, Length logicalHeightLength, const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock,
4251 LayoutUnit containerLogicalHeight, LayoutUnit bordersPlusPadding, LayoutUnit logicalHeight,
4252 Length logicalTop, Length logicalBottom, Length marginBefore, Length marginAfter,
4253 LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues) const
4254{
4255 ASSERT(heightType == MinSize || heightType == MainOrPreferredSize || !logicalHeightLength.isAuto());
4256 if (heightType == MinSize && logicalHeightLength.isAuto()) {
4257 if (shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio())
4258 logicalHeightLength = Length(logicalHeight, LengthType::Fixed);
4259 else
4260 logicalHeightLength = Length(0, LengthType::Fixed);
4261 }
4262
4263 // 'top' and 'bottom' cannot both be 'auto' because 'top would of been
4264 // converted to the static position in computePositionedLogicalHeight()
4265 ASSERT(!(logicalTop.isAuto() && logicalBottom.isAuto()));
4266
4267 LayoutUnit logicalHeightValue;
4268 LayoutUnit contentLogicalHeight = logicalHeight - bordersPlusPadding;
4269
4270 const LayoutUnit containerRelativeLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock, nullptr, false);
4271
4272 LayoutUnit logicalTopValue;
4273
4274 bool fromAspectRatio = heightType == MainOrPreferredSize && shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio();
4275 bool logicalHeightIsAuto = logicalHeightLength.isAuto() && !fromAspectRatio;
4276 bool logicalTopIsAuto = logicalTop.isAuto();
4277 bool logicalBottomIsAuto = logicalBottom.isAuto();
4278
4279 // Height is never unsolved for tables.
4280 LayoutUnit resolvedLogicalHeight;
4281 if (isTable()) {
4282 resolvedLogicalHeight = contentLogicalHeight;
4283 logicalHeightIsAuto = false;
4284 } else {
4285 if (logicalHeightLength.isIntrinsic())
4286 resolvedLogicalHeight = computeIntrinsicLogicalContentHeightUsing(logicalHeightLength, contentLogicalHeight, bordersPlusPadding).value();
4287 else if (fromAspectRatio) {
4288 resolvedLogicalHeight = blockSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalWidth());
4289 resolvedLogicalHeight = std::max(LayoutUnit(), resolvedLogicalHeight - bordersPlusPadding);
4290 } else
4291 resolvedLogicalHeight = adjustContentBoxLogicalHeightForBoxSizing(valueForLength(logicalHeightLength, containerLogicalHeight));
4292 }
4293
4294 if (!logicalTopIsAuto && !logicalHeightIsAuto && !logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4295 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4296 * If none of the three are 'auto': If both 'margin-top' and 'margin-
4297 * bottom' are 'auto', solve the equation under the extra constraint that
4298 * the two margins get equal values. If one of 'margin-top' or 'margin-
4299 * bottom' is 'auto', solve the equation for that value. If the values
4300 * are over-constrained, ignore the value for 'bottom' and solve for that
4301 * value.
4302 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4303 // NOTE: It is not necessary to solve for 'bottom' in the over constrained
4304 // case because the value is not used for any further calculations.
4305
4306 logicalHeightValue = resolvedLogicalHeight;
4307 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4308
4309 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalHeight - (logicalTopValue + logicalHeightValue + valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight) + bordersPlusPadding);
4310
4311 // Margins are now the only unknown
4312 if (marginBefore.isAuto() && marginAfter.isAuto()) {
4313 // Both margins auto, solve for equality
4314 // NOTE: This may result in negative values.
4315 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = availableSpace / 2; // split the difference
4316 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = availableSpace - computedValues.m_margins.m_before; // account for odd valued differences
4317 } else if (marginBefore.isAuto()) {
4318 // Solve for top margin
4319 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4320 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = availableSpace - computedValues.m_margins.m_after;
4321 } else if (marginAfter.isAuto()) {
4322 // Solve for bottom margin
4323 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4324 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = availableSpace - computedValues.m_margins.m_before;
4325 } else {
4326 // Over-constrained, (no need solve for bottom)
4327 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4328 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4329 }
4330 } else {
4331 /*--------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4332 * Otherwise, set 'auto' values for 'margin-top' and 'margin-bottom'
4333 * to 0, and pick the one of the following six rules that applies.
4334 *
4335 * 1. 'top' and 'height' are 'auto' and 'bottom' is not 'auto', then
4336 * the height is based on the content, and solve for 'top'.
4337 *
4338 * OMIT RULE 2 AS IT SHOULD NEVER BE HIT
4339 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
4340 * 2. 'top' and 'bottom' are 'auto' and 'height' is not 'auto', then
4341 * set 'top' to the static position, and solve for 'bottom'.
4342 * ------------------------------------------------------------------
4343 *
4344 * 3. 'height' and 'bottom' are 'auto' and 'top' is not 'auto', then
4345 * the height is based on the content, and solve for 'bottom'.
4346 * 4. 'top' is 'auto', 'height' and 'bottom' are not 'auto', and
4347 * solve for 'top'.
4348 * 5. 'height' is 'auto', 'top' and 'bottom' are not 'auto', and
4349 * solve for 'height'.
4350 * 6. 'bottom' is 'auto', 'top' and 'height' are not 'auto', and
4351 * solve for 'bottom'.
4352 \*--------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4353 // NOTE: For rules 3 and 6 it is not necessary to solve for 'bottom'
4354 // because the value is not used for any further calculations.
4355
4356 // Calculate margins, 'auto' margins are ignored.
4357 computedValues.m_margins.m_before = minimumValueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4358 computedValues.m_margins.m_after = minimumValueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4359
4360 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalHeight - (computedValues.m_margins.m_before + computedValues.m_margins.m_after + bordersPlusPadding);
4361
4362 // Use rule/case that applies.
4363 if (logicalTopIsAuto && logicalHeightIsAuto && !logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4364 // RULE 1: (height is content based, solve of top)
4365 logicalHeightValue = contentLogicalHeight;
4366 logicalTopValue = availableSpace - (logicalHeightValue + valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight));
4367 } else if (!logicalTopIsAuto && logicalHeightIsAuto && logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4368 // RULE 3: (height is content based, no need solve of bottom)
4369 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4370 logicalHeightValue = contentLogicalHeight;
4371 } else if (logicalTopIsAuto && !logicalHeightIsAuto && !logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4372 // RULE 4: (solve of top)
4373 logicalHeightValue = resolvedLogicalHeight;
4374 logicalTopValue = availableSpace - (logicalHeightValue + valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight));
4375 } else if (!logicalTopIsAuto && logicalHeightIsAuto && !logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4376 // RULE 5: (solve of height)
4377 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4378 logicalHeightValue = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, availableSpace - (logicalTopValue + valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight)));
4379 } else if (!logicalTopIsAuto && !logicalHeightIsAuto && logicalBottomIsAuto) {
4380 // RULE 6: (no need solve of bottom)
4381 logicalHeightValue = resolvedLogicalHeight;
4382 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4383 }
4384 }
4385 computedValues.m_extent = logicalHeightValue;
4386
4387 // Use computed values to calculate the vertical position.
4388 computedValues.m_position = logicalTopValue + computedValues.m_margins.m_before;
4389 computeLogicalTopPositionedOffset(computedValues.m_position, this, logicalHeightValue + bordersPlusPadding, containerBlock, containerLogicalHeight);
4390}
4391
4392void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalWidthReplaced(LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues) const
4393{
4394 // The following is based off of the W3C Working Draft from April 11, 2006 of
4395 // CSS 2.1: Section 10.3.8 "Absolutely positioned, replaced elements"
4396 // <http://www.w3.org/TR/2005/WD-CSS21-20050613/visudet.html#abs-replaced-width>
4397 // (block-style-comments in this function correspond to text from the spec and
4398 // the numbers correspond to numbers in spec)
4399
4400 // We don't use containingBlock(), since we may be positioned by an enclosing
4401 // relative positioned inline.
4402 const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container());
4403
4404 const LayoutUnit containerLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock);
4405 const LayoutUnit containerRelativeLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock, nullptr, false);
4406
4407 // To match WinIE, in quirks mode use the parent's 'direction' property
4408 // instead of the container block's.
4409 TextDirection containerDirection = containerBlock.style().direction();
4410
4411 // Variables to solve.
4412 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
4413 Length logicalLeft = style().logicalLeft();
4414 Length logicalRight = style().logicalRight();
4415 Length marginLogicalLeft = isHorizontal ? style().marginLeft() : style().marginTop();
4416 Length marginLogicalRight = isHorizontal ? style().marginRight() : style().marginBottom();
4417 LayoutUnit& marginLogicalLeftAlias = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? computedValues.m_margins.m_start : computedValues.m_margins.m_end;
4418 LayoutUnit& marginLogicalRightAlias = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? computedValues.m_margins.m_end : computedValues.m_margins.m_start;
4419
4420 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4421 * 1. The used value of 'width' is determined as for inline replaced
4422 * elements.
4423 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4424 // NOTE: This value of width is final in that the min/max width calculations
4425 // are dealt with in computeReplacedWidth(). This means that the steps to produce
4426 // correct max/min in the non-replaced version, are not necessary.
4427 computedValues.m_extent = computeReplacedLogicalWidth() + borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth();
4428
4429 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalWidth - computedValues.m_extent;
4430
4431 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4432 * 2. If both 'left' and 'right' have the value 'auto', then if 'direction'
4433 * of the containing block is 'ltr', set 'left' to the static position;
4434 * else if 'direction' is 'rtl', set 'right' to the static position.
4435 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4436 // see FIXME 1
4437 computeInlineStaticDistance(logicalLeft, logicalRight, this, containerBlock, containerLogicalWidth, nullptr); // FIXME: Pass the fragment.
4438
4439 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4440 * 3. If 'left' or 'right' are 'auto', replace any 'auto' on 'margin-left'
4441 * or 'margin-right' with '0'.
4442 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4443 if (logicalLeft.isAuto() || logicalRight.isAuto()) {
4444 if (marginLogicalLeft.isAuto())
4445 marginLogicalLeft.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
4446 if (marginLogicalRight.isAuto())
4447 marginLogicalRight.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
4448 }
4449
4450 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4451 * 4. If at this point both 'margin-left' and 'margin-right' are still
4452 * 'auto', solve the equation under the extra constraint that the two
4453 * margins must get equal values, unless this would make them negative,
4454 * in which case when the direction of the containing block is 'ltr'
4455 * ('rtl'), set 'margin-left' ('margin-right') to zero and solve for
4456 * 'margin-right' ('margin-left').
4457 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4458 LayoutUnit logicalLeftValue;
4459 LayoutUnit logicalRightValue;
4460
4461 if (marginLogicalLeft.isAuto() && marginLogicalRight.isAuto()) {
4462 // 'left' and 'right' cannot be 'auto' due to step 3
4463 ASSERT(!(logicalLeft.isAuto() && logicalRight.isAuto()));
4464
4465 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4466 logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4467
4468 LayoutUnit difference = availableSpace - (logicalLeftValue + logicalRightValue);
4469 if (difference > 0) {
4470 marginLogicalLeftAlias = difference / 2; // split the difference
4471 marginLogicalRightAlias = difference - marginLogicalLeftAlias; // account for odd valued differences
4472 } else {
4473 // Use the containing block's direction rather than the parent block's
4474 // per CSS 2.1 reference test abspos-replaced-width-margin-000.
4475 if (containerDirection == TextDirection::LTR) {
4476 marginLogicalLeftAlias = 0;
4477 marginLogicalRightAlias = difference; // will be negative
4478 } else {
4479 marginLogicalLeftAlias = difference; // will be negative
4480 marginLogicalRightAlias = 0;
4481 }
4482 }
4483
4484 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4485 * 5. If at this point there is an 'auto' left, solve the equation for
4486 * that value.
4487 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4488 } else if (logicalLeft.isAuto()) {
4489 marginLogicalLeftAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4490 marginLogicalRightAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4491 logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4492
4493 // Solve for 'left'
4494 logicalLeftValue = availableSpace - (logicalRightValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias + marginLogicalRightAlias);
4495 } else if (logicalRight.isAuto()) {
4496 marginLogicalLeftAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4497 marginLogicalRightAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4498 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4499
4500 // Solve for 'right'
4501 logicalRightValue = availableSpace - (logicalLeftValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias + marginLogicalRightAlias);
4502 } else if (marginLogicalLeft.isAuto()) {
4503 marginLogicalRightAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4504 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4505 logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4506
4507 // Solve for 'margin-left'
4508 marginLogicalLeftAlias = availableSpace - (logicalLeftValue + logicalRightValue + marginLogicalRightAlias);
4509 } else if (marginLogicalRight.isAuto()) {
4510 marginLogicalLeftAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4511 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4512 logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4513
4514 // Solve for 'margin-right'
4515 marginLogicalRightAlias = availableSpace - (logicalLeftValue + logicalRightValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias);
4516 } else {
4517 // Nothing is 'auto', just calculate the values.
4518 marginLogicalLeftAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalLeft, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4519 marginLogicalRightAlias = valueForLength(marginLogicalRight, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4520 logicalRightValue = valueForLength(logicalRight, containerLogicalWidth);
4521 logicalLeftValue = valueForLength(logicalLeft, containerLogicalWidth);
4522 // If the containing block is right-to-left, then push the left position as far to the right as possible
4523 if (containerDirection == TextDirection::RTL) {
4524 int totalLogicalWidth = computedValues.m_extent + logicalLeftValue + logicalRightValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias + marginLogicalRightAlias;
4525 logicalLeftValue = containerLogicalWidth - (totalLogicalWidth - logicalLeftValue);
4526 }
4527 }
4528
4529 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4530 * 6. If at this point the values are over-constrained, ignore the value
4531 * for either 'left' (in case the 'direction' property of the
4532 * containing block is 'rtl') or 'right' (in case 'direction' is
4533 * 'ltr') and solve for that value.
4534 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4535 // NOTE: Constraints imposed by the width of the containing block and its content have already been accounted for above.
4536
4537 // FIXME: Deal with differing writing modes here. Our offset needs to be in the containing block's coordinate space, so that
4538 // can make the result here rather complicated to compute.
4539
4540 // Use computed values to calculate the horizontal position.
4541
4542 // FIXME: This hack is needed to calculate the logical left position for a 'rtl' relatively
4543 // positioned, inline containing block because right now, it is using the logical left position
4544 // of the first line box when really it should use the last line box. When
4545 // this is fixed elsewhere, this block should be removed.
4546 if (is<RenderInline>(containerBlock) && !containerBlock.style().isLeftToRightDirection()) {
4547 const auto& flow = downcast<RenderInline>(containerBlock);
4548 LegacyInlineFlowBox* firstLine = flow.firstLineBox();
4549 LegacyInlineFlowBox* lastLine = flow.lastLineBox();
4550 if (firstLine && lastLine && firstLine != lastLine) {
4551 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeftValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias + lastLine->borderLogicalLeft() + (lastLine->logicalLeft() - firstLine->logicalLeft());
4552 return;
4553 }
4554 }
4555
4556 LayoutUnit logicalLeftPos = logicalLeftValue + marginLogicalLeftAlias;
4557 // Border and padding have already been included in computedValues.m_extent.
4558 computeLogicalLeftPositionedOffset(logicalLeftPos, this, computedValues.m_extent, containerBlock, containerLogicalWidth);
4559 computedValues.m_position = logicalLeftPos;
4560}
4561
4562void RenderBox::computePositionedLogicalHeightReplaced(LogicalExtentComputedValues& computedValues) const
4563{
4564 // The following is based off of the W3C Working Draft from April 11, 2006 of
4565 // CSS 2.1: Section 10.6.5 "Absolutely positioned, replaced elements"
4566 // <http://www.w3.org/TR/2005/WD-CSS21-20050613/visudet.html#abs-replaced-height>
4567 // (block-style-comments in this function correspond to text from the spec and
4568 // the numbers correspond to numbers in spec)
4569
4570 // We don't use containingBlock(), since we may be positioned by an enclosing relpositioned inline.
4571 const RenderBoxModelObject& containerBlock = downcast<RenderBoxModelObject>(*container());
4572
4573 const LayoutUnit containerLogicalHeight = containingBlockLogicalHeightForPositioned(containerBlock);
4574 const LayoutUnit containerRelativeLogicalWidth = containingBlockLogicalWidthForPositioned(containerBlock, nullptr, false);
4575
4576 // Variables to solve.
4577 Length marginBefore = style().marginBefore();
4578 Length marginAfter = style().marginAfter();
4579 LayoutUnit& marginBeforeAlias = computedValues.m_margins.m_before;
4580 LayoutUnit& marginAfterAlias = computedValues.m_margins.m_after;
4581
4582 Length logicalTop = style().logicalTop();
4583 Length logicalBottom = style().logicalBottom();
4584
4585 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4586 * 1. The used value of 'height' is determined as for inline replaced
4587 * elements.
4588 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4589 // NOTE: This value of height is final in that the min/max height calculations
4590 // are dealt with in computeReplacedHeight(). This means that the steps to produce
4591 // correct max/min in the non-replaced version, are not necessary.
4592 computedValues.m_extent = computeReplacedLogicalHeight() + borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight();
4593 const LayoutUnit availableSpace = containerLogicalHeight - computedValues.m_extent;
4594
4595 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4596 * 2. If both 'top' and 'bottom' have the value 'auto', replace 'top'
4597 * with the element's static position.
4598 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4599 // see FIXME 1
4600 computeBlockStaticDistance(logicalTop, logicalBottom, this, containerBlock);
4601
4602 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4603 * 3. If 'bottom' is 'auto', replace any 'auto' on 'margin-top' or
4604 * 'margin-bottom' with '0'.
4605 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4606 // FIXME: The spec. says that this step should only be taken when bottom is
4607 // auto, but if only top is auto, this makes step 4 impossible.
4608 if (logicalTop.isAuto() || logicalBottom.isAuto()) {
4609 if (marginBefore.isAuto())
4610 marginBefore.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
4611 if (marginAfter.isAuto())
4612 marginAfter.setValue(LengthType::Fixed, 0);
4613 }
4614
4615 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4616 * 4. If at this point both 'margin-top' and 'margin-bottom' are still
4617 * 'auto', solve the equation under the extra constraint that the two
4618 * margins must get equal values.
4619 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4620 LayoutUnit logicalTopValue;
4621 LayoutUnit logicalBottomValue;
4622
4623 if (marginBefore.isAuto() && marginAfter.isAuto()) {
4624 // 'top' and 'bottom' cannot be 'auto' due to step 2 and 3 combined.
4625 ASSERT(!(logicalTop.isAuto() || logicalBottom.isAuto()));
4626
4627 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4628 logicalBottomValue = valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight);
4629
4630 LayoutUnit difference = availableSpace - (logicalTopValue + logicalBottomValue);
4631 // NOTE: This may result in negative values.
4632 marginBeforeAlias = difference / 2; // split the difference
4633 marginAfterAlias = difference - marginBeforeAlias; // account for odd valued differences
4634
4635 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4636 * 5. If at this point there is only one 'auto' left, solve the equation
4637 * for that value.
4638 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4639 } else if (logicalTop.isAuto()) {
4640 marginBeforeAlias = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4641 marginAfterAlias = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4642 logicalBottomValue = valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight);
4643
4644 // Solve for 'top'
4645 logicalTopValue = availableSpace - (logicalBottomValue + marginBeforeAlias + marginAfterAlias);
4646 } else if (logicalBottom.isAuto()) {
4647 marginBeforeAlias = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4648 marginAfterAlias = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4649 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4650
4651 // Solve for 'bottom'
4652 // NOTE: It is not necessary to solve for 'bottom' because we don't ever
4653 // use the value.
4654 } else if (marginBefore.isAuto()) {
4655 marginAfterAlias = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4656 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4657 logicalBottomValue = valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight);
4658
4659 // Solve for 'margin-top'
4660 marginBeforeAlias = availableSpace - (logicalTopValue + logicalBottomValue + marginAfterAlias);
4661 } else if (marginAfter.isAuto()) {
4662 marginBeforeAlias = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4663 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4664 logicalBottomValue = valueForLength(logicalBottom, containerLogicalHeight);
4665
4666 // Solve for 'margin-bottom'
4667 marginAfterAlias = availableSpace - (logicalTopValue + logicalBottomValue + marginBeforeAlias);
4668 } else {
4669 // Nothing is 'auto', just calculate the values.
4670 marginBeforeAlias = valueForLength(marginBefore, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4671 marginAfterAlias = valueForLength(marginAfter, containerRelativeLogicalWidth);
4672 logicalTopValue = valueForLength(logicalTop, containerLogicalHeight);
4673 // NOTE: It is not necessary to solve for 'bottom' because we don't ever
4674 // use the value.
4675 }
4676
4677 /*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*\
4678 * 6. If at this point the values are over-constrained, ignore the value
4679 * for 'bottom' and solve for that value.
4680 \*-----------------------------------------------------------------------*/
4681 // NOTE: It is not necessary to do this step because we don't end up using
4682 // the value of 'bottom' regardless of whether the values are over-constrained
4683 // or not.
4684
4685 // Use computed values to calculate the vertical position.
4686 LayoutUnit logicalTopPos = logicalTopValue + marginBeforeAlias;
4687 // Border and padding have already been included in computedValues.m_extent.
4688 computeLogicalTopPositionedOffset(logicalTopPos, this, computedValues.m_extent, containerBlock, containerLogicalHeight);
4689 computedValues.m_position = logicalTopPos;
4690}
4691
4692VisiblePosition RenderBox::positionForPoint(const LayoutPoint& point, const RenderFragmentContainer* fragment)
4693{
4694 // no children...return this render object's element, if there is one, and offset 0
4695 if (!firstChild())
4696 return createVisiblePosition(nonPseudoElement() ? firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(nonPseudoElement()) : Position());
4697
4698 if (isTable() && nonPseudoElement()) {
4699 LayoutUnit right = contentWidth() + horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent();
4700 LayoutUnit bottom = contentHeight() + verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent();
4701
4702 if (point.x() < 0 || point.x() > right || point.y() < 0 || point.y() > bottom) {
4703 if (point.x() <= right / 2)
4704 return createVisiblePosition(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(nonPseudoElement()));
4705 return createVisiblePosition(lastPositionInOrAfterNode(nonPseudoElement()));
4706 }
4707 }
4708
4709 // Pass off to the closest child.
4710 LayoutUnit minDist = LayoutUnit::max();
4711 RenderBox* closestRenderer = nullptr;
4712 LayoutPoint adjustedPoint = point;
4713 if (isTableRow())
4714 adjustedPoint.moveBy(location());
4715
4716 for (auto& renderer : childrenOfType<RenderBox>(*this)) {
4717 if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this)) {
4718 ASSERT(fragment);
4719 if (!downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this).objectShouldFragmentInFlowFragment(&renderer, fragment))
4720 continue;
4721 }
4722
4723 if ((!renderer.firstChild() && !renderer.isInline() && !is<RenderBlockFlow>(renderer))
4724 || renderer.style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
4725 continue;
4726
4727 LayoutUnit top = renderer.borderTop() + renderer.paddingTop() + (is<RenderTableRow>(*this) ? 0_lu : renderer.y());
4728 LayoutUnit bottom = top + renderer.contentHeight();
4729 LayoutUnit left = renderer.borderLeft() + renderer.paddingLeft() + (is<RenderTableRow>(*this) ? 0_lu : renderer.x());
4730 LayoutUnit right = left + renderer.contentWidth();
4731
4732 if (point.x() <= right && point.x() >= left && point.y() <= top && point.y() >= bottom) {
4733 if (is<RenderTableRow>(renderer))
4734 return renderer.positionForPoint(point + adjustedPoint - renderer.locationOffset(), fragment);
4735 return renderer.positionForPoint(point - renderer.locationOffset(), fragment);
4736 }
4737
4738 // Find the distance from (x, y) to the box. Split the space around the box into 8 pieces
4739 // and use a different compare depending on which piece (x, y) is in.
4740 LayoutPoint cmp;
4741 if (point.x() > right) {
4742 if (point.y() < top)
4743 cmp = LayoutPoint(right, top);
4744 else if (point.y() > bottom)
4745 cmp = LayoutPoint(right, bottom);
4746 else
4747 cmp = LayoutPoint(right, point.y());
4748 } else if (point.x() < left) {
4749 if (point.y() < top)
4750 cmp = LayoutPoint(left, top);
4751 else if (point.y() > bottom)
4752 cmp = LayoutPoint(left, bottom);
4753 else
4754 cmp = LayoutPoint(left, point.y());
4755 } else {
4756 if (point.y() < top)
4757 cmp = LayoutPoint(point.x(), top);
4758 else
4759 cmp = LayoutPoint(point.x(), bottom);
4760 }
4761
4762 LayoutSize difference = cmp - point;
4763
4764 LayoutUnit dist = difference.width() * difference.width() + difference.height() * difference.height();
4765 if (dist < minDist) {
4766 closestRenderer = &renderer;
4767 minDist = dist;
4768 }
4769 }
4770
4771 if (closestRenderer)
4772 return closestRenderer->positionForPoint(adjustedPoint - closestRenderer->locationOffset(), fragment);
4773
4774 return createVisiblePosition(firstPositionInOrBeforeNode(nonPseudoElement()));
4775}

4777bool RenderBox::shrinkToAvoidFloats() const
4778{
4779 // Floating objects don't shrink. Objects that don't avoid floats don't shrink. Marquees don't shrink.
4780 if ((isInline() && !isHTMLMarquee()) || !avoidsFloats() || isFloating())
4781 return false;
4782
4783 // Only auto width objects can possibly shrink to avoid floats.
4784 return style().width().isAuto();
4785}

4798
4799void RenderBox::addVisualEffectOverflow()
4800{
4801 bool hasBoxShadow = style().boxShadow();
4802 bool hasBorderImageOutsets = style().hasBorderImageOutsets();
4803 bool hasOutline = outlineStyleForRepaint().hasOutlineInVisualOverflow();
4804 if (!hasBoxShadow && !hasBorderImageOutsets && !hasOutline)
4805 return;
4806
4807 addVisualOverflow(applyVisualEffectOverflow(borderBoxRect()));
4808
4809 if (auto* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow())
4810 fragmentedFlow->addFragmentsVisualEffectOverflow(this);
4811}
4812
4813LayoutRect RenderBox::applyVisualEffectOverflow(const LayoutRect& borderBox) const
4814{
4815 bool isFlipped = style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode();
4816 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
4817
4818 LayoutUnit overflowMinX = borderBox.x();
4819 LayoutUnit overflowMaxX = borderBox.maxX();
4820 LayoutUnit overflowMinY = borderBox.y();
4821 LayoutUnit overflowMaxY = borderBox.maxY();
4822
4823 // Compute box-shadow overflow first.
4824 if (style().boxShadow()) {
4825 auto shadowExtent = style().boxShadowExtent();
4826
4827 // In flipped blocks writing modes such as vertical-rl, the physical right shadow value is actually at the lower x-coordinate.
4828 overflowMinX = borderBox.x() + ((!isFlipped || isHorizontal) ? shadowExtent.left() : -shadowExtent.right());
4829 overflowMaxX = borderBox.maxX() + ((!isFlipped || isHorizontal) ? shadowExtent.right() : -shadowExtent.left());
4830 overflowMinY = borderBox.y() + ((!isFlipped || !isHorizontal) ? shadowExtent.top() : -shadowExtent.bottom());
4831 overflowMaxY = borderBox.maxY() + ((!isFlipped || !isHorizontal) ? shadowExtent.bottom() : -shadowExtent.top());
4832 }
4833
4834 // Now compute border-image-outset overflow.
4835 if (style().hasBorderImageOutsets()) {
4836 auto borderOutsets = style().borderImageOutsets();
4837
4838 // In flipped blocks writing modes, the physical sides are inverted. For example in vertical-rl, the right
4839 // border is at the lower x coordinate value.
4840 overflowMinX = std::min(overflowMinX, borderBox.x() - ((!isFlipped || isHorizontal) ? borderOutsets.left() : borderOutsets.right()));
4841 overflowMaxX = std::max(overflowMaxX, borderBox.maxX() + ((!isFlipped || isHorizontal) ? borderOutsets.right() : borderOutsets.left()));
4842 overflowMinY = std::min(overflowMinY, borderBox.y() - ((!isFlipped || !isHorizontal) ? borderOutsets.top() : borderOutsets.bottom()));
4843 overflowMaxY = std::max(overflowMaxY, borderBox.maxY() + ((!isFlipped || !isHorizontal) ? borderOutsets.bottom() : borderOutsets.top()));
4844 }
4845
4846 if (outlineStyleForRepaint().hasOutlineInVisualOverflow()) {
4847 LayoutUnit outlineSize { outlineStyleForRepaint().outlineSize() };
4848 overflowMinX = std::min(overflowMinX, borderBox.x() - outlineSize);
4849 overflowMaxX = std::max(overflowMaxX, borderBox.maxX() + outlineSize);
4850 overflowMinY = std::min(overflowMinY, borderBox.y() - outlineSize);
4851 overflowMaxY = std::max(overflowMaxY, borderBox.maxY() + outlineSize);
4852 }
4853 // Add in the final overflow with shadows and outsets combined.
4854 return LayoutRect(overflowMinX, overflowMinY, overflowMaxX - overflowMinX, overflowMaxY - overflowMinY);
4855}
4856
4857void RenderBox::addOverflowFromChild(const RenderBox* child, const LayoutSize& delta)
4858{
4859 // Never allow flow threads to propagate overflow up to a parent.
4860 if (child->isRenderFragmentedFlow())
4861 return;
4862
4863 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
4864 if (fragmentedFlow)
4865 fragmentedFlow->addFragmentsOverflowFromChild(this, child, delta);
4866
4867 // Only propagate layout overflow from the child if the child isn't clipping its overflow. If it is, then
4868 // its overflow is internal to it, and we don't care about it. layoutOverflowRectForPropagation takes care of this
4869 // and just propagates the border box rect instead.
4870 LayoutRect childLayoutOverflowRect = child->layoutOverflowRectForPropagation(&style());
4871 childLayoutOverflowRect.move(delta);
4872 addLayoutOverflow(childLayoutOverflowRect);
4873
4874 // Add in visual overflow from the child. Even if the child clips its overflow, it may still
4875 // have visual overflow of its own set from box shadows or reflections. It is unnecessary to propagate this
4876 // overflow if we are clipping our own overflow.
4877 if (child->hasSelfPaintingLayer() || hasOverflowClip())
4878 return;
4879 LayoutRect childVisualOverflowRect = child->visualOverflowRectForPropagation(&style());
4880 childVisualOverflowRect.move(delta);
4881 addVisualOverflow(childVisualOverflowRect);
4882}
4883
4884void RenderBox::addLayoutOverflow(const LayoutRect& rect)
4885{
4886 LayoutRect clientBox = flippedClientBoxRect();
4887 if (clientBox.contains(rect) || rect.isEmpty())
4888 return;
4889
4890 // For overflow clip objects, we don't want to propagate overflow into unreachable areas.
4891 LayoutRect overflowRect(rect);
4892 if (hasOverflowClip() || isRenderView()) {
4893 // Overflow is in the block's coordinate space and thus is flipped for horizontal-bt and vertical-rl
4894 // writing modes. At this stage that is actually a simplification, since we can treat horizontal-tb/bt as the same
4895 // and vertical-lr/rl as the same.
4896 bool hasTopOverflow = isTopLayoutOverflowAllowed();
4897 bool hasLeftOverflow = isLeftLayoutOverflowAllowed();
4898
4899 if (!hasTopOverflow)
4900 overflowRect.shiftYEdgeTo(std::max(overflowRect.y(), clientBox.y()));
4901 else
4902 overflowRect.shiftMaxYEdgeTo(std::min(overflowRect.maxY(), clientBox.maxY()));
4903 if (!hasLeftOverflow)
4904 overflowRect.shiftXEdgeTo(std::max(overflowRect.x(), clientBox.x()));
4905 else
4906 overflowRect.shiftMaxXEdgeTo(std::min(overflowRect.maxX(), clientBox.maxX()));
4907
4908 // Now re-test with the adjusted rectangle and see if it has become unreachable or fully
4909 // contained.
4910 if (clientBox.contains(overflowRect) || overflowRect.isEmpty())
4911 return;
4912 }
4913
4914 if (!m_overflow)
4915 m_overflow = adoptRef(new RenderOverflow(clientBox, borderBoxRect()));
4916
4917 m_overflow->addLayoutOverflow(overflowRect);
4918}
4919
4920void RenderBox::addVisualOverflow(const LayoutRect& rect)
4921{
4922 LayoutRect borderBox = borderBoxRect();
4923 if (borderBox.contains(rect) || rect.isEmpty())
4924 return;
4925
4926 if (!m_overflow)
4927 m_overflow = adoptRef(new RenderOverflow(flippedClientBoxRect(), borderBox));
4928
4929 m_overflow->addVisualOverflow(rect);
4930}
4931
4932void RenderBox::clearOverflow()
4933{
4934 m_overflow = nullptr;
4935 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
4936 if (fragmentedFlow)
4937 fragmentedFlow->clearFragmentsOverflow(this);
4938}

4940bool RenderBox::percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable() const
4941{
4942 // Do this to avoid duplicating all the logic that already exists when computing
4943 // an actual percentage height.
4944 Length fakeLength(100, LengthType::Percent);
4945 return computePercentageLogicalHeight(fakeLength) != std::nullopt;
4946}
4947
4948bool RenderBox::hasUnsplittableScrollingOverflow() const
4949{
4950 // We will paginate as long as we don't scroll overflow in the pagination direction.
4951 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
4952 if ((isHorizontal && !scrollsOverflowY()) || (!isHorizontal && !scrollsOverflowX()))
4953 return false;
4954
4955 // We do have overflow. We'll still be willing to paginate as long as the block
4956 // has auto logical height, auto or undefined max-logical-height and a zero or auto min-logical-height.
4957 // Note this is just a heuristic, and it's still possible to have overflow under these
4958 // conditions, but it should work out to be good enough for common cases. Paginating overflow
4959 // with scrollbars present is not the end of the world and is what we used to do in the old model anyway.
4960 return !style().logicalHeight().isIntrinsicOrAuto()
4961 || (!style().logicalMaxHeight().isIntrinsicOrAuto() && !style().logicalMaxHeight().isUndefined() && (!style().logicalMaxHeight().isPercentOrCalculated() || percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable()))
4962 || (!style().logicalMinHeight().isIntrinsicOrAuto() && style().logicalMinHeight().isPositive() && (!style().logicalMinHeight().isPercentOrCalculated() || percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable()));
4963}
4964
4965bool RenderBox::isUnsplittableForPagination() const
4966{
4967 return isReplaced()
4968 || hasUnsplittableScrollingOverflow()
4969 || (parent() && isWritingModeRoot())
4970 || (isFloating() && style().styleType() == PseudoId::FirstLetter && style().initialLetterDrop() > 0)
4971 || shouldApplySizeContainment(*this);
4972}
4973
4974LayoutUnit RenderBox::lineHeight(bool /*firstLine*/, LineDirectionMode direction, LinePositionMode /*linePositionMode*/) const
4975{

5008
5009LayoutRect RenderBox::visualOverflowRectForPropagation(const RenderStyle* parentStyle) const
5010{
5011 // If the writing modes of the child and parent match, then we don't have to
5012 // do anything fancy. Just return the result.
5013 LayoutRect rect = visualOverflowRect();
5014 if (parentStyle->writingMode() == style().writingMode())
5015 return rect;
5016
5017 // We are putting ourselves into our parent's coordinate space. If there is a flipped block mismatch
5018 // in a particular axis, then we have to flip the rect along that axis.
5019 if (style().writingMode() == WritingMode::RightToLeft || parentStyle->writingMode() == WritingMode::RightToLeft)
5020 rect.setX(width() - rect.maxX());
5021 else if (style().writingMode() == WritingMode::BottomToTop || parentStyle->writingMode() == WritingMode::BottomToTop)
5022 rect.setY(height() - rect.maxY());
5023
5024 return rect;
5025}

5029 LayoutRect rect = layoutOverflowRectForPropagation(parentStyle);
5030 if (!parentStyle->isHorizontalWritingMode())
5031 return rect.transposedRect();
5032 return rect;
5033}
5034
5035LayoutRect RenderBox::layoutOverflowRectForPropagation(const RenderStyle* parentStyle) const
5036{
5037 // Only propagate interior layout overflow if we don't clip it.
5038 LayoutRect rect = borderBoxRect();
5039 if (!shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this) && !hasOverflowClip())
5040 rect.unite(layoutOverflowRect());
5041
5042 bool hasTransform = this->hasTransform();
5043 // While a stickily positioned renderer is also inflow positioned, they stretch the overflow rect with their inflow geometry
5044 // (as opposed to the paint geometry) because they are not stationary.
5045 bool paintGeometryAffectsLayoutOverflow = hasTransform || (isInFlowPositioned() && !isStickilyPositioned());
5046 if (paintGeometryAffectsLayoutOverflow) {
5047 // If we are relatively positioned or if we have a transform, then we have to convert
5048 // this rectangle into physical coordinates, apply relative positioning and transforms
5049 // to it, and then convert it back.
5050 // It ensures that the overflow rect tracks the paint geometry and not the inflow layout position.
5051 flipForWritingMode(rect);
5052
5053 if (hasTransform && hasLayer())
5054 rect = layer()->currentTransform().mapRect(rect);
5055
5056 if (isInFlowPositioned())
5057 rect.move(offsetForInFlowPosition());
5058
5059 // Now we need to flip back.
5060 flipForWritingMode(rect);
5061 }
5062
5063 // If the writing modes of the child and parent match, then we don't have to
5064 // do anything fancy. Just return the result.
5065 if (parentStyle->writingMode() == style().writingMode())
5066 return rect;
5067
5068 // We are putting ourselves into our parent's coordinate space. If there is a flipped block mismatch
5069 // in a particular axis, then we have to flip the rect along that axis.
5070 if (style().writingMode() == WritingMode::RightToLeft || parentStyle->writingMode() == WritingMode::RightToLeft)
5071 rect.setX(width() - rect.maxX());
5072 else if (style().writingMode() == WritingMode::BottomToTop || parentStyle->writingMode() == WritingMode::BottomToTop)
5073 rect.setY(height() - rect.maxY());
5074
5075 return rect;
5076}
5077
5078LayoutRect RenderBox::flippedClientBoxRect() const
5079{
5080 // Because of the special coordinate system used for overflow rectangles (not quite logical, not
5081 // quite physical), we need to flip the block progression coordinate in vertical-rl and
5082 // horizontal-bt writing modes. Apart from that, this method does the same as clientBoxRect().
5083
5084 LayoutUnit left = borderLeft();
5085 LayoutUnit top = borderTop();
5086 LayoutUnit right = borderRight();
5087 LayoutUnit bottom = borderBottom();
5088 // Calculate physical padding box.
5089 LayoutRect rect(left, top, width() - left - right, height() - top - bottom);
5090 // Flip block progression axis if writing mode is vertical-rl or horizontal-bt.
5091 flipForWritingMode(rect);
5092 // Subtract space occupied by scrollbars. They are at their physical edge in this coordinate
5093 // system, so order is important here: first flip, then subtract scrollbars.
5094 if (shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft() && isHorizontalWritingMode())
5095 rect.move(verticalScrollbarWidth(), 0);
5096 rect.contract(verticalScrollbarWidth(), horizontalScrollbarHeight());
5097 return rect;
5098}

5110LayoutPoint RenderBox::flipForWritingModeForChild(const RenderBox* child, const LayoutPoint& point) const
5111{
5112 if (!style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
5113 return point;
5114
5115 // The child is going to add in its x() and y(), so we have to make sure it ends up in
5116 // the right place.
5117 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
5118 return LayoutPoint(point.x(), point.y() + height() - child->height() - (2 * child->y()));
5119 return LayoutPoint(point.x() + width() - child->width() - (2 * child->x()), point.y());
5120}
