5210bool RenderBox::shouldIgnoreAspectRatio() const
5211{
5212 return !style().hasAspectRatio() || isTablePart();
5213}
5214
5215static inline bool shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatioAndInsets(const RenderBox& renderer)
5216{
5217 if (!renderer.isOutOfFlowPositioned())
5218 return false;
5219
5220 auto& style = renderer.style();
5221 if (!style.logicalWidth().isAuto()) {
5222 // Not applicable for aspect ratio computation.
5223 return false;
5224 }
5225 // When both left and right are set, the out-of-flow positioned box is horizontally constrained and aspect ratio for the logical width is not applicable.
5226 auto hasConstrainedWidth = (!style.logicalLeft().isAuto() && !style.logicalRight().isAuto()) || renderer.intrinsicLogicalWidth();
5227 if (hasConstrainedWidth)
5228 return false;
5229
5230 // When both top and bottom are set, the out-of-flow positioned box is vertically constrained and it can be used as if it had a non-auto height value.
5231 auto hasConstrainedHeight = !style.logicalTop().isAuto() && !style.logicalBottom().isAuto();
5232 if (!hasConstrainedHeight)
5233 return false;
5234 // FIXME: This could probably be omitted and let the callers handle the height check (as they seem to be doing anyway).
5235 return style.logicalHeight().isAuto();
5236}
5237
5238bool RenderBox::shouldComputeLogicalHeightFromAspectRatio() const
5239{
5240 if (shouldIgnoreAspectRatio())
5241 return false;
5242
5243 if (shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatioAndInsets(*this))
5244 return false;
5245
5246 auto h = style().logicalHeight();
5247 return h.isAuto() || h.isIntrinsic() || (!isOutOfFlowPositioned() && h.isPercentOrCalculated() && !percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable());
5248}
5249
5250bool RenderBox::shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio() const
5251{
5252 if (shouldIgnoreAspectRatio())
5253 return false;
5254
5255 auto isResolvablePercentageHeight = [&] {
5256 return style().logicalHeight().isPercentOrCalculated() && (isOutOfFlowPositioned() || percentageLogicalHeightIsResolvable());
5257 };
5258 return hasOverridingLogicalHeight() || shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatioAndInsets(*this) || style().logicalHeight().isFixed() || isResolvablePercentageHeight();
5259}
5260
5261LayoutUnit RenderBox::computeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio(RenderFragmentContainer* fragment) const
5262{
5263 ASSERT(shouldComputeLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio());
5264 auto computedValues = computeLogicalHeight(logicalHeight(), logicalTop());
5265 LayoutUnit logicalHeightforAspectRatio = computedValues.m_extent;
5266
5267 auto logicalWidth = inlineSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), LayoutUnit(style().logicalAspectRatio()), style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), logicalHeightforAspectRatio);
5268
5269 LayoutUnit containerWidthInInlineDirection = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, containingBlockLogicalWidthForContentInFragment(fragment));
5270 return constrainLogicalWidthInFragmentByMinMax(logicalWidth, containerWidthInInlineDirection, *containingBlock(), fragment, AllowIntrinsic::No);
5271}
5272
5273std::pair<LayoutUnit, LayoutUnit> RenderBox::computeMinMaxLogicalWidthFromAspectRatio() const
5274{
5275 auto ratio = LayoutUnit { style().logicalAspectRatio() };
5276 LayoutUnit blockMinSize = constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(LayoutUnit(), std::nullopt);
5277 LayoutUnit blockMaxSize = constrainLogicalHeightByMinMax(LayoutUnit::max(), std::nullopt);
5278 LayoutUnit transferredMinSize = LayoutUnit();
5279 LayoutUnit transferredMaxSize = LayoutUnit::max();
5280 if (blockMinSize > LayoutUnit())
5281 transferredMinSize = inlineSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), ratio, style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), blockMinSize);
5282 if (blockMaxSize != LayoutUnit::max())
5283 transferredMaxSize = inlineSizeFromAspectRatio(horizontalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), verticalBorderAndPaddingExtent(), ratio, style().boxSizingForAspectRatio(), blockMaxSize);
5284 // Minimum size wins over maximum size.
5285 transferredMaxSize = std::max(transferredMaxSize, transferredMinSize);
5286 return { transferredMinSize, transferredMaxSize };
5287}

5320LayoutRect RenderBox::absoluteAnchorRectWithScrollMargin(bool* insideFixed) const
5321{
5322 LayoutRect anchorRect = absoluteAnchorRect(insideFixed);
5323 const LengthBox& scrollMargin = style().scrollMargin();
5324 if (scrollMargin.isZero())
5325 return anchorRect;
5326
5327 // The scroll snap specification says that the scroll-margin should be applied in the
5328 // coordinate system of the scroll container and applied to the rectangular bounding
5329 // box of the transformed border box of the target element.
5330 // See https://www.w3.org/TR/css-scroll-snap-1/#scroll-margin.
5331 const LayoutSize boxSize = size();
5332 const LayoutBoxExtent margin(
5333 valueForLength(scrollMargin.top(), boxSize.height()),
5334 valueForLength(scrollMargin.right(), boxSize.width()),
5335 valueForLength(scrollMargin.bottom(), boxSize.height()),
5336 valueForLength(scrollMargin.left(), boxSize.width()));
5337 anchorRect.expand(margin);
5338
5339 return anchorRect;
5340}
5341
5342LayoutBoxExtent RenderBox::scrollPaddingForViewportRect(const LayoutRect& viewportRect)
5343{
5344 // We are using minimumValueForLength here, because scroll-padding values might be "auto". WebKit currently
5345 // interprets "auto" as 0. See: https://drafts.csswg.org/css-scroll-snap-1/#propdef-scroll-padding
5346 const auto& padding = style().scrollPadding();
5347 return LayoutBoxExtent(
5348 minimumValueForLength(padding.top(), viewportRect.height()), minimumValueForLength(padding.right(), viewportRect.width()),
5349 minimumValueForLength(padding.bottom(), viewportRect.height()), minimumValueForLength(padding.left(), viewportRect.width()));
5350}
